<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="MRK" stage="Final" version="Q">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="John Wimbish" created="2009-10-05 05:38:29Z" when="2009-10-05 05:38:29Z" stage="Draft">(consider larger font for printing first books, because of è and implosives); TSC partner project; 1st draft by Lazarus Aplugi,.Michael Sina, Dr. Ayub Ranoh following BIS; 2nd &amp; 3rd draft revised by Lazarus Aplugi,.Michael Sina, Dr. Ayub Ranoh following KM Mark; 4th draft exegetical, discourse and naturalness pass by Lazarus Aplugi,.Michael Sina, Dr. Ayub Ranoh with Chuck Grimes in Darwin, early March 2000; UNS pass by Chuck (with Lazarus [most sessions], Michael, or Ayub) in Kupang March-April 2000 with two groups: am group came in from Ndao Island, pm group from Kupang Ndao community; back translation by Chuck; 120 key terms by Chuck; consultant checked by David Glasgow with Chuck in Kupang, 8-16 May 2000; checked *priest, a'a-ari, Jahudi, June 2007; ch.14-16 revised to Kupang-R Feb 2009 for Easter book;</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Markus</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Lii Lolo Be'a nèti Lamatua Yesus<bt>*Good Story about *Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">madhutu sasuri<bt>following the writing of</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Markus<bt>Markus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Ne'e ne, Lii Lolo Be'a lula-nèti Ana Ama Lamatua.<bt>[NOTE: Mark has undergone significant revisions, but BT is not yet caught up. Dec 2011.] This here, is the Good Story, from the beginning, about/from the Child of *God.</bt><note reference="1:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii padhai &lt;Ana Ama Lamatua&gt; abhu boe ètu d'ara sasuri uuru sèra.<bt>The word 'Child of God' is not found in the oldest writings (coll = collective plural).</bt></note>Ngara na Yesus Kristus, dhu Ama Lamatua paj'uj'u karèi nèti uru ka mai. Lii lolo Na mulai sèmi ne'e:<bt>His name is Yesus *Kristus, who God designated/appointed from long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis, tuka sarani dhèu, bhoke j'ara hia Lamatua Yesus<bt>Yohanis, the Tukang (person habitually identified with activity X) who *Baptizes People, opens the way/path for the *Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 3:1-12; Lukas 3:1-18; Yohanis 1:19-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Lod'o Yesus sab'a mèka sasab'a Na, Ama Lamatua pua uru dhèu èci, ngara na Yohanis, la'e tao tèke j'ara hia Yesus dhu mai bèli-camèd'a. Lula uru èèna, Ama Lamatua peka le dènge dhèu nèti lii padhai Na, ngara na Yesaya. Na suri tèke, peka na,<bt>Before Yesus had begun His work, God first ordered a person, named Yohanis, to go do/prepare the road/path/way for Yesus who was coming in the future (lit. tomorrow next day). Because [lula] previously, God had already said using a person who spoke His message. His name was *Grandpa/Cultural.Personality Yesaya. And he had written, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ne'e ne, lii karej'e-karae nèti Yesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ne'e ne, lii karej'e-karae nèti Yesus Kristus, Ana Ama Lamatua.; 4: Lii karej'e-karae ne'e, j'aj'i sèmi dhu Nabi Yesaya suri:</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nèti 1) dari 2) tentang; Ama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">nèti 1) dari 2) tentang; Ama Lamatua = Creator God (entrenched in region)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nanene! Ja'a pua le dhèu èci, ho bhoke j'ara hia Èu.<bt>"Listen! I have ordered a person, to open the path for You.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Aku Ama Lamatua, ne'e ne Ana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">"Aku Ama Lamatua, ne'e ne Ana paleha Ja'a.; 4: Ja'a hia uru nèngu mai nèt'i èu, ho sè'na ka na pamera j'ara [bhoke j'ara] hia.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Meliaki 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Dhèu èèna la'e asa d'ara mamoo, ho na rodhe, peka na,<bt>That person, goes to a wide.empty place, to call.out, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Miu aa'i-aa'i mi tao pabe'a ku j'ara, sèna ka sèmi mere mamai Lamatua!<bt>'You(pl) all fix/make-good the path, so you can be ready for the coming of the *Lord/Master!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Pamera j'ara ho soru mamai Na.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Make the path smooth for His coming.'"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="find bttr altrnativ for /gh/ --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">find bttr altrnativ for /gh/ -- VV onset</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="'Sadia j'ara hia Lamatua, pamera j'ara-j'ara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">'Sadia j'ara hia Lamatua, pamera j'ara-j'ara [pamola j'ara] dhu Lamatua kako.&gt;&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4-6" />Ra pangare dhèu ne'e, Yohanis, tuka sarani dhèu. Era pea nèngu ètu d'ara mamoo. Kodho na tao nèti rèu badha onta, dhara hake na, tao nèti ka'uri badha. Nganga'a nèngu kabara dènge dhua nasu oni.<bt>This person, they call him Yohanis, the Tukang characterised by *Baptising (method neutral-assimilated Malay loan) People. The place where he stayed/lived was a wide.empty place. His clothes were made from the fur of an onta (BI loan) animal, his waistband was made from the skin of anomals. His food was grasshoppers and honey.</bt><note reference="1:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Dhèu Aae sèra 1:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Lod'o èèna, dhèu ae nèti kota Yerusalem dènge propensi Yudea, mai paraga dènge Yohanis ètu era pea na. Dhèu se mai neo rèdhi Yohanis, aa nanene lii holo-nori na. Na peka, &lt;&lt;Hua iia miu ele-ho'a nèti tatao karehe, sèna ka Ama Lamatua saku eele sasala-sasigo miu. Èle èèna miu sarani uuru ku j'aj'i mi tadha, na, miu be'a le dènge Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, many people from the city (assim. Malay loan) of Yerusalem, and the province (loan) of Yudea, came to meet Yohanis there at that place where he stayed. Those people came wanting to see Yohanis, and to hear his advice (=what he had to say). He spoke like this, "It's best if you(pl) get.rid.of the deeds of your bad ways, so that God can *wipe away (forgive) your *wrongs. Then you should be *baptised, to be a sign, that you are good/right with God/Lord."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lula lii lole Yohanis ne'e ka,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Lula lii lole Yohanis ne'e ka, dhau-dhau mai nèt'i Rae Yudea, ka nèt'i Yerusalem lasi nanene lii lolo nori, dhu Yohanis lole. Dhèu se'e aa'i-aa'i ra dhaa [mengaku] sasala rèngu, ka Yohanis sarani si, ètu dara loko Yordan.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pantes: not necessarily every last person,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">pantes: not necessarily every last person, but lots, by a hyperbole common in Greek. Could be "plenny plenny," but "all" is OK.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00296C.tif" rtfFormat="width:6cm;textWrapping:around;verticalPosition:top;horizontalPosition:right">Yohanis, tuka sarani dhèu<bt>Yohanis, the Tukang who baptises people</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Nèti èèna ka, dhèu se'e bhoka sasala rèngu, ka Yohanis sarani si ètu loko Yarden.<bt>Because of that, those people *confessed their wrongs (lit. opened their insides) and Yohanis baptised them, there at the Yarden river.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ele ho'a = tobat; li holo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ele ho'a = tobat; li holo nori = nasehat; wol = bulu domba; dosa = between us &amp; God; sala between us &amp; God, &amp; man w/man; a'ae = nafas, breath (n), doesn't work for Holy Spirit (parallel used in Sabu)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mèdha papake Yohanis tao nèt'i rou"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Mèdha papake Yohanis tao nèt'i rou badha onta. Dhara hake na, tao nèt'i ka'uri, aa nganga'a nginu na kabara, dènge dhua nasu oni j'ami.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ka na peka hari, &lt;&lt;Bèli-camèd'a dhèu èci mai, dhu kapai risi nèti ja'a. Lula ja'a ne haha d'ai seli, neo j'aj'i ana pua-paleha èèna ka, lèke boe sa hèi.<bt>And he spoke like this, "In the future (tomorrow-next day) a person who is more important that me is coming. As for me, I am very low/unimportant, wanting to be [his] *servant, even that, is not even a good match.</bt><note reference="1:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani asli suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;pacud'u ho lècu dhari salapa Na hèi, ja'a nia boe.&gt;&gt; Sasoa na, Yohanis ne dhèu haha seli, de masi ka j'aj'i dhèu pajuu nèti Lamatua Yesus, nia boe sa hèi.</note><v n="8" />Ja'a ne dhodhoka sarani miu dènge èi di, te ngaa Nèngu tao risi eele nèti ja'a. Te Na papènu d'ara miu dènge Roh Ama Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci.&gt;&gt;<bt>As for me, I only/merely baptise you(pl) with water, but [te ngaa] He will do much more/better than I. He will fill your insides with the *Spirit of God who is *Holy (straight-clean=without deceit and without blemish)."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="È'le èèna ka, Yohanis peka mi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">È'le èèna ka, Yohanis peka mi dhau se'e, "Dhèu limuri hari nèt'i ja'a, ho na mai bè'li camèda Nèngu kapai risi nèt'i ja'a. Nèt'i èèna ka, ho ladhe pacu'dhu bhoke dhari salapa Na, ja'a ho nia boe hèi.; 8: Ja'a sarani miu dènge &lt;èi, te ngaa Nèngu sarani miu dènge Roh Ama Lamatua.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ngangee = pikiran; samanga = jiwa,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ngangee = pikiran; samanga = jiwa, can imply person is dead, but not necessarily; Samanga bho! = Lu sonde ada pung apa-apa! ; 'a'èra = kekuatan; kaj'alu = kotor (physical or social); mola = lurus, tulus (j'ara, dara, dhèu) but for humans, awk for God; Ant = koe, kapod'e ; mèu = bersih (pikiran, siang, pintar); mera-milu = damai-sejahtera (mera = rata, milu = licin); mola-mèci = lurus betul, tidak ada cacat, tidak bengkok sedikitpun</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis sarani Lamatua Yesus<bt>Yohanis baptises the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 3:13-17; Lukas 3:21-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ca lod'o hari, Yesus la'e nèti rae Nasaret ètu rai Galilea, ka Na paraga dènge Yohanis. Èle èèna ka Yohanis sarani Ne ètu loko Yarden.<bt>One day, Yesus went from the village of Nasaret in the area of Galilea, and met with Yohanis. Then Yohanis baptised Him, at the Yarden river.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kai egeneto: scene setting best expressed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">kai egeneto: scene setting best expressed by a comma after "time"</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ropa Yesus bhodho nèti d'ara èi mai, Na ladhe, na, liru bhoke eele, ka Roh Ama Lamatua puru mai sama sèmi koro j'aha ci'u, puru mai asa Yesus.<bt>When Yesus appeared from out of the water, saw (no subject) the sky opened, and the Spirit of God descended came like a pidgeon/dove, descended came toward Yesus.</bt><v n="11" />Kaca'a la, ra tadèngi lii Ama Lamatua nèti dedha-liru, peka na,<bt>And suddenly, they (non-referential, impersonal construction) heard the voice of God from up in the sky saying like this,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lod'o èèna Yesus mai nèt'i rae"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Lod'o èèna Yesus mai nèt'i rae Galilea, ka Yohanis sarani Yesus ètu dara loko Yordan.; 9: Ca lod'o hari, Yesus la'e nèt'i rae Nasaret ètu rai Galilea, ka paraga dènge Yohanis. è'le èèna ka Yohanis sarani Ne, ètu loko Yarden.; 10: Ropa Yesus kalua nèti dara èi, ladhe nèdhi liru [ra'i liru] manyè'le [boka] ka Roh Ama Lamatua sama sè'mi koro-'èi, puru mai asa dedha Yesus.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sa from asa; koro èi ci'u"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sa from asa; koro èi ci'u = wild bird on Ndao, can't tame; koro j'aha = dove, pidgeon</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Èu ne, Ana pasue Ja'a,<bt>"You here, are my favoured/loved Child,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Èu pakarej'e taruu d'ara Ja'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>You continually make My insides happy."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ra-3p, hr imprsonal, non-rfrntial"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ra-3p, hr imprsonal, non-rfrntial</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ropa &lt;è'le èèna ka, nèbhu boe,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ropa &lt;è'le èèna ka, nèbhu boe, tadè'ngi lii Ama Lamatua nèti surga: "Èu ne'e ana pasue Ja'a, èu pakarej'e dara Ja'a.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 22:2, Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 2:7, Yesaya 42:1, Mateos 3:17, 12:18, Markus 9:7, Lukas 3:22</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01656b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm">Yohanis sarani Lamatua Yesus<bt>Yohanis baptises the Lord Yesus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu aae nidhu dadugu neo pamanahu Yesus<bt>*Satan (King of Evil.Spirits) *tempts wanting to bring down Yesus</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nidhu neo pamanahu Yesus è'tu dara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Nidhu neo pamanahu Yesus è'tu dara mamoo; Dhèu aae nidhu = term already in use; nidhu = setan (Tim/Rtoe = nitu)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:1-11; Lukas 4:1-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Nèbhu boe ka, Roh Ama Lamatua jajuku Yesus asa d'ara mamoo la'e.<bt>Not long after that the Spirit of God pushed Yesus to go to a wide.empty place.</bt><v n="13" />Na pea dènge badha hui ètu èèna, èpa nguru lod'o. Ka dhèu aae nidhu mai dadugu tenge j'ara sèna ka Yesus madhutu nèngu, te ngaa tao nare boe. Èle èèna ka, ana pajuu nèti Ama Lamatua puru mai lalau-lalo'o Ne.<bt>He stayed with the wild animals there, forty days. And *Satan came and *tempted him looking for a way for Yesus to follow him, but it didn't work. After that, *angels (servants from God) descended came (serial vbs) and *served (took care of) Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hahi hui = babi fuik; pajuu-paleha"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hahi hui = babi fuik; pajuu-paleha = orang suruhan; angel/angels = number neutral; boe = NEG vs. bhoe = udang; lalau-lo'o = urus, layani (also lalau-lalo'o)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaa: da Devil &quot;Wild animals&quot; is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">Satanaa: da Devil "Wild animals" is part of the setting for Pidgin, so moved to connect with "boonies".<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>Implicit "come" to get them on site. Not "take care Jesus," because the reference is clear from the cast of characters and the semantics. In this case the pronoun works.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus la'e Galilea ho lole Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua<bt>Lord Yesus goes to Galilea, [and] speaks the *Word/Message/Advice of God</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="holo nori -menasehati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">holo nori -menasehati</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:12-17; Lukas 4:14-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Lod'o dhu kèpe rare Yohanis tuka sarani pamaso asa d'ara bèdho, nèbhu boe ka Yesus pakèd'i la'e propensi Galilea. La'e lole Lii Lolo Be'a nèti Ama Lamatua ètu nèi.<bt>When they arrested (serial) Yohanis the Tukang Baptiser and put him into jail, not long after that Yesus left (and) went to the province of Galilea. He went and told the *Good News about God there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Tukang Sarani&quot; from the first section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">"Tukang Sarani" from the first section.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ka Na peka,<bt>And He said,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karej'e-karae = berita sukacita"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">karej'e-karae = berita sukacita</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Mi nanene! Lod'o Ama Lamatua d'ai kèna!<bt>"You(pl) listen! God's day/time has arrived!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dai kèna = su sampe, su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dai kèna = su sampe, su dekat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Limuri ne, dhèu aa'i-aa'i re'a, na, Ama Lamatua nèd'u le paredha karèi nèti uru ka.<bt>So in not a long time *humans (people of the earth-below) here will know, God holds *government/kingdom and has from before.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nèti èèna ka, miu hud'i tèke eele ka tatao karehe sèra,<bt>Because of that, you(pl) leave.behind your evil deeds (coll-PL),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ho lèpa madhutu Ama Lamatua.<bt>to follow the *will/desires of God and the *Word/Teachings of God."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ele ho'a nèti tatao miu, dhu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ele ho'a nèti tatao miu, dhu karehe [loe ele ka nèti tatao dhu karehe] kè'pe pa'ère [sanèd'e paère] lii lolo nori [lii karej'e-karae] Ama Lamatua.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Hèia parcaya ka Lii Holo-Nori Nèngu kahèi.&gt;&gt;<note reference="1:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus hag'e nare ana madhutu Na<bt>Lord Yesus sets.aside His *followers</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hag'e = pisahkan, pilah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hag'e = pisahkan, pilah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:18-22; Lukas 5:1-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ca lod'o hari, Yesus kako re sebhe dano Galilea, ka nèdhi dhèu dua, ngara ra Simon dènge ari na Anderias. Sasab'a rèngu bèli-bèli èèna, j'ala i'a.<bt>One day, Yesus was walking along the edge of lake (loan) Galilea, and he saw a person, named Simon with his younger.sibling.same.sex Anderias. Their daily work was just cast-netting for fish.</bt><v n="17" />Ka Yesus paroa nare dua ra, peka na, &lt;&lt;We! Mai madhutu Ja'a! Miu tema tenge i'a, te ngaa Ja'a neo aj'a miu, sèna ka j'aj'i dhèu tenge samanga.&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus summoned the two of them, "We! Come follow Me! You look for fish, but I want to teach you(pl) to become people who look for *souls (if 'people' as object here would imply sorcerer)."</bt><v n="18" />Ropa ra nanene rare, hèia ra tèke eele j'ala rèngu, ka lasi dènge madhutu Ne.<bt>When they heard him, then [hèia] they left behind their castnet, and they went following with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mananga = lagoon, pool filled at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mananga = lagoon, pool filled at high tid from th sa, but not from a river; 17: tng = cari; samanga = jiwa (ovrlap with roh), whn prson dis, samanga tidak ada lagi, mamuri = khidupan (lif-forc); samanga (archaic) spirit of dad prson whos prsnc and involvmnt continus, but not commonly undrstood in this sns today. nidhu (archaic) also usd as spirit of dad prson, but now mans stan, vil spirit; tenge dhèu = meminang nona; 18:</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ka hèia Yesus gale dua ra:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ka hèia Yesus gale dua ra: "Mai madhutu Ja'a, sè'na ka, Ja'a aj'a [nori] miu j'aj'i j'ala dhau.&gt;&gt;; 17: Ka Yesus paroa nare dua si, "We! Mai madhutu Ja'a! Miu tenge i'a, tènga Ja'a neo aj'a miu, ho sè'na ka j'aj'i dhau tènge samanga.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01682b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus kako hari ciki, ka nèdhi ana-ana Sabadeus, a'a ngara na Yakobis, aa ari ngara na Yohanis. Dua ra lalau paie pèku ètu dedha koha.<bt>After that, Yesus walked on a little, and he saw the children of Sabadius, the older.sibling's name was Yakobis, and the younger.sibling's name was Yohanis. The two of them were arranging their dragnet on top of a boat.</bt><v n="20" />Ka Yesus paroa dua ra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mai we! Madhutu Ja'a!&gt;&gt; Ropa ra tadèngi rare lii Yesus, ka dua ra tèke eele ama ra, dènge dhèu sab'a sa ètu dedha koha, lasi dènge ka madhutu Yesus.<bt>And Yesus summoned the two of them saying, "Come, we! Follow me!" When they heard Yesus' voice the two of them left behind their father, with the workers there on top of the boat, and went off and followed Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paie pa-ie 'bekin bae-bae, atur, susun';"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">paie pa-ie 'bekin bae-bae, atur, susun'; pa'ie = perbaiki dgn jahit, pèku = pukat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus lalèta eele nidhu nèti dhèu èci dhu pea ètu kota Kapernaum<bt>Lord Yesus *evicts *evil.spirit from a person who lives in the city of Kapernaum</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 4:31-37)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na dhèu èpa sèra lasi d'ai kota Kapernaum. Lod'o èèna, lod'o manèngi-mangaj'i dhèu Yahudi.<bt>After that, Yesus with His followers, the four of them went until they arrived at the city of Kapernaum. That day was the day of *worship of the *Jahudi people.</bt><note reference="1:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lod'o sabaj'a dhèu Yahudi, ra pangare na &lt;Hari Sabat&gt;. Lod'o èèna, dhèu sab'a boe.<bt>The day of worship4 of Jahudi people, they call 'Hari Sabat'. On that day, people don't work.</bt></note>Ka Yesus la'e asa d'ara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i, ka Na lole Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua ètu èèna.<bt>And Yesus went inside the *house of worship, and He told them the *Word of God there.</bt><v n="22" />Dhèu ae sèra malaa, nanene lii padhai Na, lula Nèngu ne'a mèu lii dhu Nèngu lole, risi nèti mese-mese agama Yahudi.<bt>Many people there were *amazed hearing what He said, because He knew cleanly the things He was saying, more than the teachers of the Jahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manèngi-mangaj'i = sembahyang-menyembah; èmu sabaj'a ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">manèngi-mangaj'i = sembahyang-menyembah; èmu sabaj'a = rumah sembahyang</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:28-29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Lod'o èèna, abhu dhèu èci dhu nidhu tao. Dhèu ne'e la'e asa d'ara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i kahèi. Kaca'a laa na pakèce, peka na,<bt>That day/time, there was a person afflicted with a sickness which an evil.spirit had caused. This person also came into the house of worship, and suddenly he screamed and said,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en: &quot;take ova&quot; and &quot;let go&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">en: "take ova" and "let go" is the culturally appropriate way to talk about a person being under the control of an outside power. "In" and "go out" or "throw out" doesn't make a lot of sense. At least two of the translators have had first hand experience with this kind of situation.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />&lt;&lt;We! Yesus, dhèu Nasaret! Ngaa unu Èu dènge ji'i! Èu mai ho pa'ele iie ji'i, do? Ji'i tadhe Èu. Èu ne'e ka dhu mai nèti Ama Lamatua. Èu ne'e Dhèu dhu dènge boe sasala-sasigo.&gt;&gt;<bt>"We! Yesus, a person from Nasaret! What's your business with us(exc)! (rhetorical Q's marked by ! indicating accusation--following Marten's paper, liked by team) You've come to destroy us, right? We(exc) know2 you. You here are the one who came from God. You here are the Person who is without *sin2."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lod'o èèna, dhau èci dhu pè'dha"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Lod'o èèna, dhau èci dhu pè'dha nidhu tao, la'e asa dara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i; dhau ne'e maso dènge paradhu, ka na peka,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bo = NG; bhoe = udang;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">bo = NG; bhoe = udang; ji'i = plural; do = tag; sasala-sasigo = cacat-cela</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ka Yesus jèke ne, &lt;&lt;Hutu hèb'a èu na! Rai eele nèti dhèu ne'e!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus spoke.angrily to him, "Shut your mouth! Run off from this person!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jèke = masparak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">jèke = masparak</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Kaca'a laa nidhu tèku ngi'u dhèu ne'e, sama sèmi dhèu dhu pèd'a rèdha. Ka na rai eele nèti dhèu ne'e, dènge lii pakèce.<bt>Suddenly the evil.spirit made the person's body stiff, like a person who is having a convulsion. And he ran off from this person, with a terrifying.scream.</bt><v n="27" />Hèia dhèu ètu d'ara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i sèra, malaa-maloha. Ka ra padhue èci dènge èci, &lt;&lt;Eea! Ngaa ka ne'e? Ne'e ne, lii holo-nori dhu hiu, do? Lii padhai lii Mone heka ne, ele madha, nga! Na paredha nidhu se, ka ra kalua kahèi, madhutu dad'èi Na.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the people there inside the house of worship were amazed2. And they said to each other, "Eea! What's this! This here is a new teaching, right? The words of this (respected) Man are incredible (idiom--disappearing eyes)! He commands the evil.spirits (coll), and they come out also, following His will/desires."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèku = kaku ; rèdha ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tèku = kaku ; rèdha = hela step (convulse?), make (rope) taught,; 27: malaa-maloha = heran; padhue = saling berunding; Eea (heran); Mone = paitua; ele madha nga = idiom (hilang mata) (positive praise); kalua kahei = kaluar ju; se'e = sira/dong; dadei = kehendak, mau-mau</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Several people have remarked on the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">Several people have remarked on the inadequacy of just "?" and "!" for Pidgin. The combination "?!" is what they suggest for something that sounds like a question but which is really a surprised exclamation. kat' exousian: could go either with "teaching" or with "tell". This kind of sits on the fence.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Hèia dhèu palolo lème era, ètu d'ara rae-rae propensi Galilea.<bt>Then people told the story all over that region, in the villages of the province of Galilea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haia = hia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">haia = hia</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle papèd'a ina dhèu èmu Petrus, dènge papèd'a dhèu-dhèu leo<bt>Yesus heals the sickness of Petrus' mother-in-law (lit. mother of the person of the house), and sicknesses of other people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:14-17; Lukas 4:38-41)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Lod'o rèngu lèpa nèti d'ara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i, hèia Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na, lasi asa èmu Simon dènge Anderias.<bt>When they returned.home from the house of worship, Yesus with His followers went to the house of Simon and Anderias.</bt><v n="30" />Ina dhèu èmu Simon pèd'a maringi-sagoro, ka dhu j'unu. Ropa Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na d'ai d'ara èmu èèna, dhèu mai peka dènge Ne, &lt;&lt;Bhèni heka ne, pèd'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>Simon's mother-in-law was sick with fever-and-chills, [and] she was sleeping/lying down. When Yesus and His followers arrived in the house, a person came and said to Him, "The old lady [+respect] is sick."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pa'èle = heal (direct); tao pa'èle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pa'èle = heal (direct); tao pa'èle = heal (indirect), do s.t. that causes healing; 30: maringi-sagoro = demam; teto = FZ (default understsnding), WM (if also by kinship)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ropa Yesus dènge Yakobis, Yohanis, dènge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ropa Yesus dènge Yakobis, Yohanis, dènge ana madhatu dhu leo kalua gereja rèngu lasi asa èmu Simon dènge Anderias.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Nèti èèna ka, Yesus la'e ladhe bhèni heka ne. Hèia Na kèpe kacui-aai na, ho pamadhèdi ne. Kaca'a laa papèd'a maringi-sagoro èèna èle dènge. Hèia bhèni heka ne kèd'i la'e lalau nganga'a-nganginu hia si.<bt>So then went to see this old lady. Then He held her hand to sit her up. Suddenly the aforementioned fever-and-chills sickness was gone. So then this old lady got.up and fixed/served food to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangaj'i = songgo, some feel has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mangaj'i = songgo, some feel has overtones of or is exclusive to berhala, but after discussion they prefer to keep it. They use it in Christian prayers (I've seen it directly in contexts where they are not thinking about it). ina dhèu èmu = mother in law (WM, HM); lalèta = kick out, shoo away (chook)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="She couldn't cook because it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">She couldn't cook because it was Sabbath.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ropa lod'o cèna, dhèu pakako rèti asa Yesus a'ari rèngu dhu pèd'a, dènge dhèu-dhèu dhu nidhu tao, sèna ka Na puri-pa'èle si.<bt>When the sun was going.down, people started bringing to Yesus their kin (older-younger siblings = family/relatives) who were sick, and people afflicted by evil.spirits, so He could heal them.</bt><v n="33" />Nèti èèna ka, ca kabarai mai pakaboko pènu tao cèci ètu madha èmu èèna.<bt>So then the populace came and gathered jam-packed (idiom) in front of that house.</bt><v n="34" />Èi papèd'a ra rupa-rupa, te ngaa Yesus puri-pa'èle aa'i mèu-mèu si. Hèia Na lalèta eele nidhu ae nèti dhèu sèra. Yesus hia boe tebho nidhu se'e padhai lii, lula ra tadhe Ne.<bt>The kinds of sicknesses that afflicted people were a huge variety, but Yesus healed them all completely. And he also evicted lots of evil.spirits from those people. Yesus didn't give opportunity to the evil.spirits to speak, because they knew2 Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pa'èle = sembuhkan; 33: idiom; 34:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pa'èle = sembuhkan; 33: idiom; 34: tebho = tempo, kesempatan; dhèu se'e (se) = ini orang dong; dhèu sèra (sa) = itu orang dong; Simon si = Simon dong (with proper name); dhèu sèi = orang dong sana; @@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus kako palème rae, ho lole Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua<bt>Yesus walks around the villages to tell the Word of God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 4:42-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Bèli èèna mad'ae aae era, ako maroga, Yesus kèd'i ka la'e asa era èci dhu nee-nee, ka Na manèngi-mangaj'i mi Ama Lamatua.<bt>The next morning when it was still dark, Yesus got.up and went to a place that was quiet, and He prayed/worshiped God.</bt><v n="36" />Ropa Simon si kèd'i, rèdhi heka Yesus, ka lasi tenge Ne.<bt>When Simon (coll) got.up, they didn't see Yesus, so they went looking for Him.</bt><v n="37" />Ra paraga dènge Yesus, ka ra peka, &lt;&lt;Ama, dhèu canau mai tenge Ama ku.&gt;&gt;<bt>They met with Yesus and said, "Father, a group/crowd of people has come looking for Father [=you +respect]."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Te ngaa Yesus dhaa lii rèngu, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èèna be'a kahèi. Te ngaa be'a risi lati uru asa rae-rae leo, ho Ja'a aj'a Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua. Te èèna sasab'a-la'a Ja'a na.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus answered them saying like this, "That's good too. But it is better if we go first to the other villages so that I can teach the Word of God. Cause [te] that is My work."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Èle èèna ka, rèngu kako palème era ètu propensi Galilea, ho lole Lii Lolo Be'a Ama Lamatua. Ètu d'ara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i, Na babège-lalèta eele nidhu nèti dhèu sèra.<bt>After that, they walked around the province of Galilea to tell the Good News2 of God. In the houses of worship He evicted3 evil.spirits from people there.</bt><note reference="1:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 4:23, 9:35</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle dhèu èci dhu pèd'a kusta<bt>Yesus heals a person who is sick with kusta (BI loan for leprosy), which makes.him.gross.to.people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:1-4; Lukas 5:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Dhèu èci dhu lèke papèd'a kusta mai paraga dènge Yesus, ka na patitu kètu urutuu ètu madha Yesus. Na manèngi, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama, ee! Sue ku ja'a laa. Tao pa'èle ku papèd'a ja'a ne. Ja'a ke'a, na, Ama bisa pa'èle papèd'a ja'a ne, sèna ka dhèu madenge heka dènge ja'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>A person afflicted by the kusta sickness came to meet with Yesus, and he knelt down in front of Yesus, asking, saying, "Father, oo! *Love/pity me now. Heal this sickness of mine. I know that Father can heal this sickness of mine, so that people are no longer grossed.out at me."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lepros: probably not a Hansen's disease"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">lepros: probably not a Hansen's disease patient, but someone suffering from a skin disease that made him ritually unfit for worship. But with so many people here having relatives who were (or are) in the Kalaupapa leper colony, "lepa" has instant recognition, and a strong emotional reaction as serious. Ideas of "ritually impure" are not, on the other hand, common in the culture. katharisai: "cleanse" in the ritual sense, "make me so I can worship with the rest again"<span class="Italic">(40)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Nèti lii roma iisi na, ka d'ara Yesus roe, ka Na j'ole kacui-aai ho kèpe ne. Hèia Na peka, &lt;&lt;Tare'a! Ja'a bisa! Èu èle kèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of his request, Yesus insides were soft, and He extended his hand taking hold of him and said, "True! I am.able.to! You are healed!"</bt><v n="42" />Kaca'a laa, papèd'a èèna ele dènge. Ka dhèu èèna pèd'a heka.<bt>Suddenly the aforementioned sickness disappeared. And that person was no longer sick.</bt><v n="43" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus pua dhèu èèna lèpa dènge pasanèd'e ne, peka na,<bt>After that, Yesus ordered the aforementioned person to go.home, reminding him, saying,</bt><v n="44" />&lt;&lt;Mu nanene! Èu èle le, te ngaa baku lole dènge cee-cee! Èu hud'i madhutu ku lii paredha Musa uru èèna. De lamu uru ku asa ama agama, ho na parisa ngi'u mu. Sèna ka ne'a èi papèd'a èu na ele le, do dhae. Èle èèna ka, heka èu hia mèdha èci sèmi tadha makasi, sèna ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i re'a èu èle le tare'a-re'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>"You remember! You have been healed, but don't tell anybody, oo! You must follow the regulation of Grandpa Musa from before. So [de] go now the the *priest (father of religion), so he can inspect your body. So he knows that your sickness has been healed, or not. After that, you should give something as a sign of thanks, so that everyone knows you are really healed."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ele = hilang; èle = sembuh;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ele = hilang; èle = sembuh; ej'a = hilang, sudah pergi; mèdha sogo tagu = barang-barang persembahan (agama suku); sogo = songgo, berkaitan dgn berhala, agama suku (disputed); Masi ka = meskipun, walaupun (becoming archaic); mèdha = things, stuff; mèdha-panyao = harta-benda, possessions, all types of belongings</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="embrimeesamenos ... exebalen: Jesus was very"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">embrimeesamenos ... exebalen: Jesus was very abrupt with the man, and practically pushed him out the door. Two senses of "now": admonition with "no foget", and time with "stay good." No clash.<span class="Italic">(44)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 14:1-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Masi ka Yesus kai baku peka dènge cee-cee, te ngaa ropa la'e d'ai li'u, ka na lolo lème dènge dhèu. Èle èèna ka, dhèu ae neo paraga dènge Yesus. Te ngaa, lula lii dhèu èèna, ka Yesus bisa boe pad'elo iisi Na asa d'ara kota. Nèti èèna ka, Yesus pea dhoka ètu era mau èci ètu li'u kota. Te ngaa dhèu mai paraga dènge Ne nèti mia-mia.<bt>Even though Yesus forbade him to not tell anyone about that, but when he went outside he told it around there to people. After that, many people wanted to meet with Yesus. But because of what this aforementioned man had said, Yesus couldn't reveal Himself (=let Himself be seen) inside the city. So then Yesus just stayed at a peaceful place outside the city. But from everywhere people came to meet with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mau = 1) nee-nee 2) kaliu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mau = 1) nee-nee 2) kaliu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle dhèu karuku<bt>Lord Yesus heals a lame person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:1-8; Lukas 5:17-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Èle pèri-pèri lod'o, hèia Yesus lèpa hari asa Kapernaum. Ka ra papeka d'ai mia-mia, peka na, Yesus d'ai le èmu.<bt>After several days/time, Yesus returned again to Kapernaum. And people were telling each other all over the place, saying that Yesus had arrived at the house.</bt><v n="2" />Nèti èèna ka, dhèu mai nèti mia-mia. Lula dhèu ae seli, ka ètu d'ara èmu pènu risi, toke d'ai hèb'a èmu. Èle èèna ka, Yesus lole dènge ra dad'èi Ama Lamatua.<bt>So then people came from everywhere. Because there were so many people, the house was over full inside, right up to the door. Then Yesus told them the will/desires of God.</bt></p>
    <fig path="Art-Read\thruRoof.jpg" rtfFormat="textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ètu talora Na padhai lii era, dhèu èpa jèru dhèu karuku èci neo asa madha Yesus.<bt>When He was still speaking, four people were pole.carrying a lame person [to put] in front of Yesus. [CHECK if this is seen as realis (accomplished) or irrealis (intended)].</bt><v n="4" />Te ngaa, lula dhèu ae d'ai seli, ka rèngu abhu boe sasanga ho rèti dhèu èèna asa madha Yesus. Hèia ca'e lasi asa kolo èmu, bhoke eele rèu èmu re dedha kètu Yesus. Ropa ra bhoke rare rèu èmu, hèia ra papuru dhèu karuku èena dènge dhèpi na.<bt>Because there were so many people, they couldn't find a gap to take the aforementioned person in front of Yesus. So they ascended to the peak/top of the house, opened up the roof, right above Yesus' head. When the roof was opened up, then they lowered using his mat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krabatton: The mat was the sick"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">krabatton: The mat was the sick man's, not a mat that happened to be in front of Jesus.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ra tao Dhèpi èèna nèti mèdha dhu mèke.<bt>That mat, they made it from material which was strong.</bt></note><v n="5" />Ropa Yesus ladhe nèdhi si, Nèngu ne'a le dhèu se'e parcaya tare'a-re'a Nèngu. Ka na padhai lii dènge dhèu karuku ne, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ana, ee! Ja'a saku eele le sasala èu!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus saw them, He knew those people really *believed1 (assimilated loan) in Him. And He said to this lame person, saying, "Child, ee! I have wiped away your wrongs!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jèru = two poles w/person in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">jèru = two poles w/person in middle; must have person on both ends of pole (two or four people; one person with pole = fv:d'ui; fv:pasae = shoulder-carry, one person without pole; fv:tèd'u = head-carry; 4: ; 4: ; 5: tao eele = bekin hilang; saku eele = hapus buang (both used in church); rase eele = cuci buang /bersih (literal, rather than fig.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ètu èèna kahèi, abhu pèri-pèri mese agama Yahudi. Ropa ra tadèngi rare lii padhai lii Yesus, ka d'ara ngangee rèngu be'a boe.<bt>In that aforementioned place there were also several Jahudi *teachers of religion. When they heard what Yesus had just said, their inside thoughts were not good.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;in their hearts&quot; would be overkill"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">"in their hearts" would be overkill for Pidgin, though it's sayable</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Hèia ra papeka, &lt;&lt;Boo! Dhèu ne'e bani titu kèna, padhai lii sèmi nèi! Dhodhoka Ama Lamatua di, dhu dènge hak ho saku eele sasala dhèu. Te ngaa dhèu ne'e tao ngi'u na èci èèna ka dènge Ama Lamatua. Nèngu pakarehe kolongara Ama Lamatua!&gt;&gt;<bt>And they said, "Boo! This person is really bold! He speaks like that! Only God alone is the one who can wipe away a person's wrongs. But this person make himself one with (=same as) God. He is slandering (lit cause-evil/bad to the name/reputation/character) of God!"</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01689b.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Te ngaa Yesus ne'a le ngangee rèngu. Hèia Na peka, &lt;&lt;Heh! Miu baku pangee sèmi èèna.<bt>But Yesus already knew their thoughts. So He said, "He! You(PL) shouldn't be thinking like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pneumati: could say &quot;inside his spirit&quot;,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">pneumati: could say "inside his spirit", but it isn't as meaningful as "inside". Same thing for "inside yoa heart".</Message></Annotation><v n="9-10" />Mia dhu be'a risi? Ladhe Ja'a peka mi dhèu karuku ne, &lt;Sasala èu saku eele le,&gt; miu me'a boe, na, j'aj'i do aad'o. Te ngaa ladhe Ja'a peka, &lt;Kèd'i ka! Nedhe dhèpi èu, ho lèpa ka.&gt; Ladhe na kèd'i ho miu ladhe mèdhi kahèi, heka miu me'a kèna, Ja'a ne Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a. Aa Ja'a dènge koasa kahèi, ho saku eele sasala-sasigo dhèu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Which is better? If [ladhe] I say to this lame person, 'Your wrongs have been wiped away,' you(PL) don't know if it happens, or not. But if I say, 'Get up now! Pick up your mat and go home.' If he then gets up so you can see it, only.then will you really know that I here am the *Son of Man (Child of Humans). And that I here also have *power (assimilated loan) to get rid of people's wrongs!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana dhèu = someone's child; Dhèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ana dhèu = someone's child; Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a = child of the world's people/inhabitants (?); rai-haha = bumi, dunia; abhu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Èle èèna ka, Yesus padhai lii dènge dhèu karuku èèna, peka na,<bt>After that, Yesus spoke to the aforementioned lame person,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="compare Matthew 9:5-6."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">compare Matthew 9:5-6.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />&lt;&lt;Èu nanene, ee! Èu èle le ne! Kèd'i ka, nedhe dhèpi èu ho lamu ka.&gt;&gt;<bt>"Listen up, ee! You're healed now! Get up, pick up your mat and go now."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ropa tadèngi nare, cag'ag'a laa dhèu ne kèd'i titu. Na nedhe dhèpi na, hèia la'e ka asa li'u. Dhèu-dhèu ètu sèra rèdhi dènge musi madha ra. Rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra malaa-maloha, ka ra peka, &lt;&lt;Ira ii! Èdhi heka tèdhi ka! Ama Lamatua tare'a-re'a kapai d'ai seli!&gt;&gt;<bt>When he heard him, the person stood up immediately. He picked up his mat, and then he went outside. The people there saw this with their own eyeballs. They all were amazed2, saying, "Waa! We've never seen anything like this, oo! God is really great [+emphasis]!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malaa-maloha = tanganga bodoh, amazed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">malaa-maloha = tanganga bodoh, amazed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus paroa nare Lewi ho madhutu Ne<bt>Yesus summons Lewi to follow Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:9-13; Lukas 5:27-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus la'e hari asa sebhe dano Galilea. Ka dhèu ae titu kèna mai paraga dènge Ne, hèia Na lole dad'èi Ama Lamatua mi rèngu.<bt>After that, Yesus went again along the edge of lake Galilea. And lots and lots of people came to meet with Him, so He told them the will/desires of God.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00309C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Dhèu roro doi bea<bt>A person collecting taxes</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ètu èèna, abhu dhèu èci ngara na Lewi, ana nèti Alpius. Sasab'a na roro doi bea. Lod'o Yesus kako re èèna ka ladhe nèdhi Lewi. Ka Na peka dènge ne, &lt;&lt;Wee! Mai madhutu Ja'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>In that place was a person named Lewi, a child of Alfeus. His work was cutting/collecting tax money (Malay loan). When Yesus went there he saw Lewi. And He said to him, "Ee! Come follow Me!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bea = tax (BI); be'a ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">bea = tax (BI); be'a = baik; bera = kerja paksa, kerja rodi; roro = pungut</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ropa tadèngi lii Yesus ne, Lewi kèd'i dènge ka la'e madhutu Ne.<bt>When he heard Yesus, Lewi got up and went following Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus si ra'a ètu d'ara èmu Lewi, pa'èci dènge angalai Lewi dhèu roro doi bea sèra. Abhu kahèi dhèu-dhèu leo madhèdi ra'a dènge rèngu. Madhutu ngangee dhèu Yahudi, dhèu se'e dhèu karehe. Nèti dhèu-dhèu dhu madhèdi ra'a se abhu dhèu ae kahèi dhu d'èi nanene lii padhai lii Yesus.<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) ate in the house of Lewi, together with Lewi's friends'companions tax collecting people (coll). There were also other people, who according to the thinking of the Jahudi people, were bad/evil people, sitting eating with them. Among the people who were sitting eating there were also many people who wanted to listen to the sayings of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teloonai kai hamartooloi: sinners in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">teloonai kai hamartooloi: sinners in the eyes of the pharisaical. Even in Galilee of the Gentiles, people who associated with non-Jews were considered second class Jews. It isn't a matter of them actually sinning or being bad people; they were just religious outcasts as the religious leaders defined it. Verse 16 mentions them too, and 17 mentions the outcasts. eekolouthoun: they were tagging along (not "plenny peopo" but a crowd of the wrong kind of people who were curious about Jesus and wanted to see more).<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Lod'o èèna, abhu pèri-pèri mese agama nèti partei Parisi dhu rèdhi Yesus madhèdi na'a-ninu dènge tuka roro doi bea, dènge dhèu karehe sèra. Ka ra karèi ana madhutu Yesus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka mese miu madhèdi na'a-ninu dènge dhèu roro doi bea dènge dhèu dhu laku-laku boe sèra?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time several religious teachers from the Parisi group/party (KM loan) saw Yesus sitting eating-drinking with tukang collecting taxes, and with other bad people (coll). And they asked Yesus followers like this, "Why does your(PL) teacher eat-drink with people who collect taxes and people who have no use/worth (coll)?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;odda kine peopo jalike dem&quot; in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">"odda kine peopo jalike dem" in Matthew. "Bad name jalike dem" may be better, since it is judgmental and reflects the Pharisees' viewpoint. It also leads into Verse 17 better, which the neutral term used in Matthew doesn't do. Matthew has "fo da odda kine peopo" in 9:13. Change?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Yesus tadèngi lii karèi rèngu èèna, ka Na dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu pèd'a mema parluu dote, te ngaa dhèu dhu pèd'a boe, parluu boe dote. Mamai Ja'a ne sèna ka lalau dhèu dhu laku-laku boe. Te Ja'a mai boe ho uri dhèu dhu rasa ngi'u na mola.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus heard their question and He answered them like this, "A sick person really needs a doctor (assimilated loan), but a person who is not sick does not need a doctor. My coming here is with the purpose to serve1 people who have no use/worth. I didn't come to take care of people who feel themselves straight/pure."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pusi boe = dale boe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pusi boe = dale boe = paralu boe = not need, tidak butuh</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">A'aj'a hiu Lamatua Yesus, leko-leo nèti a'aj'a dhèu Parisi<bt>The way of (=about) fasting (loan) and new teaching</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:14-17; Lukas 5:33-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ca tèka, dhèu nèti partei agama Parisi puasa. Rèngu rèdhi ana madhutu Yohanis tuka sarani, puasa kahèi. Te ngaa rèdhi boe ana madhutu Yesus puasa sèmi rèngu. Hèia dhèu rèngu mai paraga dènge Yesus, ka ra karèi, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama. Ji'i puasa sama sèmi ana madhutu Yohanis kahèi. Te, nga tao ka, ana madhutu Ama puasa boe?&gt;&gt;<bt>Once people from the Parisi religious party/group were *fasting (loan). They saw the Yohanis the Tukang Baptiser's followers also fasted. But they didn't see Yesus' followers fasting like them. So some of them came to meet with Yesus and asked him, saying, "Father. We(exc) fast, and the followers of Yohanis also fast in the same way. But, why don't your followers fast?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dara kab'oko Farisi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dara kab'oko Farisi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mema miu me'a le, ladhe abhu pesta kab'i, dhèu dhu abhu nèru sèra puasa boe, ka ra'a toke bècu. Ladhe mone dhu kab'i èèna era, dhèu sèra aa'i-aa'i ra'a-rinu.<bt>So Yesus sanswered, "You(PL) certainly know that, as for a bridegroom (lit. wedding person), the people who receive invitations do not fast, but.rather they eat until they are satiated. When the afroementioned man who is marrying is still there, all those people eat-drink.</bt><v n="20" />Te ladhe d'ai lod'o ho ra kèpe rèti dhèu mone dhu kab'i èèna, ka mone aanga-angalai na sèra d'ara susa, heka ra puasa kèna.<bt>But when the day/time arrives, that this man who is marrying is absconded with (impersonal construction, no referential subject), the man's friends (coll) will be sad, and will soon fast. [Check TAM here, use of heka...kèna].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho here like te, gives contrast"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ho here like te, gives contrast 'but'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, bèla hiu baku kalape mi kodho dhui. Te ladhe base, na, bèla hiu èèna karuku, hèia kodho èèna asa ka mae aae.<bt>It's also like new cloth shouldn't be patched onto an old shirt. Cause when it's washed, that aforementioned new cloth shrivels, and then that shirt becomes torn even worse.</bt><v n="22" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, miu baku edhe dhua pèd'u ètu d'ara sabha dhui. Te aad'o na, sabha èèna mae, aa dhua pèd'u na bhori eele asa rai.&gt;&gt;<bt>It's also like you(PL) shouldn't put fresh palmjuice into an old palmjuice container. Cause like it or not the container will disintigrate and the fresh palmjuice will pour out (completely) onto the ground." From that, Yesus was saying to them, not to mix together His new teaching with the teaching of the Parisi people from before.</bt><note reference="2:22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Baku soli èi anggor dhu hiu mi d'ara tas ka'uri dhui, sèna ka baku mae.&gt;&gt;</note>[Nèti èèna ka Yesus peka dènge si, baku pakihu-kee lii holo-nori Nèngu dhu hiu, dènge lii holo-nori dhèu Parisi dhu dhui.]</p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana madhutu Yesus g'ètu are, lèke lod'o a'oro sasab'a<bt>The followers of Yesus pick grain on the day without work</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:1-8; Lukas 6:1-5)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ca tèka, lèke lod'o manèngi-mangaj'i dhèu Yahudi, Yesus si kako re j'ara ètu d'ara oka. Ka ana madhutu Na g'ètu rèti are gandum.<bt>Once, on the day of worship of the Jahudi people, Yesus on the path through the garden.fields. And His followers picked/plucked gandum (BI loan) grain.</bt><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 23:25</note><v n="24" />Ropa dhèu Parisi ladhe rèdhi, ka ra karèi Yesus, &lt;&lt;Tasamia ka, ana madhutu Èu madhutu boe j'ara-j'ara agama èdhi? Rèngu se g'ètu are gandum lèke lod'o a'oro sasab'a. Miu baku tao sèmi èèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the Parisi people (coll) saw that they asked Yesus, "How come Your followers don't follow the ways of our(inc) religion? They are picking gandum grain on the day that work is prohibited. You(PL) shouldn't do like that!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma'are = sawah ; oka ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ma'are = sawah ; oka = kebun; 24: lab'a = oral opposition, argue; oro = prohibit,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00099C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Are gandum<bt>Gandum grain</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, &lt;&lt;Samia, ee? Miu sanèd'e heka lii lolo Daud. Tèu èèna, Abyatar j'aj'i kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi. Lod'o èèna, Daud dènge dhèu madhutu na aa'i-aa'i ra manganga bia. Ka ra maso asa d'ara Paleo Ama Lamatua, hèia ra'a roti dhu ama agama hia le mi Lamatua. Madhutu atora agama èdhi, dhèu dhu bisa ra'a roti èèna, dhoka ama-ama agama di; dhèu leo bisa boe. Daud dènge ana madhutu na sèra, ra'e rare roti èèna, te ngaa dhèu èci sa peka boe, na, Daud si sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus responded, "How is it, ee? You(PL) no.longer remember that story of Grandpa Daud. Once Abyatar was the *high priest (father of religious fathers). That day/time Grandpa Daud with all his followers were really hungry. And they entered inside God's *Tent (temporary shelter) [and] ate the bread (loan) that the *priests (fathers of religion) had given to God2. According to the regulations of our(inc) religion, the people who can eat that bread were only just the fathers of religion; other people couldn't. The ones who Grandpa Daud and his followers (coll) took and ate that aforementioned bread, but one person even has not said that Daud (coll) were wrong (=not even one person said...)."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paleo = kemah, dari daun, tarpal;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">paleo = kemah, dari daun, tarpal; èmu = rumah, has sense of more permanence; ra'e (perf) / ra'a ; pasale = tersinggung;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The point is not just that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">The point is not just that David and his ate the special bread, but that the action is not condemned by Scripture even though it broke the letter of the law.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 21:1-6; Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 24:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus lole hari dènge rèngu, &lt;&lt;Miu baku bhèlu! Lamatua hia lod'o a'oro sasab'a hia èdhi dhèu rai-haha. Lamatua paj'aj'i boe èdhi dhèu rai-haha, ho madhutu dhoka atora lod'o a'oro sasab'a di.<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again to them, "You(PL) don't forget! God gave the day on which work is prohibited to we(inc) humans. God did not make/create us humans for the purpose of only just following the rules/ways of the day on which work is prohibited.</bt><v n="28" />Ja'a ne, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a. Ja'a ne ka dhu peka ho dhèu sab'a, do aad'o, lèke dènge lod'o a'oro sasab'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>I here, am the Child of Humans. I here am the one who says that people work, or not, on that day on which work is prohibited."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sanèd'e = ingat; always dhoka...di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sanèd'e = ingat; always dhoka...di</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho hyios tou anthroopou: Jesus is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">ho hyios tou anthroopou: Jesus is talking about himself. Is this clear? "Lord" is a relation to people, not to a time period. The relation to the day has to be spelled out more, because "Boss" does not collocate that way.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle dhèu pèd'a lèke lod'o a'oro sasab'a<bt>Lord Yesus heals2 a sick person on the day on which work is prohibited</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:9-14; Lukas 6:6-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus lèpa hari la'e asa èmu manèngi-mangaj'i. D'ai nèi, ka Yesus paraga dènge dhèu èci dhu ai na roe cabèka.<bt>After that, Yesus returned again to go to the house of worship. Arriving there Yesus met a person who's arm was withered on one side.</bt><v n="2" />Ètu èèna, abhu pèri-pèri dhèu dhu patangi-tenge sasala Yesus. Ra ma'u Yesus, neo re'a Na puri-pa'èle dhèu pèd'a lèke lod'o a'oro sasab'a, do aad'o.<bt>In that place there were several people who were looking for ways to find something wrong with Yesus. They were spying/peeping at Yesus, wanting to know if He would heal2 a sick person on the day on which work is prohibited, or not.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Hèia Yesus paroa dhèu dhu ai roe cabèka èèna, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Mai ku! Titu ku mi madha Ja'a ne.&gt;&gt;<bt>Without warning, Yesus summoned the aforementioned person with the withered arm, "Come here! Stand in front of Me here."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ka Na karèi dhèu ae ètu sèra sa, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Madhutu atora agama èdhi, èdhi bisa tao ngaa lod'o a'oro sasab'a? Tao madha j'ara dhu be'a, do karehe? Tao pabe'a dhèu, do pamadhe dhèu?&gt;&gt; Te ngaa dhèu sèra èci sa bani boe bhoke hèb'a.<bt>Then He asked the many people there, "According to the ways of our(inc) religion, what deeds can we do on the day on which work is prohibited? [Can we] do things that are good, or evil? [Can we] do.good/help a person, or kill a person?" But not one of the people there had the courage to open his mouth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Nèti èèna ka, Yesus d'ara pèd'a, lula rèngu madhutu dhoka ad'a di, tao boe madha-dhilu mi dhèu ai roe cabèka ne. Yesus nasa, ka Na ladhe lème dhèu sèra. Hèia Na peka mi dhèu ai roe cabèka, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;J'ole kacui-aai èu mai sa ne'e!&gt;&gt; Ka dhèu èèna soro kacui-aai asa Yesus la'e. Kabèdhi laa, èle dènge papèd'a na.<bt>Because1 of that Yesus was sad (sick insides), because2 they were only just following customs (loan--adat), and didn't care about (idiom--eye-ear) the person with the withered arm. Yesus was angry and He looked around at those people, saying, "Extend your hand coming here now!" And when that person stretched out his hand to Yesus, suddenly it was healed from its sickness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekteinin: may imply trying to stretch"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">ekteinin: may imply trying to stretch out the paralyzed fingers, or just extending the hand and arm.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ropa dhèu Parisi ladhe rèdhi Yesus pa'èle kacui-aai dhèu èèna lèke lod'o a'oro sasab'a, aa'i-aa'i ra kalua nèti d'ara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i. Ka lasi padhue dènge dhèu partei politik Herodes, ho tenge j'ara neo pamadhe Yesus.<bt>When the Parisi people saw that Yesus healed the arm of that aforementioned person on the day on which work is prohibited, they all went out from inside the house of worship. And they went and discussed with people of the Herodes political party (loan) to look for a way so they could kill Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Healing itself was not the issue;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">Healing itself was not the issue; details of the Law were. This is implicit in the Greek, but not accessible in Pidgin. The "Herodians" were a political group. Herod was a very unpopular king, but some people backed him because he was generally a winner.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle papèd'a dhèu ae ètu sebhe dano<bt>Lord Yesus heals2 the sickness of many people at the edge of the lake</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhèu pèdha ae = banyak orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhèu pèdha ae = banyak orang sakit; dhèu pèdha aae = orang sakit berat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7-8" />Ca lod'o, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na lasi asa sebhe dano Galilea. Te ngaa, lula dhèu ae sèra re'a le ngaa dhu Nèngu tao, ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i mai nèti rae-rae ho madhutu Ne. Rèngu mai nèti propensi Galilea, propensi Yudea, aa propensi Idumea. Abhu kahèi dhu mai nèti kota Yerusalem, kota Sidon dènge kota Tirus. Abhu kahèi cahag'e dhu mai nèti cabèka dhimu loko Yarden. Aa'i-aa'i sèra neo mai paraga dènge Ne.<bt>One day/time Yesus with His followers didn't want to be seen so they went along the edge of lake Galilea. Because3 many people already knew everything He had done, so everybody came from the villages around the province of Galilea wanting to follow Yesus. In the same way, many people came from the province of Yudea, from the city of Yerusalem, from the province of Idumea, from across the river Yarden, from the city of Sidon and the city of Tirus. All of them wanted to come and meet with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eekoloutheesen: not necessarily &quot;followed by boat.&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">eekoloutheesen: not necessarily "followed by boat." The place all these people ended up was "by the lake," however they got there</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Taga dhèu dhu mai sèra ae seli, ka Yesus pua ana madhutu Na lasi tenge koha cue hia Nèngu. Na neo padhai lii dènge dhèu ae sèra nèti dedha koha, sèna ka rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra bisa ladhe rèdhi rèhu Na, aa tadèngi lii padhai lii Na hèi.<bt>Because4 so many people had come, Yesus ordered His followers to go find a boat for Him. He wanted to speak to them from on top of the boat, so they could all see His face, and also hear what He was saying.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ca hari ni, Na puri-pa'èle dhèu pèd'a ae titu kèna. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu ae mai paseti èci dènge èci, neo g'ag'e Yesus.<bt>And again, He healed all sorts of sick people. Because of that, a great many people came crowding in on each other wanting to touch Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="etherapeusen: aorist covers the whole occasion;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">etherapeusen: aorist covers the whole occasion; it's not a perfect, so "befo time" is probably wrong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 4:1, Lukas 5:1-3</note><v n="11" />Ropa dhèu dhu nidhu tao sa ladhe rèdhi Yesus, ka ra bèbha d'ai rai ètu madha Yesus. Hèia ra taraa, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èu ne mema tare'a Ana Ama Lamatua!&gt;&gt;<bt>When people who had been afflicted by evil.spirits saw Yesus, they fell on the ground in front of Yesus. And they shouted, saying, "You here are truly the Child of God!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari eele ; kako eele ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hari eele ; kako eele ; sigo ; hag'e ; aku pacèu-pahoni ; pamau ; lu'u = tarik diri ; ra mai = mereka datang; raa mai = haid (darah datang)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Te ngaa Yesus kai rèngu, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu baku ale dènge dhèu èci sa hèi, Ja'a ne cee!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus forbade them, saying, "Be careful [not] to tell a single person who I am!" [CHECK pos-neg on this].</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus hag'e nare dhèu canguru dua j'aj'i ana madhutu Na<bt>Yesus chooses/sets.aside 12 people to be/become His followers</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:1-4; Lukas 6:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus kako la'e asa kolo ledhe èci. Na paroa pèri-pèri dhèu dhu Nèngu d'èi. Ka dhèu se mai madhutu Ne.<bt>After that Yesus went up on top of a mountain/hill. He summoned several people who He liked/who pleased Him. And those people came and followed Him.</bt><v n="14" />Èle èèna ka, Na hag'e nare dhèu canguru dua. Ka Na peka, &lt;&lt;Ja'a pili miu ho madhutu taruu Ja'a, j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha Ja'a. Ja'a neo pua miu, lami lole Lii Lolo Be'a Ama Lamatua mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that He set.aside/chose 12 people. And He spoke to them like this, "I choose you(PL) to be My followers. I'm going to tell you to go and tell the Good Story about God."</bt><v n="15" />Sèmi èèna kahèi Ja'a neo hia miu koasa, sèna ka miu bisa babège-lalèta nidhu nèti d'ara dhèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>In a similar way I want to give you power, so that you can evict2 evil.spirits from people."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhei = tahi; d'ei = senang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhei = tahi; d'ei = senang, suka; 14: lami go-2p; lamu go-2s; (aj'a) li holo nori = ajaran &amp; kehendak (lole) li lolo nori = cerita; 15: general statement, i.e. unreduplicated nidhu and dhèu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16-19" />Ngara dhèu canguru dua sa, nuka:<bt>The names of those 12 people were like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simon (dhu Yesus pangare na, Petrus),<bt>Simon (who Yesus called Petrus),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis,<bt>Yakobis, with his younger.sibling.same.sex</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanis, (Yakobis dènge ari na, Yohanis ne, dua ra ana Sabadeus. Yesus pangare rèngu dua ra, ngara na &lt;Boanerges&gt;, dhu sasoa na &lt;sama sèmi d'oro&gt;.)<bt>Yohanis, (the two of them were children of Sabadius. Yesus called the two of them by the name 'Boanerges', which means 'like thunder'.)</bt><note reference="3:19a" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;ana d'oro&gt;, dènge sasoa, &lt;tatao nuka sèmi d'oro&gt;. Abhu dhèu d'èlu-mèu cahag'e dhu peka na, ele boe lii Yakobis dènge Yohanis mèdhu nuka sèmi lii d'oro, do, rèngu d'èi pajèka sama sèmi d'oro.</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Anderias,<bt>Anderias,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Pelipus,<bt>Filipus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bertolomeos,<bt>Bartolomeos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mateos,<bt>Mateos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tomas,<bt>Tomas,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis (ana Alpius),<bt>Yakobis (the child of Alpius)</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tadius,<bt>Tadius,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simon (dhu madhutu partei politik Selot),<bt>Simon (who followed the political party of Selot),</bt><note reference="3:16-19b" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Partei Selot ne tenge j'ara sèna ka rèngu mardeka nèti dhèu paredha Roma. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu pangare partei &lt;Patriot&gt; kahèi. Patriot sasoa na &lt;dhèu sarii kabarai&gt;.<bt>This Selot party was looking for a way so they could be free from the people of the government of Roma. Because of that, people also called the party 'Patriot'. Patriot means 'person defending his native land'.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dènge Yudas Iskariot (dhu èèna na pahie eele Yesus).<bt>and Yudas Iskariot (who *betrayed (lit. sold off) Yesus).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pahie eele = jual buang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pahie eele = jual buang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mese agama sèra peka Yesus abhu koasa nèti dhèu aae nidhu<bt>Teachers of religion (coll) say Yesus gets power from *Satan (King of Evil.Spirits)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:22-32; Lukas 11:14-23, 12:10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na sèra puru hari nèti kolo ledhe deo na. Ka lasi asa d'ara èmu èci. Dhèu ae titu kèna mai oke rare Ne, ka Na bisa boe na'a-ninu.<bt>After that, Yesus and His followers descended again from the top of the aforementioned mountain. And they went inside a house. Lots of people came and surrounded Him, so much so that He couldn't eat-drink.</bt><v n="21" />Rèdhi sèmi èèna, hèia ra papeka, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu ladhe ku Yesus! Ne'a heka lalau iisi Na.&gt;&gt; Ropa a'ari Na tadèngi lii palolo dhèu, ka ra mai neo rare Ne.<bt>Seeing that, [people] were talking, saying, "You.all take a look at Yesus! He doesn't even know how to take care of Himself." When His kin heard what people were saying, they came to fetch Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bhèlu urus ngi'u Na."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">bhèlu urus ngi'u Na.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krateisai: sieze, restrain It's unclear whether"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">krateisai: sieze, restrain It's unclear whether it was Jesus' family saying he was nuts, or if it was other people were saying it. It doesn't sound, however, as if it were the other people, who were quite enthusiastic about him. It was probably his family who were shamed by his being so prominent. There are other indications the family were upset, as in John when Jesus' brothers did not believe in him.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Lod'o èèna, mese-mese agama nèti Yerusalem mai peka dènge dhèu ètu sèra, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Heh! Pasa dhilu miu! Baku madhutu Yesus. Te dhèu aae nidhu, dhu ra paroa ngara na Baalsebul, maso asa d'ara Yesus, ka hia Ne koasa, ho bata-magèla nidhu nèti d'ara dhèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>One day/time, teachers of religion from Yerusalem came telling those people around there like this, "Ee! Listen up (idiom--fasten on your ears)! Don't follow what Yesus says. Cause *Satan, who is called Baalsebul, has entered inside Yesus, and given Him power to evict3 evil.spirits from people."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasa ro'a dhilu / pasa dhilu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pasa ro'a dhilu / pasa dhilu miu = pasang bosong pung telinga ; ee! Miu me'a mèka, do? = Bosong balom tahu, ko? ; bata = usir; magèla = usir; @@hia ne koasa = order OK give + IO + DO</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:34, 10:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ropa Yesus tadèngi nare lii padhue rèngu èèna, heia Na paroa nare rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra, ka Na peka, &lt;&lt;Lèke boe dènge ngangee dhèu! Tasamia ka dhèu aae nidhu bisa babège ngi'u mesa na!?<bt>When Yesus heard what they were saying, He summoned all of them saying like this, "It doesn't make sense (idiom)! How can it be that *Satan evicts1 his own self.!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parabolee: here Jesus is not telling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">parabolee: here Jesus is not telling stories, but using concise examples to make a point. Stick with the intent to teach, not the means used to do it. "Satan" doesn't fly as a name. After discussion it always comes back to "Devil."<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ladhe ètu d'ara paredha dhèu aae èci, ana kabarai sèra èci patao-palaha dènge èci, paredha dhèu aae èèna taha nèbhu boe.<bt>If in the kingdom of a king, one of the populace is arguing/fighting with another, the kingdom/government of the aforementioned king cannot endure/last.</bt><v n="25" />Sèmi èèna kahèi ètu d'ara èmu, ladhe isi èmu èci patao dènge èci, isi èmu èèna mae-manyèla!<bt>In the same way, in a house, if a member of the household is arguing/fighting with another, the aforementioned household will break apart!</bt><v n="26" />Sèmi èèna kahèi dènge nidhu. Ladhe èci pamusu dènge èci, rèngu mae-manyèla kahèi. Sèmi èèna na, heka rèngu laho kao-kao.<bt>Evil.spirits are also the same! If one is at war with another, they will also self-destruct. In a short time they will be totally destroyed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="; 24: patao = bertengkar ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">; 24: patao = bertengkar ; pahaka-paparu = berperang ; patao-palaha = bertengkar; 25: mae = pecah; manyèla = berantakan; 26: manyèla/manyèle = neutral/perfective</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil Not the destruction"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil Not the destruction of the Devil, but the demise of his organization.<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>"going" is not the future auxiliary "goin", but the main verb "go gains" 'oppose' in the progressive.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ladhe dhèu parapo neo mai parapo èmu dhèu èra èci, na hud'i èki-karadhe uuru ku lamatua èmu na, heka bau nèti mèdha-panyau kèna.<bt>If a robber wants to rob the house of a brave/strong person, he must tie/wrap up first the master of the house, and only.then remove his things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parapo = perampok; mana'u = steal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">parapo = perampok; mana'u = steal ; madha'u = takut; generic implies PL; parama = rampas; bau = kumpul</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ladhe dhèu neo mai rapo èmu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ladhe dhèu neo mai rapo èmu cue, dhu lamatua èmu na dhèu bani, dhèu parapo mai èki-karadhe uuru ku dhèu èèna, heka ra parapo rara mèdha kèna.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dènge j'ara èèna, Yesus peka na, Nèngu èra risi nèti dhèu aae nidhu, dhu tema ra pangare na, &lt;Baalsebul&gt;.</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Nèti èèna ka, Ja'a peka mema dènge miu: Ama Lamatua sadia saku eele sasala dhèu. Ladhe dhèu padhai lii karehe mi dedha dhèu leo, Ama Lamatua bisa saku eele sasala na era.<bt>Therefore, I'm telling you(PL) this directly: God is prepared to wipe away the wrongs of people. If a person speaks evil toward another person, God can still get rid of that wrong.</bt><v n="29" />Te ngaa lii padhai lii karehe mi dedha Roh Ama Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci, Ama Lamatua saku eele boe sasala nèngu, toke d'ai mia-mia la'e!&gt;&gt;<bt>But words that are evil about/toward the Spirit of God who is *Holy, God will not wipe away his wrong, [and that goes] not even until ever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mi dedha ~~ tentang; lalangu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mi dedha ~~ tentang; lalangu = hina ; dhu mèci boe ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te ladhe dhèu padhai lii karehe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Te ladhe dhèu padhai lii karehe Roh Ama Lamatua dhu Mola-mèci na, sasala nèngu na toke dai rai-haha èle, bisa boe abhu saku eele.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Yesus peka sèmi èèna, lula dhèu sèra peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu èèna, nidhu tao.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus said that, because2 those people were saying, "An evil.spirit is working inside Him."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu dhu madhutu dad'èi Ama Lamatua, tare'a-re'a j'aj'i a'ari Lamatua Yesus<bt>The person who is truly Yesus' kin</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:46-50; Lukas 8:19-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Èle èèna ka, ina dènge ari Yesus sèra mai tenge Ne. D'ai èmu dhu Yesus madhèdi ètu d'ara na, rèngu lasi boe asa d'ara, te ngaa ra titu ètu li'u, ka ra hia dhèu lasi paroa Yesus.<bt>After that, Yesus mother and younger.siblings (coll) came looking for Him. Arriving at the house where Yesus was sitting inside, they couldn't get inside, but they stood outside and had some people summon Yesus.</bt><v n="32" />Lasi, na, Yesus madhèdi padhai lii dènge dhèu ae. Ka dhèu sèra peka dènge Ne, &lt;&lt;Ama, ee! Ina Mu dènge a'ari Mu nuka ètu li'u si. Ra neo paraga dènge Ama.&gt;&gt;<bt>Summoning, Yesus sat speaking with the many people. And those aformentioned people said to Him, "Father, ee! Your mother and Your kin are (right now) outside. They want to meet with Father."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hia = kasi (here in sense"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hia = kasi (here in sense of order)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Te ngaa Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Cee ka dhu tare'a-re'a j'aj'i ina dènge a'ari Ja'a?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus responded, saying, "Who are actually (truly) My mother and My kin?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="a'ari = \va a-ari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">a'ari = \va a-ari</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Hèia Na ladhe palème asa dhèu dhu madhèdi ètu sèra, ka Na peka, &lt;&lt;Miu se'e se ka dhu tare'a-re'a j'aj'i ina dènge a'ari Ja'a.<bt>And He looked around at those people sitting there, and said, "You(PL) here are My mother and My kin, the true ones.</bt><v n="35" />Te cee ka dhu madhutu dad'èi Ama Lamatua, rèngu sèra ka dhu tare'a-re'a j'aj'i ina dènge a'ari Ja'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>Whoever follows the will/desires of Father God, they are the ones who are actually My mother and My kin."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus peka lii pakasame lula-nèti hini dhu lèke ètu dedha rupa-rupa rai<bt>Lord Yesus tells an *illustration/parable/example/allegory of seed that hits on various kinds of ground</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:1-9; Lukas 8:4-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ca lod'o, Yesus la'e hari asa dano Galilea. D'ai nèi dhèu ae mai oke rare Ne. Ka Yesus ca'e la'e madhèdi asa dedha koha cue dhu panahu. Na aj'a dhèu sèra dènge lii pakasame. Dhèu dhu titu ètu dedha salae sèra aa'i-aa'i nanene Yesus aj'a Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua.<v n="2" />Na aj'a si lii holo-nori rupa-rupa pake lii pakasame. Aku Nèngu sèmi ne'e ka:<bt>Once, Yesus went again to lake Galilea. Arriving there many people came and gathered around Him. And Yesus got up and sat on top of a boat which was at anchor. He taught those aforementioned people, using *illustration/parable/example/allegory. The people standing on the shore all heard Yesus teach the *Word of God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hini = bibit; dai = sampai;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hini = bibit; dai = sampai; dhai = sejenis jaring; salae = foreshore near water, edge; nebhe = shore farther away from water. panahu = berlabuh</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 5:1-3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />&lt;&lt;Nanene paie-iie! Dhèu èci la'e ceb'e hini ètu d'ara oka na.<bt>"You(PL) listen well! A person went planting (generic, multiple methods including dibble and broadcasting) seed in his field/garden.</bt><v n="4" />Ropa na ceb'e hini sèra, cahag'e lèke ètu sebhe j'ara. Kabèdhi laa, manu-bhui mai ka ra'a aa'i.<bt>When he planted those seeds, some landed on the side of the road. Immediately birds came and ate them all.</bt><v n="5" />Cahag'e hari lèke ètu era rai dhu pènu dènge hadhu. Hini sèra muri, te ngaa rai isi dhoka ciki oo'e di.<bt>Some others landed on a place where the ground was full with rocks. Those seeds lived/grew, but the soil was only too little.</bt><v n="6" />Ropa lod'o rea mai, ana nganga'a sèra kamale eele hèia madhe aa'i si, lula amo d'ai boe d'ara rai.<bt>When the sun came up, those sprouts wilted away until they were all dead, because the roots couldn't get through/into the soil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sèle = plant seed, some take"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sèle = plant seed, some take using dibble-stick as default understanding, but caan include broadcasting; usu = feten, botok, foxtail millet (Setaria italica); 4: cebe hini = broadcast ; dhudhu-marège = semak duri ; muri dènge sega = subur betul (sega = rimbun) ; sèle = all kinds of planting (implies digging hole in ground); kohi = kopi, coffee; 5: manii = tipis (doesn't collocate with soil); 6: ana nganga'a = anakan ; ko'o1 = tofa (kebun) ; ko'o2 = saya-setuju (inflected)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Art-Read\sower.jpg" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Hini cahag'e lèke ètu dedha rai dhu pènu dènge j'u'u padhudhu. Ropa j'u'u sèra muri, hèlu rare ana nganga'a sèra, ka j'aj'i boe hua-hela.<bt>Some seeds landed on soil that was full of grass thorny. When that grass lived/grew, it choked out those sprouts, and there was no fruit/result.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akanthoon: available varieties of thorns are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">akanthoon: available varieties of thorns are more like cockleburrs, and wouldn't grow up over a wheat stalk or stunt its growth. There are, however, several imported plants that take over native growth and strangle it ("choke" is used in discussions of this), and some can be referred to as "weeds."</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te ngaa hini cahag'e lèke ètu dedha rai hèu mèngi. Hini sèra muri dènge sega. Hua ae titu kèna. Cahag'e dhu abhu d'ai tèlu nguru hari, cahag'e èna nguru hari, aa cahag'e d'ai cangasu hari.<bt>But some seed landed on fertile soil (idiom, aromatic smelling soil). Those seeds grew well. They produced exceedingly well. Some produce to the point of 30 again, some to the point of 60 again, some to the point of 100 again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'u'u = rumput ; padhudhu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">j'u'u = rumput ; padhudhu = baduri ; cangèpi = jepit (two sides), gepe ame ; hèlu = lilit, belit; dhudhu-marège = ; gage = type of grass ;; 8: rai hèu mèngi = tanah subur</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />De ladhe cee dènge ro'a dhilu, na, nanene paie!&gt;&gt;<bt>So if anyone is with his/her ear holes, listen well!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nga tao ka Lamatua Yesus holo-nori dhèu pake lii pakasame<bt>Why the Lord Yesus taught using illustrations</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:10-17; Lukas 8:9-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ca tèka, Yesus mesa Na. Hèia ana madhutu Na dhèu canguru dua dènge pèri-pèri dhèu dhu tadèngi le lii holo-nori Na, mai paraga dènge Ne. Ka ra karèi sasoa nèti lii pakasame èèna.<bt>When Yesus taught2, His 12 followers and several (many) other people who had heard His teaching came and met with Him. And they asked the meaning of the recent illustration.</bt><v n="11" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, &lt;&lt;Lula miu tare'a-re'a neo me'a Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua, Ja'a neo peka dènge miu. Te ngaa mi dhèu leo, Ja'a pake lii pakasame.<bt>So Yesus answered, "Because you(PL) really want to know the Word of God, I want to tell it to you. But as for other people, I use illustrations.</bt><v n="12" />Tatao dhèu leo sèra sama sèmi dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua suri tèke, peka na,<bt>The deeds of other people are like what a *spokesman of God once wrote saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="li upama = known by all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">li upama = known by all generations, example, allegory, parable; li pakasame (archaic); 11: me'a = miu tahu; 12: ana pajuu = anak suruhan, bawahan ; ana nèru = orang undang (utk pesta); mone padhai = orang pandai (tukang); mone padhue = tukang bawa kabar, tukang berunding; ana padhue-padhai = UNS 1) Y p murid, 2) rasul, 3) jubir, but after extensive discussion of Gk profetei, prefer to leave as is.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dhèu leo sèra èci èèna ka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Dhèu leo sèra èci èèna ka sèmi lii dhu ana pajuu Ama Lamatua suri tèke peka na,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Rèngu rèdhi le, te ngaa ro'o boe re'a.<bt>'They have seen, but they don't want to know.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Rèngu tadèngi le, te ngaa ro'o boe tèke ètu d'ara.<bt>They have heard, but they don't want to think about (w/goal to understand).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèke mi dara = simpan di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tèke mi dara = simpan di hati (tidak mau direnungkan); nanene = tadèngi (connect to heart)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ladhe sèmi èèna, hud'i rèngu sène. Ra parcaya ia ka Lamatua,<bt>If that's the way they're gonna be, then let them be like that. Otherwise they might *believe the Lord/Master</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hudi = biarkan; Kèri sèmi èna"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hudi = biarkan; Kèri sèmi èna kalau begitu (neg overtones), kasi tenga sang dong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sèna ka Lamatua saku eele ia ka sasala ra.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>and the might Lord wipe away their wrongs.'"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hina: Implies that Jesus expected a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">hina: Implies that Jesus expected a negative outcome when he told stories to some people.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 6:9-10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus peka sasoa lii pakasame hini sèra<bt>Lord Yesus tells the meaning of the recent seed illustration</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:18-23; Lukas 8:11-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus peka dènge dhèu sèra sasoa lii pakasame hini èèna, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe miu me'a boe sasoa nèti lii upama deo na, carui risi hari miu me'a sasoa lii pakasame dhu leo.<bt>After that, Yesus began to tell those people the meaning of the recent seed illustration like this, "If you(PL) don't know/understand the meaning of that recent illustration, it's even more difficult for you to know/understand the meaning of other illustrations.</bt><v n="14" />De sasoa na sèmi ne'e ka: dhèu dhu ceb'e hini èèna, nuka dhèu dhu lole Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua.<bt>So it's meaning is like this. The person who was broadcasting those seeds is like a person who tells the Word of God.</bt><v n="15" />Hini dhu lèke ètu sebhe j'ara ka manu-bhui mai ra'a aa'i, nuka sèmi dhèu dhu nanene Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua. Te ngaa nèbhu boe, dhèu aae nidhu mai parame rare Lii Holo-Nori nèti d'ara dhèu èèna.<bt>The seed which land on the side of the path and the birds eat them all up, are like the Word of God in people's insides which is heard. But in a little while *Satan comes and robs away the aforementioned Word of God from the hearts (insides) of those people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil The figure of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil The figure of "take away the seed" loses the thread of the meaning. What the Devil is doing is not taking away seeds, he is removing the ability to assimilate the Word.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Aa hini dhu lèke ètu dedha hadhu, nuka sèmi dhèu dhu nanene, ka na sèmi nare Lii Holo-Nori èèna dènge d'ara karej'e.<bt>And the seed which landed on the rocks, is like people who listen and are pleased/happy.</bt><v n="17" />Te ngaa Lii Holo-Nori ne, taha nèbhu boe ètu d'ara dhèu èèna. Ropa nèngu paraga j'aj'èra lula na sèmi nare lii ne'e, na tèke eele.<bt>But this Word (full form) does not last long in their insides. When they encounter difficulty because of this Word (short anaphoric form), they leave it behind.</bt><v n="18" />Aa hini dhu lèke ètu talora j'u'u dhu padudhu, èci èèna ka dènge Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua dhu dhèu nanene.<bt>And the seed which lands in the middle of thorny grass, is like the Word of God a person who listens to.</bt><v n="19" />Te ngaa dhèu èèna bhute dhoka dènge rupa-rupa madha j'ara rai-haha dhu pakarej'e ngi'u na. Nèti èèna ka, j'ara se'e seti eele Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua nèti d'ara nèngu, ka j'aj'i heka ngaa-ngaa.<bt>But that aformentioned person is just looking only for the pleasant way of the world, so s/he can live well; because of that, everything else crowds out the Word of God from his/her insides, and there is nothing left.</bt><v n="20" />Te ngaa hini dhu lèke ètu dedha rai hèu mèngi, nuka sèmi dhèu dhu pasa dhilu ho nanene Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua dènge karej'e-karae. Tatao nèngu madhutu dad'èi Ama Lamatua dènge d'ara kateme. Dhèu ne'e tao j'ara-j'ara dhu pakarej'e d'ara Ama Lamatua, sama sèmi hini dhu nèti hua-hela. Abhu kahèi d'ai tèlu nguru hari, cahag'e d'ai èna nguru hari, aa abhu kahèi dhu d'ai cangasu hari.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the seed which lands on this fertile soil, is like as a person who engages his/her ears to listen to the Word of God well/happily. His/her deeds follow the will of God with his/her whole insides (=wholeheartedly). This [type of] person does things which please God's insides, just like the seed which produces well. Some can also get 30 times, some up to 60 times, and some even reach 100 times.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tasa mia = karmana; carui risi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tasa mia = karmana; carui risi hari = lebih sulit lagi; 14: nuka = is like; 15: ra'a &gt; ra'e (irrealis &gt; realis? activity &gt; accomplishment?); 17: taha = tahan (lama); core = angkat; bhèlu = lupa; 19: ti = is it a proximal form of tu? ma ~ mi; 20: tao j'ara-j'ara = does things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te ngaa nèngu ladhe dhodhoka sasab'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Te ngaa nèngu ladhe dhodhoka sasab'a mamuri ngi'u aae ne'e, ka dara nèngu bhèlu eele lii holo nori deo sa.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="What it is that is being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">What it is that is being multiplied by 30, 60, and 100 isn't clear, and perhaps doesn't need to be.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Baku paheo mere labhu ho saguru hari dènge soe<bt>Don't light a lamp and then close it up again with a basket</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 8:16-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Nèti dedha koha, Yesus tuhu hari lii padhai Na. Na peka hari lii upama èci, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Tasamia, ee! Miu mèdhi le, do dhae? Dhèu suru rare labhu, ka saguru eele hari dènge soe! Ka ra tèke asa ro'a koi la'e! Aad'o, sina ma? Te ladhe sèmi èèna, tèdhi boe saraa nèngu. Dhèu hud'i tao labhu ètu era dhu dedha, sèna ka dhèu rèdhi saraa nèngu.<bt>Yesus told told another illustration, saying like this, "How is it, ee! Do you(PL) see (=understand), or not.yet? A person lights a lamp, s/he then cover it up again with a basket! And s/he puts it under a bed! It wouldn't be that way, right? Cause if it was like that, we couldn't see its light. Because of that, a person does a lamp and puts it up high, so people can see its light.</bt><note reference="4:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:15, Lukas 11:33</note><v n="22" />Ngaa dhu dhèu pahuni deo ne'e, bèli-camèd'a dhèu rèdhi aa'i. Te ngaa dhu dhèu re'a boe lod'o deo ne'e, bèli-camèd'a dhèu re'a aa'i.<bt>That which is hidden now, in the future people will see it all. But [that] which people do not know today, in the future people will know it all.</bt><note reference="4:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:26, Lukas 12:2</note><v n="23" />De ladhe cee dhu dènge ro'a dhilu, na, nanene paie!<bt>So if anyone is with his/her ear holes, listen well!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="medhi = lihat (\hm with black);"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">medhi = lihat (\hm with black); sinama = conf tag, last syll extrametrical; paheo = menyalakan;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00148C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Nanene paie-iie! Ladhe miu tenge sasala dhèu, na, dhèu leo tenge sasala miu kahèi. Sèmi èèna kahèi, Ama Lamatua tenge sasala miu. Te ngaa Na tao bia risi hari nèti èèna.<bt>After that, He said again like this, "Listen well! If you(PL) look for a person's wrongs, then other people will also look for your wrongs. In the same way, God will look for your wrongs. But2 He will do heavier again than that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Where is the source of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Where is the source of the negative reading? Can/should this be rephrased so a positive reading is also possible.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:2, Lukas 6:38</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ladhe dhèu èci neo tenge tare'a-re'a dad'èi Lamatua, nèngu asa d'èlu-mèu. Te ngaa ladhe dhèu pusi-pahae boe dad'èi Lamatua, nèngu j'aj'i asa goa.&gt;&gt;<bt>If a person really want to look for the will of God2 s/he will become increasingly wise/smart (idiom--clean guts). But if someone doesn't care about the will of God2, s/he will become increasingly foolish/unwise."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="d'èlu mèu = Idiom 'pintar, arif,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">d'èlu mèu = Idiom 'pintar, arif, bijaksana, rajin' (lit. clean guts); asa = become increasingly</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 13:12, 25:29, Lukas 19:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus hia lii pakasame lula-nèti hini dhu muri unu na<bt>Illustration of seed that grows by itself</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="unu = sendiri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">unu = sendiri</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus tuhu hari lii padhai Na, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Paredha Ama Lamatua asa tabha kapai, sama sèmi hini dhu dhèu ceb'e ètu d'ara oka na.<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again, saying, "The *kingdom of God becomes increasingly big/great, just like a seed that a person plants in the garden/field.</bt><v n="27" />Nèngu ceb'e nare, ka la'e bhèj'i. Tao heka ai hèb'a mi hini sèra. Te ngaa hini sèra muri, ka asa kapai.<bt>The aforementioned owner of the field, plants the seed and go off and sleeps. He doesn't think about (idiom--hand mouth) the aforementioned seed. But that seed grows and increases in length.</bt><v n="28" />Hini se muri unu ra. Mulai ti rèu, hela, toke d'ai huri.<bt>This seed grows/lives on its own. It begins to leaf, flower, to the point that it produces.a.grain.head.</bt><v n="29" />Ropa kasere nare nganga'a dhu ètu d'ara oka mami, dhèu unu oka heka la'e puu-g'ètu kèna. Sèmi èèna kahèi, paredha Ama Lamatua. Lamatua ka dhu ad'u-ue aa'i-aa'i sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>When it is estimated that the grain/food in the field is ripe, the master of the field comes and harvests it. It's the same way with the kingdom of God. God2 is the one who causes it all to happen."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èra = kuat (kuasa, orang); 27:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">èra = kuat (kuasa, orang); 27: Dhèu unu oka = tuan kebun; 28: dadana = cabang; rèu = daun; hela = 1) bunga 2) parang; huri = bulir, grain head; hua 1) buah 2) muat; 29: puu-g'ètu = harvest, panen; mami = masak, ripe; mango = kering; nganga'a = 1) food 2) grain ; ropa ka sere nare = When it is thought that ; ad'u-ue = menyebabkan</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 3:13</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii pakasame lamusi dhu ana iiki<bt>Illustration of a tiny seed2</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:31-32, 34; Lukas 13:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus padhai lii hari, &lt;&lt;Ja'a peka hari lii upama èci sèmi ne'e ka: miu ladhe sèku, dhèu dhu j'aj'i unu Lamatua sèra. Uru èèna ciki di, nèbhu-nèbhu j'aj'i ae.<bt>After that, Yesus said again, "I'm telling another illustration like this. Take a look at the people who become owned by God2. [Those people] used to be just a few, but eventually became many people.</bt><v n="31" />Èèna sama sèmi lamusi aj'u dhu ana iiki-iiki.<bt>That's like a plant seed2 which is tiny.</bt><v n="32" />Ladhe èdhi sèla lamusi èèna, na muri mai, j'aj'i aj'u dhu kapai aae. Manu-bhui nèti mia-mia mai tèka tenge mamaho, dènge tao rèd'a ètu kolo aj'u èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>When we(inc) plant that seed, it grows and becomes a huge tree. Birds from all over come and alight [on it] looking for shade and making nests under the cover of that aforementioned tree."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check if dhèu-dhèu unu Lamatua is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">check if dhèu-dhèu unu Lamatua is too strong -- literal from Kupang Tuhan pung orang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />J'ara-j'ara a'aj'a Yesus madhutu rare'a dhèu.<bt>Yesus' way of teaching followed their understanding.</bt><v n="34" />Ladhe Na aj'a dhèu leo, Na pake lii pakasame. Te ngaa ladhe Na aj'a ana madhutu Na, Nèngu peka aa'i-aa'i sasoa lii pakasame sèra.<bt>When He taught other people, He used illustrations. But when He taught His followers, He always explained the meaning of those illustrations.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus pamau eele ngèlu aae<bt>Yesus tames the big wind</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:23-27; Lukas 8:22-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />D'ai lod'o nihia na, Yesus aj'a dhèu nèti dedha koha era. Hèia Na pua ana madhutu Na sèra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mai èdhi pakèd'i lati asa cabèka dano.&gt;&gt;<bt>In the afternoon, Yesus was still teaching people from on the boat. And He said, "Come on and let's go to the other side."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ka ra ca'e koha èci dènge Yesus. Ra pakèd'i tèke eele dhèu ae sèra ètu èèna. Te ngaa dhèu cahag'e ca'e koha leo madhutu Yesus si.<bt>And they got in the boat together with Yesus. They left behind lots of people there at that place. But some people got in another boat and followed Yesus (coll).</bt><v n="37-38" />Lod'o èèna, Yesus pasaluu kètu Na mi nanèlu, ka bhèj'i luu ètu hui koha. Nèbhu boe ka, ngèlu aae mai. Naha kapai, ka èi tao sabhori oe pènu koha Yesus si. Nèti èèna ka, ana madhutu Yesus sèra madha'u bia. Hèia ra parèi Ne, &lt;&lt;Ama! Kèd'i ku laa! Èdhi oe molo kèna! Te ngaa Ama pusi-pahae boe!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they had left, Yesus sleep in the back of the boat. Suddenly a big wind came. [There were] huge waves, and water poured in until Yesus' boat was almost swamped. Because of that, Yesus' followers were terrified. Big waves like that, but Yesus was still sleeping soundly. So they woke Him up, "Father! Get up now! We're about to drown/sink! Why are you (Father) quiet (=not doing anything about this)!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="no mention of pillow here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">no mention of pillow here</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ropa Yesus tadèngi lii parèi ra, ka Na kèd'i, hèia Na kai ngèlu, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mau ka!&gt;&gt; Ka Na paredha naha, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Mera ka!&gt;&gt; Hèia ngèlu mau, aa naha mera dènge ka.<bt>When Yesus heard their waking.up.words, He forbade the wind, and He ordered the waves, saying, "Quiet! Flatten!" Then the wind was quiet, and even the waves flattened just then.</bt><v n="40" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus jèke ana madhutu Na, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka miu madha'u sèmi èèna? Miu parcaya Ja'a, do aad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus spoke with anger to His followers, "Why were you(PL) afraid like that? Do you know2 Me, or not?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lèka = percaya, ; tadhe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">lèka = percaya, ; tadhe = kenal dan mengandalkan (character)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra madha'u dènge malaa, ka èci peka dènge èci, &lt;&lt;Te dhèu ngaa ne? Ka bisa ngèlu dènge naha, madhutu lii paredha Nèngu?&gt;&gt;<bt>They were all afraid and amazed/confused, and said to each other, "What kind of person is this? So even the wind and the waves follow/obey what He commands?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malaa = heran, bingung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">malaa = heran, bingung</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus babège ele nidhu ae nèti dhèu èci<bt>Yesus heals a crazy person who a large many evil.spirits have afflicted</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:28-34; Lukas 8:26-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na sèra d'ai cabèka dano Galilea. Era èèna, ngara na Garasa.<bt>After that, Yesus and His followers (coll) arrived on the other side of Galilea. That place was called Garasa.</bt><v n="2-6" />Ètu èèna, abhu dhèu mone èci dhu nidhu tao, ka na huj'u. Dhèu huj'u ne pea ètu era padhane dhèu madhe. Mèu-mèda na kako ca'e-puru ledhe ètu èèna, dènge pake boe mèdha-papake. Na pa'oo-parodha ma'ète boe, aa na nare hadhu ho tuku iisi na toke d'ai nu'a. Na èra titu kèna. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu èci sa bisa boe èki ne. Masi ka ra èki dènge rate bèsi èèna ka, bisa boe kahèi. Pèri-pèri hari, dhèu uj'u haga-ai na kahèi, pake rate dènge kanau bèsi, te ngaa na pama'ète aa'i si. Dhèu ne èra bia, nèti èèna ka, èci sa taha boe ne.<bt>In that place there was a man whom evil.spirits had afflicted, and he was crazy. This crazy man, lived at the place where they buried dead people. Day and night he went up and down the mountain/hill there, and he didn't wear anything. And he shouted.accusingly things of no substance, and he took stones to beat his body to the point that there were fresh.wounds. He was very strong, [and] nobody was able to oppose him to tie him. Even if/when they tied him with iron chains, it wouldn't work. People had also hog-tied him thoroughly, using chains and iron rings, but he broke them all apart. He was incredibly strong, and because of that not one [person] was up to defeat him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="abhu often in presentational clauses; ro'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">abhu often in presentational clauses; ro'a dhèu madhe = kuburan; mèu-mèda = siang-malam; j'èru1 = mampu lawan ; j'èru2 = jeruk; j'èru3 = topang (support, shore up); karadhe = ikat dgn belit ulang2</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00303C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10cm;textWrapping:none">Dhèu huj'u dhu nidhu tao<bt>Crazy man whom many evil.spirits have afflicted</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ropa Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na puru nèti dedha koha, dhèu huj'u èèna ladhe nèdhi rèngu nèti kaj'èu. Hèia na kalua nèti era padhane dhèu madhe, ka na mai patitu kètu urutuu ètu madha Yesus.<bt>When Yesus and His followers descended from the boat, that crazy person saw them from far off. So he came out of the place where they bury dead people, and he came and knelt in front of Yesus.</bt><v n="7-8" />Ropa ladhe nèdhi rèhu dhèu ne'e, hèia Yesus peka, na, &lt;&lt;Hee, nidhu bhelu! Kalua pakaj'èu nèti dhèu ne'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>When he saw the face of this person, Yesus said, "Hee, bad evil.spirit! Come out and go far away from this person here."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nidhu bhelu = phrase associated w/language"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">nidhu bhelu = phrase associated w/language of curse/cursing</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Èle èèna ka, dhèu èèna pajèka, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Weh! Èu neo tao ngaa mi ja'a? Ja'a ke'a Èu ne Yesus, Ana nèti Ama Lamatua dhu Koasa Risi Eele. Ja'a manèngi Èu baku paj'èra ja'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, the person screamed.with.anger, saying, "Weh! You want to do what with me? I know You are Yesus, the Child of God who is full of power. I ask that You cause difficulty for me!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Hèia Yesus karèi ne, &lt;&lt;Ngara èu cee?&gt;&gt;<bt>So then Yesus asked him, "What's your name?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Na dhaa, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ngara ja'a <span class="Italic">Legion, </span>lula ji'i ae titu kèna, sama sèmi ca kaboko sordad'u!&gt;&gt;<bt>He answered, saying, "My name is Legion, because we(exc) are a great many [in number], like a grouping of soldiers (loan)!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dialectal = hèia &gt; haia &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dialectal = hèia &gt; haia &gt; hia</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Èle èèna ka, nidhu sèra peka re dhèu huj'u èèna, ho manèngi Yesus, sèna ka baku pua rèngu kalua nèti d'ara rae ne.<bt>After that, those evil.spirits spoke through the aforementioned person, to ask Yesus to not send them out from this village's area.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mati'a = hiccough, hek ; cèki"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mati'a = hiccough, hek ; cèki = reaction (e.g. to chili) that constricts thoat and makes it hard to speak; kabholo1 = s.t. stuck in throat ; kabholo2 = white ball that grows inside a maturing coconut ; doa 1) belch, burp 2) lift head (as sea turtle taking a breath)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Kaj'èu boe nèti èèna, abhu hahi ca oka dhu dhèu madhenge. Ele boe hahi sèra dua riho ngi'u. Dhu tenge nganga'a ètu sebhe ledhe.<bt>Not far from there were a herd of pigs (lit. a field of pigs) that people were watching/guarding. Those pigs were about 2,000 bodies. They were looking for food on the side of the mountain.</bt><v n="12" />Ka nidhu sèra manèngi Yesus, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Hia ji'i maso asa d'ara hahi sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>And those evil.spirits asked Yesus, saying, "Let us(exc) go inside those pigs there."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tadèngi nare sèmi èèna, hèia Yesus d'èi kahèi. Ka nidhu sèra kalua nèti d'ara dhèu èèna, ka lasi asa d'ara hahi sèra. Hèia hahi sèra rai paj'ala, ka lasi asa sebhe tèbhi, ka ra manahu asa d'ara dano, hèia madhe aa'i si.<bt>Hearing that, Yesus agreed (lit also wanted it). And so the evil.spritis came out from inside the aforementioned person, and went inside those pigs there. Suddenly those pigs ran helter-skelter to the edge of the drop-off, and they fell into the lake, so they all died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rai paj'ala = lari menyebar, scatter;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">rai paj'ala = lari menyebar, scatter; ridhu = terjun ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ropa dhèu j'aga hahi sèra ladhe rèdhi madha j'ara dhu j'aj'i èèna, ra madha'u titu kèna. Ka rai lasi peka palème dènge dhèu ètu d'ara rae-rae dhu dètu ètu era èèna. Nèbhu boe dhèu canau-kateme mai neo re'a.<bt>When the people watching those pigs saw the way things had happened, they were terrified. And they ran home telling people in the villages near that place. Not long after that a bunch of people ran coming wanting to know.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ephugon: flee, escape from danger, run"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">ephugon: flee, escape from danger, run out of fear, seek safety, shun, avoid</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dhèu sèra mai paraga dènge Yesus, ka ra ladhe la'a, na, dhèu dhu nidhu tao èèna, madhèdi ètu èèna kahèi. Dhèu èèna pake le mèdha-papake. Kahadhu na mase'a le. Rèdhi sèmi èèna, hèia dhèu sèra madha'u. Lula rèngu re'a le, ladhe dhèu cee dhu bisa babège eele nidhu nèti d'ara dhèu huj'u èèna, nèngu tare'a-re'a dhèu èra risi.<bt>They came and met with Yesus, and they went and saw the aforementioned person who had been afflicted by evil.spirits sitting near there. That person was wearing clothes. His brain was healthy/lucid. Seeing these things like that, those people were afraid. Because they already knew that whoever was able to evict the evil.spirits from that crazy person, was truly a powerful person.</bt><v n="16" />Èle èèna ka, dhèu aa'i-aa'i sèra lasi peka palème ètu mia-mia, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ji'i ngèdhi le dènge madha, dhèu huj'u ne èle le. Sèmi èèna kahèi hahi dhu madhe ètu d'ara dano.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, all of those people told this around everywhere, saying, "We(exc) have seen this with our eyes, that crazy man is healed, and also the pigs who died in the lake."</bt><v n="17" />Ka dhèu kabarai èèna mai manèngi ho Yesus tèke eele ka rai rèngu.<bt>Because of that, all the inhabitants of that area came requesting that Yesus hurry and leave (lit run away from) their area.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kahadhu 1) otak, 2) (animal) pregnant;;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kahadhu 1) otak, 2) (animal) pregnant;; 16: ngèdhi 2p-see</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ngangee na, mèu le hi."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ngangee na, mèu le hi.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ropa Yesus neo ca'e hari asa dedha koha, ka dhèu dhu èle nèti huj'u dhu nidhu tao èèna manèngi Yesus, sèna ka nèngu madhutu Ne kahèi.<bt>When Yesus wanted to get into a boat again, the person who was healed from the craziness which the evil.spirits had made asked Yesus if he could also follow Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Te ngaa Yesus kai. Ka Na peka dènge dhèu èèna, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Be'a risi èu lèpa ka asa èmu, ho peka dènge a'ari èu, ngaa dhu Ama Lamatua tao le mi dedha èu. Peka dènge si, mema Ama Lamatua sue èu titu kèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus forbade him. And He said to the aforementioned person, saying, "It's better that you return home to your house, to tell your kin what God has done for you. Tell them, that God *loves/pities you a lot."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mi dedha = benefactive; bera-bera ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mi dedha = benefactive; bera-bera = accompany; bhera = pusi boe, dale boe</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Èle èèna, hèia dhèu èèna pakèd'i la'e palème rae-rae nèti canguru kota, dhu ngara na &lt;Dekapolis&gt;. Na lole ngaa dhu Yesus tao le mi dedha nèngu. Dhèu-dhèu dhu tadèngi lii lolo na, malaa aa'i mèu-mèu, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Mema lèke tare'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, that person left and went around to the villages of the ten cities, which they call 'Dekapolis'. He told what Yesus had done for him. People who heard this story were really amazed, saying, "That's really true."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus pamamuri hari ana Yairus. Aa puri-pa'èle dhèu bhèni èci nèti papèd'a bhèni<bt>Yesus causes.to.live again the child of Yairus. And heals a woman from woman's sickness</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:18-26; Lukas 8:40-56)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Èle ka, Yesus si pakèd'i hari dènge koha asa cabèka dano. Ropa ra puru nèti dedha koha, dhèu ae mai lingu rare Yesus.<bt>After that, Yesus left again by boat [and went] across the lake. When he descended from the boat, many people came gathering around Yesus.</bt><v n="22" />Dhèu èci mai, ngara na Yairus. Nèngu ne, kètu èmu manèngi-mangaj'i dhèu Yahudi ètu kota èèna. Ropa nèngu nèdhi Yesus, ka mai patitu kètu urutuu ètu madha Yesus.<bt>One person came, named Yairus. this one was head of the house of worship of the Jahudi people in that city. When he saw Yesus, he came [and] bowed his head in front of Yesus.</bt><v n="23" />Ka na pamako, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama, ee! Ana bhèni ja'a, heka canguru dua tèu, pèd'a oe madhe. Mai lati ku asa èmu ja'a, sèna ka puri-pa'èle ne nèti papèd'a na.&gt;&gt;<bt>And he asked, "Father, ee! One of my daughters who is 12 years, is sick [and] almost dead. Let's go now to my house, so that [you] can heal her from that sickness."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lingu = kelilingi, kerumun; 22: mai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">lingu = kelilingi, kerumun; 22: mai pa haha isi = datang merendahkan diri</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:23" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama mai ho bane ai mi nèngu, sèna ka na be'a hari, ka mamuri.&gt;&gt; Ètu nèi, &lt;&lt;manèngi dhèu bane ai&gt;&gt;, sasoa na, &lt;&lt;manèngi pa'èle dhèu&gt;&gt;. Ana bhèni ne, umur na, sasuri lii Yunani suri ètu ayat 42.</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Hèia Yesus la'e dènge ka, madhutu Yairus asa èmu na.<bt>So Yesus went right away, following Yairus to his house.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa ètu d'ara kakako rèngu, dhèu ae titu kèna, ka ra seti Ne nèti haa, nèti dhimu.<bt>But on the way, there were a huge number of people crowding Him, from the west, from the east (idiom = on all sides, from all directions).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sa haa, sa dhimu = idiom;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sa haa, sa dhimu = idiom; kakako = perjalanan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ètu talora dhèu ae sèra, abhu dhèu bhèni èci dhu pèd'a dhèu bhèni. Papèd'a ne loe boe canguru dua tèu kèna.<bt>Among those many people, was a woman who had woman's sickness. Her sickness hadn't stopped for 12 years.</bt><v n="26" />Mèdha-panyau dènge doi-dhari dhèu bhèni ne'e, èle aa'i mèu-mèu ho b'ae dote. Te ngaa papèd'a na èle boe, asa na hoe.<bt>The belongings and the wealth of this woman, were all gone (idiom) to pay the doctor. But that sickness hadn't gone away, but had gotten worse instead.</bt><v n="27-29" />Bhèni ne tadèngi ae le dhèu palolo ngaa dhu Yesus tao. Nèti èèna ka, na mai pasuki asa talora dhèu ae sèra, ho na padètu dènge Yesus. Na pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Sad'i ja'a gai lèke sebhe kodho Na di, tatu papèd'a ja'a èle.&gt;&gt;<bt>This woman had heard a lot of people telling about Yesus. Because of that, she came squeezing.through.crowd in the middle of those many people, to get.close.to Yesus.Because she thought like this, "If.only/as.long.as I can just touch the edge of His clothes, my sickness will be healed."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ae boe didn't stop = ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ae boe didn't stop = ; pèdha dhèu bhèni = female sickness; 26: mèdha-panyau = harta benda; hoe = tambah parah; 29: paseti = ba seti (immobile); pasuki = get in through the crowd (active);</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ètu talora dhèu ae sèra, abhu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ètu talora dhèu ae sèra, abhu dhèu bhèni èci dhu pèda hèru (pèda bhèni se) canguru dua tèu kèna.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00310C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ropa na gai lèke sebhe kodho Yesus, kabèdhi laa raa bhèni ne tèja eele dènge. Hèia na rasa, na be'a le.<bt>When she touched the edge of Yesus clothes, suddenly her female blood (or: the blood/bleeding of this woman) stopped. so she felt herself well then.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Lod'o èèna kahèi, Yesus rasa a'èra kalua nèti d'ara ngi'u Na. Ka Na kabib'a asa kabodho, ho ladhe asa dhèu ae sèra, ka Na karèi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nèti miu se, cee ka dhu gai lèke kodho Ja'a?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that same moment also, Yesus knew that strength had gone.out from His body. And he looked.back over his shoulder to look at the many people (coll), and He asked, saying, "You(PL) here, who touched My clothes?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="raa embarrassing to hear or use"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">raa embarrassing to hear or use in the context of women. tèja eele = berenti;; 30: Dara ciki oo'e èna kahèi = pada sa'at itu juga; kabhodho = back, (some concern about Sabu speakers seeing this as a vulgar Sabu term, which as part of a Sabu compound refers to anus, concern dismissed by most of the UNS's)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ka ana madhutu Na dhaa, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama, ladhe ku laa. Dhèu ae paseti sèmi ne'e. Nga tao ka Ama karèi, peka na, &lt;Cee ka dhu gai kodho Ja'a?&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>And the followers answered, saying, "Father, take a look. Lots of people are crowding in like this. Why do you (Father) ask saying, who touched my clothes?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kèpe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kèpe =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Te ngaa Yesus ladhe pala-lème, neo ne'a cee ka dhu gai lèke sebhe kodho Na.<bt>Then Yesus looked all around, wanting to know who was the one who touched the edge of His clothes.</bt><v n="33" />Ropa Yesus karèi sèmi èèna, hèia bhèni èèna madha'u bia. Èle èèna ka, na mai patitu kètu urutuu ètu madha Yesus, ka na mangaku, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ja'a ka dhu gai lèke sebhe kodho Ama ku deo na.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus asked like that, the aforementioned woman was terrified. After that, she came [and] knelt in front of Yesus and she confessed/acknowledged, "Father! I am the one who touche the edge of your clothes just now."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Hèia Yesus peka mi bhèni ne, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Lula èu parcaya Ja'a dènge d'ara kateme, nèti èèna ka, èu èle le. Lamu ka èmu, dènge d'ara karej'e-karae.&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus spoke to this woman, saying, "Sister [+affection]. Because you believe in Me with your whole insides, therefore you are healed. Go to your house, with happy insides [doublet]."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ana hèni = [+sayang]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ana hèni = [+sayang]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ropa Yesus padhai lii era, hèia dhèu mai nèti èmu Yairus, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ira ii! Ana mu madhe le. De baku paj'èra ia ka Ama Mese. Nèngu la'e ia ka sa nèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>While Yesus was speaking, suddenly a person/people came from the house of Yairus, saying, &lt;&lt;Ira ii! [+dismay] Your child is already dead. So (consequently)consequently) don't cause any more difficulty for Father Teacher. He doesn't need to go anymore.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Te ngaa Yesus pusi boe dènge lii padhai lii dhèu ne'e. Ka Na peka dènge Yairus, &lt;&lt;Èu baku madha'u, ee! Parcaya mi Ama Lamatua di.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus wasn't concerned with what this person had said. And he said to Yairus, "You shouldn't be afraid, ee! Only just believe."</bt><v n="37" />Hèia Yesus la'e dènge ka, tèke eele ana madhutu Na cahag'e. Nèti dhoka Petrus, Yakobis dènge Yohanis.<bt>So Yesus went then, leaving behind some of His followers. [He took] only Petrus, Yakobis, and Yohanis.</bt><v n="38" />Ropa d'ai èmu Yairus, rèngu rèdhi dhèu jau oob'a-jau oob'a, aa tadèngi cahag'e tangi d'ara pèd'a.<bt>When [they] arrived at the house of Yairus, they saw and heard people making a ruckus [associated with death], and some crying with sadness.</bt><v n="39" />Yesus maso asa d'ara, ka Na karèi si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka miu maruru dènge tangi sèmi ne'e? Ana ne'e madhe boe! Nèngu dhoka bhèj'i di.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus went into the house and asked, "Why are you(PL) making a ruckus2 and crying like this? This child is not dead! She's only just sleeping."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oba-oba = ribut; jau oob'a-jau oob'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">oba-oba = ribut; jau oob'a-jau oob'a</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Dhèu ètu sèra tadèngi Yesus peka sèmi èèna, ka ra mari pakapengo hèb'a dènge Ne.<bt>Those people there heard Yesus say that, and they laughed at Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèia Na pua dhèu sèra kalua aa'i nèti d'ara kama ana dhu madhe èèna. Ka Na paroa ina-ama ana bhèni ne, dènge ana madhutu Na dhèu tèlu sèra, maso asa d'ara.<bt>So then He ordered all those people out from inside the room of the aforementioned child who had died. And He summoned the mother-father of this daughter, and the three of His followers, to come into the room.</bt><v n="41" />Hèia Yesus kèpe kacui-aai ana dhu madhe ne, ka Na padhai lii pake lii rèngu, lii Aram, aku Nèngu na, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Talita kum!&gt;&gt;</span> (Sasoa na, &lt;&lt;Ana bhèni! Kèd'i ka!&gt;&gt;)<bt>Then Yesus grabbed/held the hand of the aforementioned child who had died, and He said using their language, saying, "<span class="Italic">Talita kum!</span>" Which means, "Daughter! Get up!"</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01713b.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.5cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42-43" />Kabèdhi laa, ana dhu madhe èèna mamuri hari. Hèia na kèd'i titu, ka na kako. Hèia Yesus peka dènge ina na, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Hia ana ne'e na'a-ninu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Suddenly the aforementioned child who had died lived again, she stood up, and she walked. Then Yesus spoke to her mother, saying, "Give this child eat-drink!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dhèu ae ètu sèra dhu rèdhi j'ara dhu j'aj'i ne, ra malaa titu kèna. Hèia Yesus kai si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mage mi peka dènge dhèu èci sa, Ja'a ka dhu pamamuri hari ana ne.&gt;&gt;<bt>The many people there who saw what had happened were very amazed/confused. Then Yesus forbade them saying, "Take.care that you(PL) not be telling this to a single person, that I just cause.live again this daughter/girl."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'aj'aj'i = kejadian, peristiwa; ale ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">j'aj'aj'i = kejadian, peristiwa; ale = let know, sebut, mention</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu Nasaret ro'o boe sèmi rare Lamatua Yesus<bt>The Nasaret people do not like/reject the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:53-58; Lukas 4:16-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na sèra aa'i-aa'i ra, lèpa hari asa rae Na, Nasaret.<bt>After that, Yesus and all His followers (coll), returned/home to His village, Nasaret.</bt><v n="2" />Lod'o èèna lèke dènge lod'o sabaj'a dhèu Yahudi. Hèia Yesus la'e asa d'ara èmu manèngi-mangaj'i ho Na aj'a Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua ètu èèna. Lod'o èèna, dhèu ae lasi manèngi-mangaj'i. Ropa ra tadèngi Yesus aj'a Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua, hèia dhèu aa'i-aa'i sèra malaa, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu ne mèu samia ne! Na dènge koasa kahèi! Tasamia ka Na sèmi èèna, ee?<bt>When it was the day on which work was prohibited, Yesus went into the house of worship to teach the Word of God there. That day many people had gone to *worship. When they heard Yesus teaching the Word of God, all the people (coll) were amazed, saying, "This person here, he's really smart! And He's also got power! How can He be like that, ee?</bt><v n="3" />Nèngu ne'e dhoka tuka aj'u di. Èdhi tadhe ina Na, Maria. Sèmi èèna kahèi ari Na, Yakobis, Yoses, Yudas dènge Simon, dènge ari Na dhèu bhèni sèra. Rèngu dènge èdhi pea ca rae.&gt;&gt; Dhèu se'e ngee ètu d'ara rèngu na, rèngu mèu risi nèti Yesus. Nèti èèna ka, ra d'èi heka nanene Ne.<bt>He's a carpenter. We(inc) know2 his mother, named Maria. In the same way His younger.sibling.same.sex Yakobis, Yoses, Yudas and Simon, and His younger.sibling females (coll). They and we(inc) live in the same village." Those people were thinking to themselves, they were more clever than Yesus. Because of that, they no longer wanted to listen/obey Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ka Yesus peka, &lt;&lt;Mema tare'a! Dhèu pakab'ua risi dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua nèti rae leo. Te ngaa ra pakab'ua boe dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua dhu nèti rae nèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus said, "It's really true! People put greater value on a spokesman of God from another village. But they don't value a spokesman of God who is from his village."</bt><note reference="6:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 4:44</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6a" />D'ara dhèu sèra adhu sèmi hadhu, ka ra parcaya boe lii padhai lii Yesus. Nèti èèna ka, Na malaa, hèia Na pake boe koasa Na. Ka Na puri-pa'èle dhoka dhèu pèri di, ètu èèna.<bt>The insides of those people was hard like rocks, and they didn't believe anymore what Yesus was saying. Because of that, He was amazed, and so He didn't use His power. And He healed only a few people there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boe = tidak; heka = tidak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">boe = tidak; heka = tidak lagi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus pua ana madhutu Na dhèu canguru dua lasi lole Lii Lolo Be'a Ama Lamatua<bt>Lord Yesus orders His 12 followers to go tell the Word (short form) of God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:5-15; Lukas 9:1-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6b" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus kako palème asa rae-rae dhu padètu ètu sèra, ho aj'a dhèu j'ara mamuri Ama Lamatua.<bt>After that, Yesus walked around to the nearby villages there, to teach the Word of God.</bt><v n="7" />Na paroa nare ana madhutu Na dhèu canguru dua sèra, ka Na pua rèngu lasi dua-dua ho lole Lii Lolo Be'a nèti Ama Lamatua. Na hia si koasa kahèi, ho babège eele nidhu nèti d'ara dhèu.<bt>He summoned His 12 followers (coll), and He ordered them two by two to tell the Good News from/about God. He gave them power to evict evil.spirits from inside people.</bt><v n="8-9" />Na peka dènge si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu baku mèti mèdha ae ètu d'ara kakako miu. Baku mèti nganga'a, doi, dènge tas. Mèti dhoka tatea, salapa ètu haga, dènge kodho ètu ua di.<bt>He told them, saying, "You(PL) shouldn't carry many things on this journey of yours. Don't carry food, money, or a bag. Carry only a walking.staff, the shoes on your feet, and the clothes on your back.</bt><v n="10" />Ladhe cee dhu sèmi rare miu ètu èmu ra, miu pea dhoka ètu èèna di, toke d'ai pakèd'i hari.<bt>Whoever receives you(PL) in their house, you just stay there, until it's time to leave again.</bt><v n="11" />Te ngaa ladhe miu lami asa era èci, hèia dhèu ètu sèra sèmi rare boe miu, aa ra d'èi boe nanene lii padhai lii miu, tèke eele era èèna. Aa peka mi dhèu sèra, na, &lt;Miu mo'o boe nanene, si! De bèli-camèd'a sèmi mere pala mi!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But if/when you(PL) go to another place, and those people don't receive you, and they don't want to listen to your message, brush.off away dust from the soles of your feet at that place. Tell those people, "You(PL) don't even want to listen! So in the future, you will get your due reward! (idiom--you'll get your division)"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèti = 2p-bring, carry; kodho ètu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mèti = 2p-bring, carry; kodho ètu ua = frozen Idiom ~ ngi'u; pa'ua = put on set of clothes; 10: sèmi miu = terima kamu; 11: kabaj'èla = telapak kaki; pala = balasan; pe = nanti ; mere = miu nare; dede kabaj'èla = tinggalkan tempat dan tidak rencana kembali</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-11-21 08:41:30Z">bottom of foot</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:8-11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara Alkitab lii Yunani, suri peka na, &lt;&lt;caro eele ahu nèti haga rèngu&gt;&gt;. Tèu èèna ètu nèi, dhèu biasa caro eele ahu nèti haga rèngu ho j'aj'i tadha, peka na, dhèu dhu ro'o boe nanene, na, pasae rare pala rèngu unu ra. Ladhe kahèi ètu <span class="Italic">Lukas </span>10:4-11; <span class="Italic">Lii Lolo nèti Ana Pajuu-paleha </span>13:51.</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Èle èèna ka, ra lasi lole Lii Lolo Be'a. Ra peka, dhèu aa'i-aa'i hud'i ele ho'a nèti sasala-sasigo ra, ka lèpa ho mamuri madhutu dad'èi Lamatua.<bt>After that, they went and told the Good News. They told the people they should live according to the ways of God2.</bt><v n="13" />Ka ra babège eele nidhu nèti d'ara dhèu. Ra pasuti èi lèngi mi kètu dhèu pèd'a, aa sabaj'a ho pa'èle si nèti papèd'a. Ka ra èle dènge.<bt>They evicted evil.spirits from people. They poured.slowly [coconut/cooking] oil on the heads of sick people, and prayed2, healed them from sickness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èi lèngi = minyak kelapa manèngi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">èi lèngi = minyak kelapa manèngi = berdoa, sembahyang; pasuti = drip on, teteskan</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yakobis 5:14</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ra pare pamadhe Yohanis tuka sarani<bt>They cut (behead) to dead Yohanis the Tukang Baptiser</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:1-12; Lukas 9:7-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Lod'o èèna, dhèu ètu mia-mia tadhe aa'i le Yesus. Dhèu aae Herodes tadèngi le lii lolo lula-nèti koasa Yesus kahèi. Dhèu palolo ètu mia-mia, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Yohanis tuka sarani èèna, mamuri hari le ètu d'ara ngi'u Yesus! Nèti èèna ka, Na bisa tao tadha malaa sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, people everywhere all knew2 Yesus. Stories about power that Yesus had done, king Herodes had also heard. People were telling them everywhere, saying, "Yohanis, the Tukang Baptiser, is alive again in Yesus body! Because of that, He can do those amazing *signs."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Te ngaa dhèu cahag'e hari peka, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Aad'o! Ne'e ne, Elia dhu mamuri hari d'ara ngi'u Yesus.&gt;&gt;<bt>But some other people said, saying, "No! This one is Elia who is alive again in Yesus body." And other people still said, "This person here, is one of God's other spokesmen from before/long ago."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Aa dhèu cahag'e hari, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu ne'e ne, dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua dhu leo hari nèti uru sèra.&gt;&gt;<note reference="6:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:14, Markus 8:28, Lukas 9:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ropa dhèu aae Herodes tadèngi nare lii lolo dhèu se'e lula-nèti Yesus, ka na dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Èèna Yohanis tuka sarani, dhu ca hari ni ja'a hia dhèu pare pamadhe le, te ngaa na mamuri hari!&gt;&gt;<bt>When king Herodes heard what people were saying about2 Yesus, he responded, saying, "It is Yohanis, the Tukang Baptiser, who I once had people cut to death, but he is alive again!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17-18" />Dhèu aae Herodes pua sèmi èèna, lula nèngu lii langu dènge Yohanis. Lii lolo na sèmi ne'e ka: dhèu aae Herodes leo nare dhèu èmu ari na, Pelipus, ngara na Herodias. Aa te ngaa Pelipus dènge Herodias dhae pa'ia mèka. Nèti èèna ka, Yohanis kai pahari-pahari, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama dhèu aae baku leo dènge dhèu èmu ari mu. Te èèna sisu ad'a èdhi dhèu Yahudi.&gt;&gt; Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Herodes leo nare bhèni ne'e kahèi. Hèia na pua dhèu lasi kèpe rare Yohanis, ho pamaso ne asa d'ara bèdho.<bt>Previously, king Herodes ordered people to go catch/arrest Yohanis the Tukang baptiser to put him into jail. Because Yohanis forbade Herodes to not take Herodias, the wife of his younger.sibling, Filipus.At that time Yohanis had forbid him several times, saying, "Father king, be careful that you not take (=marry) your younger.sibling's wife, cause that violates the customary.law of we(inc) Jahudi people." But, nevertheless, Herodes married this woman.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhèu-èmu = isteri; 18: tatao a-ad'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhèu-èmu = isteri; 18: tatao a-ad'a = ajaran; gagu = ganggu</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:17-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 3:19-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Lula Yohanis kai pèri hari le, hèia bhèni ne tèka d'ara dènge ne, ka na neo pamadhe ne. Te ngaa lake nare mèka, te Herodes dhu pamaso le Yohanis asa d'ara bèdho la'e.<bt>Because Yohanis had forbidden several times, this woman was annoyed/angry with him and wanted to kill Yohanis. But, lest she have opportunity, Herodes had put Yohanis into prison.</bt><v n="20" />Ka na pua sordad'u sèra madhenge paie ne ètu d'ara bèdho.<bt>And he ordered the soldiers (coll) to guard him well in prison.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Herodes madha'u dènge Yohanis. Na ne'a tare'a, Yohanis ne dhèu dhu Ama Lamatua pua mai. Aa Yohanis ne dhèu d'ara mola. Herodes d'èi nanene lii padhai lii Yohanis kahèi. Te ngaa stèka-stèka, d'ara na pèd'a nanene lii padhai lii Yohanis.<bt>Because Herodes was afraid of Yohanis. He really knew that Yohanis was a person who God had sent to come. And this Yohanis was a straight/pure person. Herodes also wanted to listen to what Yohanis had to say. But sometimes his insides were sick listening to what Yohanis was saying.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ka ca tèka, Herodias abhu lod'o dhu be'a, sèna ka na b'ala d'ara pèd'a na. Lod'o èèna, lèke dènge hari jadi Herodes. Ka ra nèru dhèu aae-dhèu kapai mai ra'a-sisi hari jad'i. Dhèu dhu mai sèra, ama-ama dhu paredha, ama-ama sordad'u, dènge dhèu heka-dhèu heka ad'a ètu Galilea.<bt>Once, this woman found a good day/opportunity to revenge her hatred. That day was the birthday (Malay loan) of Herodes). They invited the important people to come [and] feast (idiom--eat-meat) on the aforementioned birthday. Those people who came, fathers of government, fathers of the soldiers, and fathers of traditional customs in Galilea.</bt><v n="22" />Ètu d'ara talora tatao èèna, ana bhèni Herodias la'e roge. Na roge be'a risi eele, ka d'ara Herodes dènge dhèu dhu nèru sèra karej'e bia. Nèti èèna ka, Herodes paroa ne mai asa madha, ka na karèi, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èu neo manèngi ngaa? Èu peka ho ja'a hia.<bt>In the middle of these activities the daughter of Herodias went to dance. She danced really well, and Herodes' insides, and the people who had been invited were extremely pleased. Because of that, Herodes summoned her to come before him, and he asked, saying, "What do you want to ask for? You say it so I give it.</bt><v n="23" />Èu manèngi era paredha ja'a ne bagi dua, hia èu cabèka èèna ka, ja'a ko'o kahèi. Ja'a subha dènge ngara Ama Lamatua!&gt;&gt;<bt>[If] you ask for my kingdom here to be divided in two, and even give you half, I agree (=also want it). I swear by the name of God!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="babèdho ' door' &gt; bèdho 'jail';"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">babèdho ' door' &gt; bèdho 'jail'; 20: catèka-catèka = sekali-sekali ~ stèka-stèka; 22: roge = ronggeng; mako dai seli = softly &amp; gently; 23: subha = sumpah; dhoo 1) kutuk, 2) sumpah, (clear from context)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ka ana bhèni èèna la'e karèi ina na, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ina, ee! Madhutu ngangee ina ku, na, ja'a manèngi ngaa dhu be'a risi nèti ama ku?&gt;&gt;<bt>And the aforementioned girl went [and] asked her mother, saying, "Mother, ee! According to your thinking now, what is best that I request from my father?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka ina na dhaa, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Lamu asa madha ama mu ho peka dènge ne, ja'a manèngi dhoka kètu Yohanis di.&gt;&gt;<bt>And her mother answered, saying, "Go in front of your father and say to him, I ask only for the head of Yohanis."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ka ana bhèni ne la'e asa madha Herodes, ka na peka, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ja'a manèngi kètu Yohanis, tao ètu d'ara dula èci hia ja'a. Deo ne'e ne, kahèi!&gt;&gt;<bt>And the aforementioned girl went before Herodes, and she said, saying, "Father! I ask for the head of Yohanis, put on a platter/tray and give it to me. Do it now!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kokotai = nyiru, antan; sama artinya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kokotai = nyiru, antan; sama artinya dengan dulang; dula = dulang; salabhe = woven from palm leaves, carry food such as meat; dhèu heka da rae = tokoh masyarakat; pega = piring</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ropa Herodes tadèngi nare lii manèngi ana bhèni na, ka d'ara na cag'ag'a. Te ngaa nèngu bisa heka ère hari lii subha nèngu deo na, lula dhèu ètu sèra tadèngi aa'i le.<bt>When Herodes heard the request of his daughter, then he was completely surprised. But he could no longer take back his previous oath, because the people there had all heard it.</bt><v n="27" />Èle èèna ka, Herodes paredha komedhaa sordad'u lasi poro rare kètu Yohanis nèti d'ara bèdho.<bt>After that, Herodes commanded the commander (loan) of the soldiers to go and cut off the head of Yohanis in the jail.</bt><v n="28" />Ropa ra poro rare, ra tao asa d'ara dula èci, ka rèti la'a asa ana bhèni èèna. Na sèmi nare, hèia nèti asa ina na la'e.<bt>When they had cut it off, they put it on a platter/tray, and brought it to the aforementioned girl. She received it like that, and then took it to her mother.</bt><v n="29" />Ropa ana madhutu Yohanis sèra tadèngi ra poro rèti le kètu Yohanis, rèngu mai nedhe rèti ngi'u nèngu lasi padhane.<bt>When the followers of Yohanis heard that they they had cut off Yohanis' head, they came to get his body [and] went [and] buried it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="caa pakabèdhi = &gt; cag'ag'a /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">caa pakabèdhi = &gt; cag'ag'a / cag'ag'a-sahèka = takuju; 27: dara bèdho = dalam penjara ; bedho = tutup; komedha = komandan; 29: poro</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">D'ai sange ne'e ka, lii lolo mamadhe Yohanis.<bt>Up to here is the story of the death of Yohanis.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus panga'a lèmi riho dhèu<bt>Lord Yesus feeds 5,000 people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:13-21; Lukas 9:10-17; Yohanis 6:1-14)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ca lod'o hari, ana madhutu Yesus dhu Na pua lasi asa rae-rae ho aj'a dhèu j'ara mamuri Ama Lamatua sèra, lèpa hari mai, ka ra pakaboko hari dènge Ne. Ra lolo dènge Yesus ngaa dhu rèngu tao dènge aj'a mi dhèu.<bt>On another day/time, the followers of Yesus whom He had sent out to the villages, teaching the Word of God, had returned home, and they gathered together with Yesus. They told Yesus what they had done and taught to the people with whom they had met.</bt><v n="31" />Lod'o èèna, dhèu ae mai patangi-tenge Yesus. Lula dhèu ae seli eele, ka Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na abhu boe tebho ra'a-rinu hèi. Nèti èèna ka, Yesus ale dènge ana madhutu sèra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Be'a risi èdhi pakèd'i nèti era ne'e lati tenge era èci dhu mau, sèna ka èdhi ae tara ciki.&gt;&gt;<bt>That day, many people came looking for Yesus. There were so many people that Yesus and His followers had no time even for eating-drinking. Because of that, Yesus told those followers (coll), speaking like this, "It's best if we(inc) leave from this place and go look for a quiet place so that we can rest a little bit."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakaboko = berkumpul = pa'oru; 31:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pakaboko = berkumpul = pa'oru; 31: ae tare iisi ciki = istirahat sedikit ; abhu boe tebho = sonde ada tempo; èdhi ae tara ciki = kita berihenti istirahat sedikit; ka'uu = speak so as to deliver slowly</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ka ra ca'e koha cue lasi asa era dhu mau, kaj'èu nèti d'ara rae.<bt>So, they got.up into a boat and went to a quiet place far from the village.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaj'èu = jauh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kaj'èu = jauh</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Te ngaa dhèu ae ètu sèra sa, ladhe rèdhi koha rèngu kako re sebhe dano. Hèia ra kalua nèti rae ka kako pamèri madhutu re dedha rai. Nèti èèna ka, rèngu d'ai uuru Yesus si.<bt>But many of those people saw their boat going right along the edge of that lake. So they walked quickly following on land. Because of that, they arrived first.</bt><v n="34" />Ropa Yesus puru nèti dedha koha, ladhe laa, na, dhèu ae dhu mate Ne. Dhèu se'e re'a heka tao iisi ra tasamia. Nèti èèna ka, d'ara Yesus sue si, te rèngu sama sèmi kahib'i-kalèbho dhu dènge boe ana madhenga. Èle èèna ka, Na aj'a si j'ara mamuri Ama Lamatua.<bt>When Yesus got.down from the boat, He saw all those people who were waiting for Him. These people no longer knew what to do with themselves. Because of that, Yesus' insides loved/pitied them, cause they were like *flocks (idiom--goat-sheep) who were without a shepherd (lit. follower, in context of flocks means 'shepherd'). After that, He taught them lots from/about the Word of God.</bt><note reference="6:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sensus 27:17, 1 Dhèu Aae sèra 22:17, 2 Sejara nèti Isra'el dènge Yahuda 18:16, Yeskial 34:5, Sakaria 10:2, Mateos 9:36</note><v n="35-36" />Na aj'a nèti loo nètu, toke d'ai nihia la'e. Hèia ana madhutu Na sèra mai padhue dènge Ne, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Hua iia Ama ku pua si lasi hèli nganga'a ètu rae dhu dètu ètu era se'e. Te oe mèda kèna, aa ètu era ne'e nganga'a aad'o.&gt;&gt;<bt>He taught them from midday until late afternoon. So those followers came to discuss with Yesus, saying, "Father! It's best if Father orders them to leave and buy food from the villages near this place, cause it's approaching night, and there's no food at this place."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ara b'ab'a = jalan pendek ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">j'ara b'ab'a = jalan pendek ; j'ara ète = jalan potong; 34: kahibi-kalèbho = domba; rasa kasia ; ana madhutu = in context of sheep and goats means shepherd (ex of lexiclalisation.) ; Dhèu se'e re'a heka tao iisi ra tasamia.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Te ngaa Yesus b'ala lii rèngu, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Baku tao sèmi èèna! Hud'i laa, pe miu panga'a si.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus responded to their suggestion, saying, "Don't do like that! It is necessary that [pe] you(PL) feed them."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèia ra karèi hari Ne, &lt;&lt;Ira, ee! Ladhe èdhi panga'a dhèu ae sèmi ne'e, èdhi kalua doi ae bia, nga. Sama sèmi gaji tuka ca tèu kateme, nga!<bt>So then those followers asked Him again, "Ira, ee! If we(inc) could feed this many people, we would have to put.out a huge amount of money. Like the wages of a tradesman (tukang) for one whole year!</bt><note reference="6:37" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Madhutu sasuri lii Yunani, &lt;&lt;dua ngasu doi <span class="Italic">dinari</span> pudhi&gt;&gt;. Lod'o Yesus mamuri èèna, gaji tuka ca lod'o, ca <span class="Italic">dinari.</span><bt>Following the writing in the Yunani (=Greek) language, "200 silver <span class="Italic">dinari</span> money". When Yesus was living, the wages (loan) of a tradesman for one day, was one <span class="Italic">dinari</span>.</bt></note>Aa èdhi tare doi sèra, nèti mia hua kèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>And we would get that money, from possibly where!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nga = 1peGEN; hua = semua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">nga = 1peGEN; hua = semua ; doi ètu ngaa hua ne.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Miu lami karèi sèku dhèu sèra, teko cee dhu nèti nganga'a mèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered speaking like this, "You(PL) go [and] try to ask those people, maybe someone has brought food probably."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèra ~ mèro = barangkali"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mèra ~ mèro = barangkali</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèia ra lasi karèi, ka mai peka dènge Ne, &lt;&lt;Abhu dhoka roti lèmi bua, dènge i'a dua ngi'u di.&gt;&gt;<bt>So those followers went [and] asked, and came [and] said to Him, "[We] only just found/got five fruit of bread and two bodies of fish."</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00155C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Hèia Yesus pua dhèu aa'i-aa'i sèra ho madhèdi cakaboko-cakaboko ètu dedha j'u'u.<bt>So Yesus told those many people to sit in separate.groups there on the open field.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cakaboko-cakaboko = in individual/separate groups; cakaboko-boko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">cakaboko-cakaboko = in individual/separate groups; cakaboko-boko = in groups ; pad'a = padang, tanah lapang; Yesus ~ Jesu (like Lasarus &gt; Saru, no final s)</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Dhèu se'e madhèdi sèmi dhu Yesus pua. Abhu kaboko dhu dhèu cangasu-cangasu, aa abhu kaboko dhu dhèu lèmi nguru-lèmi nguru.<bt>Those people sat as Yesus had told them. There were groups having 100 people in each, and there were groups having 50 people in each.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Hèia Yesus nare roti lèmi bua dènge i'a dua ngi'u sèra, ka na ladhe asa dedha. Na manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua. Èle èèna ka, nare roti lèmi bua, ka Na ku'u pamae ca'èta-'èta. Hèia Na hia mi ana madhutu Na, ho lasi papala hia dhèu dhu madhèdi sèra. Na pala-bagi i'a dua ngi'u sèra kahèi.<bt>So then Yesus took the fie fruit of bread and the two bodies of fish and looked upwards, and He requested *thanks [appropriate collocation] to God. After that, he took the five fruit of bread and the two bodies of fish, and He broke.off-broke in pieces. And He gave to those followers, to go divide.up to those people who were sitting (coll).</bt><v n="42" />Ka dhèu sèra ra'a toke bècu.<bt>And those people ate until satiated.</bt><v n="43" />Ra'a èle, hèia ana madhutu Na sèra lasi pakaboko nganga'a dhu risi eele sèra, pènu canguru dua soe.<bt>When they had finished eating, the followers went [and] gathered the food that was extra, 12 baskets.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="; 41: makasi = terima kasih;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">; 41: makasi = terima kasih; ku'u = cubit dgn kuku ; ca'èta-ca'èta = in pieces; ku'u cakadhèli-dhèli;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Dhèu dhu ra'a sèra, dhèu mone di, lèmi riho dhèu, ige mèka bhèni dènge ana iiki.<bt>Those people who ate there, just 5,000 men, not.yet counting the women and children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana niki = children of all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ana niki = children of all ages (investigate, kuno)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus kako ètu dedha èi<bt>Yesus walks on the water</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:22-33; Yohanis 6:16-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Èle ka, Yesus pua ana madhutu sèra pakèd'i uuru dènge koha asa rae Betsaida ètu cabèka dano. Te Nèngu dhae la'e mèka, ho Na pua dhèu ae sèra lèpa.<bt>After that Yesus ordered those followers to leave first by boat [and] go to the village of Betsaida on the other side of the lake. Cause He wasn't ready to go yet, so He told the aforementioned large number of people to go.home.</bt><v n="46" />Ropa dhèu sèra lèpa, Na la'e asa ledhe èci ètu èèna, ho Na manèngi-mangaj'i.<bt>When those people had left.for.home, He went up on top of a mountain/hill in that place, and he *prayed/worshipped.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47-50" />Lod'o mèda le, ka Yesus puru mai. Na ladhe nèdhi ana madhutu Na sèra dènge koha lasi d'ai talora dano le. Lula ngèlu madha mèdhu ae, ka ra tuku koha d'ai madhe. D'ara oe mèu sa, Yesus heka la'e madhutu si kèna. Te ngaa Na kako re dedha èi. Ropa Na kako oe seli koha ra, ana madhutu sèra ladhe rèdhi Ne, ka ra madha'u titu kèna. Hèia èci karèi èci, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Irii! Ngaa nèi? Nidhu, do?&gt;&gt;<bt>When it was almost night, Yesus descended again coming. He saw the followers were in a boat already out in the middle of the lake. Because the wind was coming from the front, they were half dead (idiom) paddling the boat. When it was almost light, Yesus left to follow them. But He walked on top of the water.And when He walked almost passing by them, the followers saw Him and they were terrified. Then they asked each other, saying, "Irii! What's that? An evil.spirit/spirit of a dead person, right?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="marango = magrib, hari menjelang malam;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">marango = magrib, hari menjelang malam; ngèlu sala = headwind;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèia Yesus lii dènge si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;We! Miu baku madha'u! Te Ja'a ne!&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yesus spoke to them, saying, "We! You(PL) shouldn't be afraid! Cause it's Me here!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Ropa Yesus ca'e la'e asa dedha koha, kabèdhi laa, ngèlu mau dènge. Ana madhutu Na sèra malaa bia.<bt>When Yesus got up into the boat, suddenly the wind became calm. Those followers of His were really amazed/confused.</bt><v n="52" />Rèngu heka rèdhi kèna, Yesus pake koasa Na, lod'o panga'a lèmi riho dhèu èèna. Te ngaa rèngu re'a iia boe koasa Yesus, lula d'ara rèngu adhu sèmi hadhu.<bt>They had just seen Yesus use His power when he fed those 5,000 people. But they didn't undertand well that power of Yesus, because their insides were hard like rocks.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu-dhèu pèd'a ètu Genesaret lasi rame-rame asa Yesus<bt>Sick people in Genesaret come boisterously to Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:34-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Ropa rèngu d'ai cabèka dano, ra panahu koha ètu dae Genesaret.<bt>When they reached the other side of the lake, they harboured the boat at the village of Genesaret.</bt><v n="54" />Ropa ra puru nèti dedha koha, dhèu ae ladhe rèdhi si. Ka ra rodhe lème, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ee! Yesus mai le!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they descended from the boat, lots of people were waiting for them there. They called.out all.around, saying, "Ee! Yesus has come!"</bt><v n="55-56" />Dhèu sèra aa'i-aa'i ra lasi peka palème rae, nèti èèna ka, dhèu mai nèti mia-mia, jèru rèti a'ari rèngu dhu pèd'a asa Yesus.<bt>All the people there went and told in the surrounding villages, and so (as a result of that), people came from everywhere, pole.carrying their kin who were sick [and] placing them in front of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="panahu = berlabuh (perahu)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">panahu = berlabuh (perahu)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sad'i ra tadèngi Yesus ètu era èci, na, rame-rame nedhe rèti dhèu pèd'a mai. Ra paj'unu si ètu d'ara tana lapa ètu èèna. Te ra pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Sad'i dhèu pèd'a sèra goi lèke sebhe kodho Yesus di, èle dènge nèti papèd'a ra.&gt;&gt; Ka dhèu goi lèke kodho Na, hèia èle nèti papèd'a ra.<bt>So when they heard that Yesus was in a place, they got.busy [+festive] [and] picked.up the sick people [and] brought them, and laid them in a wide.open place there. Cause they thought, "As long as these sick people can touch the edge of His clothes, they will be healed from their sickness." Because of that, they requested Yesus allow them to touch the edge of His clothes. Yesus accepted their request, and the people who touched, were all healed of their sickness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mamoo = padang rumput goi ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mamoo = padang rumput goi = sentuh sad'i = asal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Atora dhèu rai-haha baku pa'ele dad'èi Ama Lamatua<bt>Don't let the regulations (assimilated loan) of humans erase/cancel.out the will of God</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="naneo = dadèi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">naneo = dadèi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:1-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Ca lod'o, dhèu partei agama Parisi canau dènge mese-mese agama mai nèti kota Yerusalem neo paraga dènge Yesus.<bt>A group of people from the Parisi religious party and teachers of religion came from the city of Yerusalem wanting to meet with Yesus.</bt><v n="2-5" />Dhèu Parisi kèpe pa'èra ad'a Yahudi. Nuka sèmi, dhèu neo ra'a-rinu hud'i j'amo uuru ku kacui-aai madhutu atora ad'a. Sèmi èèna kahèi, ladhe lèpa nèti d'ara pasa, hud'i diu uuru ku èi. Toke mèdha dapu rèngu sèmi èru-pangala, pega, curu, galaa, cere, hud'i rase uuru ku madhutu atora ad'a, heka bisa pake ra'a-rinu kèna.<bt>These Parisi people strictly followed Jahudi customary.law. So, when people wanted to eat-drink, they must first wash their hand according to customary.law. In the same way, when they returned.home from the market, they had to bathe first with water. Regarding kitchen things, like plates, spoons, glasses, pitchers, they must wash first, only.then could they use them for eating-drinking.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ad'a ~ada ?? ; hudi ~hud'i;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ad'a ~ada ?? ; hudi ~hud'i; èru-pangala = cooking implements ; èru = pariuk, pots ; pangala = kitchen spoons, dippers</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ladhe dhèu Yahudi cahag'e madhutu boe ad'a rèngu sèmi èèna, dhèu Parisi nasa.<bt>If/when there were some Jahudi people who didn't follow customary.law in this way, those Parisi people would get angry.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Nèti èèna ka, ra nasa ropa rèdhi ana madhutu Yesus sèra ra'a-rinu j'amo boe kacui-aai madhutu atora ad'a rèngu. Ka rèngu mai pasala Yesus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka ana madhutu èu se ra'a-rinu j'amo uuru boe kacui-aai? Sèra sa, pasala dènge ad'a nèti bèi-baki èdhi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, they became angry when they saw the followers of Yesus eating-drinking without washing their hands according to their customary.law. So they came [and] accused Yesus, saying, "Why do your followers eat-drink without first washing their hands? They are breaking/violating *customary.law brought to us(inc) by our *ancestors!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'amo kacui ai = cuci tangan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">j'amo kacui ai = cuci tangan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6-7" />Te ngaa Yesus dhaa, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu se mema padhai lii leo, tao leo! Nèti uru nèka mai Yesaya suri tèke le, lii padhai lii Ama Lamatua sèmi ne'e,<bt>So then Yesus answered saying like this, "You(PL) here, what you say is really not the same as what you do! From long ago Grandpa Yesaya has written the Word2 of God like this,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Abhu dhèu dhu koa-kio kolongara Ja'a,<bt>'There are people who *praise My name/character/reputation,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koa-kio = puji"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">koa-kio = puji</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dhoka dènge hèb'a di, te ngaa nèti boe d'ara.<bt>only just with their mouth, but not with their *insides.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tatao rèngu sèmi èèna na, lèke boe.<bt>Their deeds/behaviour is like that, but it's in vain/for naught.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Rèngu pusi-pahae boe dad'èi Ja'a,<bt>They don't care about My will,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te ngaa rèngu madhutu dhoka atora dhèu rai-haha di.&gt;<bt>but they just follow only the regulations of humans.'</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Miu èci èèna kahèi.<bt>You(PL) are like that also.</bt><note reference="7:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 29:13</note><v n="8-9" />Miu tèke eele le paredha Ama Lamatua, ho madhutu atora dhèu rai-haha. Tatao miu ne, d'èlu-mèu bia!<bt>You have set.aside/left.behind the will of God, to follow the regulations of humans. These deeds of yours are really something! [+irony, cynical]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dèlu = hati, pikiran, rongga (trunk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dèlu = hati, pikiran, rongga (trunk of body); last sentence cynical, irony.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sèmi èèna miu d'èlu-mèu bia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sèmi èèna miu d'èlu-mèu bia</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Karèi nèti uuru èèna, Musa peka le lii paredha Ama Lamatua sèmi ne'e ka, &lt;Pakab'ua ina-ama miu.&gt; Aa tabha hari, peka na, &lt;Ladhe ana èci padhèda ama na, do ina na, hud'i ra huku pamadhe ne.&gt;<bt>A long time ago, Grandpa Musa told the command of God like this, 'Humble yourself [=honour] towards your(PL) mother-father.' And added another, saying, 'If a child curses his father, or his mother, they must punish by killing.' [they here can be referential = parents, or non-referential = people, in general]</bt><note reference="7:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 20:12, 21:17, Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 20:9, Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 5:16</note><v n="11-12" />Ama Lamatua aj'a sèmi èèna, te ngaa miu aj'a leo. Miu peka na, &lt;Ladhe dhèu èci pamoa le neo hia ngaa èci mi Ama Lamatua, masi ka ina dènge ama na j'èra oe madhe èèna ka, te ngaa pake boe mèdha èèna ho soru-bara si, lula nèngu moa le neo hia mi Lamatua.&gt;<bt>That's what God teaches, but you(PL) teach different. You say, 'If a person has already made a promise, wanting to give something to God, even.though his mother and father are in difficulty near dying [hyperbole], but he doesn't care to give them that thing, because he has made his promise, he wants to give it to God2.'</bt><v n="13" />Nèti èèna ka, deo na Ja'a peka le, miu pake heka dad'èi Ama Lamatua, te ngaa miu gati eele dènge atora miu dhu hiu. Atora ae le dhu miu gati eele sèmi èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, that's why I just said you no.longer use the will of God, but you have replaced it with your new regulations. There are many commands of God that you have replaced in that way."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Ladhe dhèu ci j'aj'i, neo hia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">"Ladhe dhèu ci j'aj'i, neo hia ngaa èci hia Lamatua, biar ina dènge ama na j'èra oe madhe na ka, ma bisa boe mèdha deo na hia mi ina dènge ama na, taga nèti nèngu j'aj'i le, neo hia Lamatua na.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padhède = maki ( kata makian);"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">padhède = maki ( kata makian); huku = beri hukuman ; karai = from before ;; 12: moa = j'aj'i; Dative raising !!@@; UNS's made direct application w/churces on Ndao! ; masi ka (not archaic!!@@)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">J'ara-j'ara dhu kaj'alu mai nèti d'ara dhèu<bt>Dirty/unclean/impure things which come from inside people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:10-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Hèia Yesus paroa hari dhèu leo ètu sèra, ka Na peka na, &lt;&lt;Pasa dhilu ho nanene paie, sèna ka miu me'a.<bt>So then Yesus again summoned the crowds, and He spoke to them like this, "Fasten on your ears so you can listen well and then you can know/understand.</bt><v n="15" />Ngaa dhu maso asa d'ara d'èlu, pakaj'alu boe. Te ngaa dhu kalua mai nèti d'ara, èèna ka dhu pakaj'alu dhèu.<bt>That which enters into the stomach, does not cause impurity, but what come.out from inside, after that, is what makes a person impure/unclean.</bt><v n="16" />[Cee dènge ro'a dhilu, na, nanene.&gt;&gt;]<bt>Whoever has holes in their ears, listen."</bt><note reference="7:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara sasuri lii Yunani asli dhu uru-uru tèka, suri boe ayat ne.<bt>In the oldest writings of Markus in the Yunani (=Greek) language, this verse (loan) is not written.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na tèke eele dhèu sèra, ka lasi asa d'ara èmu èci. Ka ana madhutu sèra karèi sasoa nèti lii pakasame deo na.<bt>After that, Yesus with His followers left behind those people and went into a house. And those followers asked the meaning of the recent illustration.</bt><v n="18-19" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Miu me'a boe kahèi? Sasoa na sèmi ne'e ka: ngaa dhu dhèu ra'a, èèna be'a. Te ngaa dhu kalua mai, karehe. Èèna be'a boe. Ngaa dhu èdhi ta'a, maso asa d'ara d'èlu, ho èèna na kalua hari asa li'u la'e. (Lii Yesus èèna neo peka mi èdhi, nganga'a aa'i-aa'i, èci sa dhu luri boe).<bt>And Yesus aanswered like this, "You(PL) also don't understand? Its meaning is like this: that which a person eats, it is good; but that which comes back out is bad/evil. That, is not good. That which we(inc) eat, goes into our stomachs, and then it comes back out again to the outside. (What Yesus was saying to us is that all food, there isn't one which is forbidden/taboo).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="upama = perumpamaan; 18: sa li'u"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">upama = perumpamaan; 18: sa li'u = outside; 19: po'e eele = berak, shit</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ngaa dhu mai nèti d'ara, èèna ka dhu pa'ele iie dhèu, nèti èèna ka, Ama Lamatua d'èi boe pa'èci dènge ne.<bt>That which comes from the inside/heart, it is that which destroys a person, [and] because of that, God doesn't want to join with him (=avoids him).</bt><v n="21" />Te j'ara bhelu-katub'a ae ka dhu kalua nèti d'ara dhèu! Nuka sèmi: ngangee karehe, tao j'ara makae dènge dhèu dhu dhèu èmu boe nèngu, mana'u, pamadhe dhèu,<bt>That which comes from the inside/heart, are things like: evil thoughts, causing.evil to the daughter of a person (implies rape), unmarried males and females doing the way of evil, stealing, killing a person,</bt><v n="22" />gagoo-gagehu, bersina, bhelu-katub'a, leko-monya, dhèu dhu taha nare boe d'ara, d'èi boe dhèu risi nèngu, padhai lii pamanahu dhèu, padedha iisi, tatao dhu lèke boe, dènge kètu hadhu.<bt>being greedy, destroying inside the house/home of a person [euphamism for adultery], all sorts of heavy-duty evil, tricking-deceiving [doublet], a person who doesn't know how to restrain his insides, not wanting another person to be better, speaking to bring.down someone, bragging/arrogance, doing inappropriate things, and being stubborn (idiom--rock headed).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakarehe = bekin buruk, jelek; kolongara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pakarehe = bekin buruk, jelek; kolongara = reputasi; pa'ele-iie dhèu = bekin rusak; ro'o boe pa'èci = sonde mau satu (bergaul); 21: mana'u pagogo-pagero = mencuri (see, open, touch, take); adat favours the woman in ; ana mone-ana bhèni tao j'ara karehe (ho pamakae ina-ama), pakarehe ana bhèni dhèu; 22: gagoo-gagehu = rakus; gagu = ganggu ; pa'ele-iie dara èmu dhèu = adultery (euphamistic), berzina; kajeo = nakal; bhelu-katuba = jahat; omo koso = omong kosong; tèka dara = simpan hati (marah yg terpendam), jealous (jeluus = cemburu); padhai li pamanahu = omong kasi jato orang; padhai li pamakae = omong bekin malu orang; pamone = orang ll yg sombong; pabhèni = per yg sombong; padedha iisi = angka diri, sombong (gender neutral); tatao lèke boe j'ara = kura a'ja</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />J'ara karehe aa'i-aa'i sèra mai nèti d'ara dhèu. Sèra ka dhu pa'ele iie dhèu. Ama Lamatua d'èi boe dènge dhèu sèmi èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>All of those evil ways are what come out of a person's insides. Those are the things which destroy a person. God does not want to be with a person like that."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus soru-bara bhèni èci dhu dhèu Yahudi boe<bt>Yesus helps (idiom does hand-mouth) a woman who is not a Jahudi person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:21-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Èle ka, Yesus tèke eele era èèna, ka la'e asa kota èci, ngara na Tirus. D'ai nèi, lasi asa d'ara èmu èci, lula Yesus d'èi boe dhèu re'a Nèngu ètu èèna. Te ngaa Nèngu bisa boe pahuni ngi'u.<bt>After that, Yesus left that place behind, and went to a city named Tirus. Arrising there they went into a house, because Yesus didn't want people to know He was there. But He couldn't hide himself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rèhu = rupa; pad'elo = kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">rèhu = rupa; pad'elo = kasi tunjuk</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-11-22 02:36:22Z">tao ai-hèb'a 1) help (pos); 2) beat up (neg)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Ètu èèna, abhu dhèu bhèni dintiu èci dhu nèti rai Finisia ètu propensi Siria. Ropa na tadèngi Yesus ètu èèna, na mai manèngi Yesus babège eele nidhu nèti ana bhèni na.<bt>A *kafir/pagan woman from the region of Finisia in the province of Siria lived in that place. When she heard that Yesus was there, she came and requested Yesus to evict and evil.spirit from her daughter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Dogs&quot; implicit to make the word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">"Dogs" implicit to make the word play make sense.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Te ngaa Yesus core lii èci, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ana-ana hud'i ra'a uuru ku, ho sisa na, ra core hia busa kèna.&gt;&gt; [Dènge lii pacele èèna, Yesus hud'i soru-bara uuru ku dhèu Yahudi Nèngu, heka dhèu leo kèna.]<bt>But Yesus tossed out a riddle, saying, "Children must eat first, and then the leftovers can be thrown to the dog." (With that indirect.speech, Yesus must first take care of the Jahudi people, only.then do other people).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Te ngaa bhèni èèna b'ala, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Mema tare'a Ama. Te ngaa busa mate le ètu ro'a mei. Nèngu abhu kahèi nganga'a dhu bèbhe nèti d'ara pega ana iiki sèra.&gt;&gt; [Madhutu bhèni èèna, lod'o ana ra'a, na, busa na'a kahèi. Masi ka Yesus soru-bara dhèu unu Na, te ngaa Nèngu hud'i soru-bara dhèu leo kahèi.]<bt>But that woman responded to Yesus' words, saying, "Yes, that's true, Father. But the dog is already waiting under the table. He also gets the food which the children are eating, and scatters off from on top of the table." (According to that woman, if/when the children were eating, even the dogs could also eat. It is true that Yesus must see.after His children, but [he] must also not forget the other people.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aa dan oo = for initial"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">aa dan oo = for initial onset, not long V; consistent with double V written for onset; sa ra'a ka ; paceb'a eele = tercecer</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ropa Yesus tadèngi lii dhaa bhèni ne, hèia Na peka, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Tare'a! Lii padhai lii èu èèna, mola-mola na kèna! Lèpa ka! Te nidhu rai le nèti ana èu.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus heard the answer of this woman, then Yesus said, saying, "True! What you have said is spot on (lit. straight-straight)! Go on home! Cause the evil.spirit has run.off leaving your child."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mola-mola = lurus-lurus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mola-mola = lurus-lurus</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Hèia bhèni ne la'e ka. Na d'ai èmu, ana na dhu bhèj'i luu. Nidhu kalua le.<bt>So then the woman left. She arrived at her house, and her child was sleeping soundly. The evil.spirit had already left.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle dhèu èci dhu lii aad'o aa katele-katipa<bt>Lord Yesus heals a person who has no voice and is deaf [doublet]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katele-katipa = tuli = kacango-ailasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">katele-katipa = tuli = kacango-ailasa</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus si pakèd'i nèti kota Tirus, kako lasi madhutu nebhe dhasi re kota Sidon. Nèti era èèna, rèngu lasi taruu d'ai dano Galilea. Hèia ra lasi asa rai èci dhu dènge canguru kota, dhu ra biasa pangare na, &lt;Dekapolis&gt;.<bt>After that, Yesus left the city of Tirus walking along the shore of the ocean to the city of Sidon. From that place, they continued on until they reached lake Galilea. Then they went to a region which had ten cities, which they normally called 'Dekapolis'.</bt><v n="32" />Ètu èèna, abhu dhèu èci dhu lii aad'o aa katele-katipa. Angalai na lere rèti ne asa Yesus. Ra manèngi sèna ka Yesus tao ai mi kètu na, sèna ka na èle.<bt>There they encountered a person who had no voice and was deaf. His friends escorted him to Yesus. They requested that Yesus place hands on his head to heal him.</bt><v n="33" />Hèia Yesus tèke eele dhèu ae sèra, ka la'e mesa Na dènge dhèu èèna. Yesus pamaso kacui-aai Na asa ro'a dhilu dhèu eèna dua-dua. Èle èèna ka, Na tao ilu ètu kacui-aai Na, ka Na g'ag'e he'o dhèu ne'e.<bt>So then Yesus left behind those many people, and went alone He with this aforementioned person. Yesus put in His hand/finger into both ear holes. After that He put salive on His hand/finger, and He touched the tongue of this person.</bt><v n="34" />Hèia Yesus ladhe asa dedha, Na ère a'ae madhera, ka Na paredha, aku Nèngu na, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Efata.&gt;&gt;</span> (Sasoa na, &lt;&lt;Bhoke ka!&gt;&gt;)<bt>Then Yesus looked upwards, He drew a long breath, and He commanded, saying, "<span class="Italic">Efata.</span>" (Its meaning is "Open up!")</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ère a'ae pamadhera = kecewa, (get"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ère a'ae pamadhera = kecewa, (get rid of pa-)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Na peka dhoka sèmi èèna di, kabèdhi laa, dhilu dhèu èèna tadèngi dènge. Sèmi èèna kahèi, he'o dhu sakaa èèna, mako ka na padhai lii dènge.<bt>He spoke only just like that, and suddenly the ears of the aforementioned person could hear. In the same way also the tongue which had been stiff, became soft and he could speak.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Èle èèna ka, dua ra lasi asa era dhèu ae sèra. Ka Yesus kai si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Nanene, ee! Baku lolo dènge dhèu, peka na, Ja'a ka dhu pa'èle dhèu ne'e ne.&gt;&gt; Masi ka Na kai si, te ngaa dhèu se'e lasi lolo palème d'ai mia-mia.<bt>After that, the two of them went back to the place where all the people were. And Yesus forbade those people saying, "Be careful [not] to tell people saying that I have healed this person here." [CHECK neg polarity of this sentence.] Even though He forbade, but those people went all over the place telling everywhere.</bt><v n="37" />Dhèu-dhèu dhu tadèngi lii lolo èèna, malaa bia. Ra papeka isi-aanga ra, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu ne'e, dhèu di, nga! Nèngu tao pabe'a aa'i mèu-mèu. Dhèu katele bisa tadèngi, aa dhèu lii aad'o bisa padhai lii.&gt;&gt;<bt>People who heard that story, were really amazed. They kept saying to their friends/companions, saying, "This person, is really something. This Person can make all things good. Deaf people can hear, and people without voice can speak."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhilu = telinga; ana dhilu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhilu = telinga; ana dhilu = anak telinga, inside ear</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus panga'a èpa riho dhèu<bt>Lord Yesus feeds 4,000 people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:32-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1-3" />Ca lod'o hari, dhèu ae mai kamue rare Yesus neo nanene lii holo-nori Na. Dhèu sèra tèlu lod'o kèna ètu era èèna dènge Yesus. Nèti èèna ka, gee ra èle aa'i le. Hèia Yesus paroa ana madhutu Na, ka Na peka, &lt;&lt;Ja'a rasa kasia dènge dhèu ae se'e. Cahag'e mai nèti rae kaj'èu, ètu era ne'e d'ai tèlu lod'o kèna, ka nganga'a rèngu aad'o heka ciki sa. Baku hia ra lèpa dènge kabake manganga. Mage dhoka ra mad'ea ho bèbha ètu j'ara.&gt;&gt;<bt>Another time, a huge number of people came [and] surrounded Yesus wanting to listen to His teaching. Those people had been three days in that place with Yesus. Because of that their trail.food was all gone. So Yesus summoned His followers, and He said like this, "I feel pity for these many people. Some came from far away villages, and they don't even have a little bit of food left. They shouldn't go home with empty bellies, lest they become dizzy and fall on the way."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kamue = kelilingi; ciki = sedikit,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kamue = kelilingi; ciki = sedikit, sisa; mad'ea ~ madea = pingsan; Tu dai èna ka (kuno) = nèti èna ka (current) = oleh karena itu; madea-magaga = ; gee = bakal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ka ana madhutu Yesus sèra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama. Era ne kaj'èu nèti rae. Èdhi panga'a tare boe dhèu ae sèmi ne'e!&gt;&gt;<bt>And the followers of Yesus (coll) answered saying, "father, this place is far from a village. We (inc) could not possibly feed this many people!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Hèia Yesus karèi si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Roti miu pèri bua era?&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus asked them, "Our bread is still how.many fruit?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka ra dhaa peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama. Roti ji'i ate dhoka pidhu bua di.&gt;&gt;<bt>And they answered, saying, "Father. Our bread just has only seven fruit remaining."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ate1 = sisa ate2 = blink"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ate1 = sisa ate2 = blink eyes, kedip mata</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ropa nanene nare, hèia Na pua dhèu ae sèra madhèdi ètu rai. Ka nare roti pidhu bua sèra, hèia Na sabaj'a manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua. Sabaj'a nare, hèia Na pamae roti pidhu bua sèra. Ka Na hia ana madhutu Na papala mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i sèra.<bt>Listening to that, He ordered those many people to sit on the ground. And he took the seven fruit of bread, and He prayed2 requesting thanks to God. After praying, He broke those seven fruit of bread, and He gave those followers to divide up among those many people.</bt><v n="7" />Rèngu dènge i'a pèri ngi'u kahèi. Ka Yesus sabaj'a hari manèngi makasi. Èle èèna ka, Na hia ana madhutu Na papala hari mi dhèu ae sèra.<bt>They also had several bodies of fish. So Yesus prayed2 again requesting thanks. After that, He gave those followers to divide up again among those many people.</bt><v n="8-9" />Dhèu aa'i-aa'i sèra ele boe d'ai èpa riho sa. Ra ra'a toke bècu. Ra'a rare, hèia ana madhutu Yesus pakaboko nganga'a sisa, ka ra ige pidhu soe hahake. Èle èèna ka, Yesus pua dhèu se lèpa.<bt>All those people, were around (lit. not desappear reaching) 4,000. They ate until satiated. When they had finished eating, Yesus followers gathered the leftover food, and they counted seven large.baskets. After that, Yesus told the people to return.home.</bt><v n="10" />Ropa dhèu se lèpa, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na ca'e koha pakèd'i asa rae èci, ngara na Dalmanuta.<bt>When these people went home, Yesus and His followers got into a boat [and] left for a village named Dalmanuta.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sabaj'a = sembahyang; pabagi = bagikan;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sabaj'a = sembahyang; pabagi = bagikan; papala = divide out; <span class="Bold">9:</span> soe hahake = large basket ; hahake = dust that comes up from cleaning ground, matress; <span class="Bold">10:</span> oro-oro = menyusuri, menyusur (pantai)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu Parisi neo pamanahu Yesus, ka ra manèngi tadha<bt>Parisi people want to bring Yesus' down, and they request a sign</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:1-4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Lod'o Yesus si d'ai Dalmanuta, dhèu partei Parisi pèri-pèri mai paraga dènge Yesus. Ra tenge j'ara neo pamanahu Ne. Ra manèngi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama. Pad'elo tadha malaa, sèna ka j'aj'i tadha, peka na, Èu tare'a-re'a abhu koasa nèti Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (coll) arrived in Dalmanuta, several people of the Parisi party came to meet with Yesus. They were looking.for a way to cause Yesus to fall. They requested saying, "Father, show Your power, to be a sign that You here really get power from God."</bt><note reference="8:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:38, Lukas 11:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Hèia Yesus ère a'ae madhera, ka Na dhaa si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe Ja'a madhutu lii padhai lii miu ne, Ja'a manyasa! Nga tao ka miu manèngi tadha malaa? Baku sèmi èèna. Ja'a bisa tao tadha malaa. Te ngaa Ja'a parluu boe pad'elo mi miu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus took a long breath, and He answered them, saying, "If I do according to what you have said here, I feel.regret! Why do you(PL) request an *amazing sign? Don't do that. I can make/do an amazing sign. But I don't need to show you."</bt><note reference="8:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:39, Lukas 11:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Hèia Yesus tèke eele dhèu Parisi sèra, la'e hari asa dedha koha. Ka Na pakèd'i dènge ana madhutu Na sèra asa cabèka dano.<bt>Then Yesus left behind those Parisi people, and went again up in a boat, and He left with His followers (coll) across to the other side of the lake.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pasanèd'e ho mage-mage dènge tatao dhèu Parisi<bt>Yesus reminds/warns to be wary of the teaching of the Parisi people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:5-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ropa Yesus si d'ai talora dano, hèia ana madhutu Na sèra heka sanèd'e kèna, na, rèngu rèti boe nganga'a leo, dhoka roti cue di.<bt>When they arrived at the middle of the lake, the followers of Yesus hadn't remembered, and so they were talking among themselves, that they hadn't brought any food, only just one bread.</bt><v n="15" />Tadèngi ra ale roti, hèia Yesus peka dènge si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu mage-mage ku! Baku lèke pangaru karehe nèti dhèu aae Herodes dènge dhèu Parisi. Pangaru rèngu, sama sèmi ragi dhu dhèu pakihu tao roti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing them discuss bread, Yesus said to them, saying, "You(PL) be careful/wary now! Don't get affected by the bad influence (loan) of king Herodes and the Parisi people. Their influence, is like yeast (loan) which is mixed in making bread."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nganga'a j'ara = bekal dalam perjalanan;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">nganga'a j'ara = bekal dalam perjalanan; mage-mage = hati-hati, awas; <span class="Bold">15:</span> pangaru = pengaruh; ree = madhutu</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ra tadèngi Na padhai lii sèmi èèna, ka ana madhutu sèra malaa. Ka ra papeka isi-aanga si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mone heka nèi, peka ngaa ne? Tao-tao èdhi tèti boe roti, ka Na lii sèmi èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>They heard Him speak like that, and the followers were amazed/confused. And they spoke among themselves, saying, "This [+respected] man, what's he talking about? Perhaps/probably it's because we didn't bring bread, that He spoke like that."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tao-tao = barangkali, jangan-jangan; teko-teko ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Tao-tao = barangkali, jangan-jangan; teko-teko = kira-kira, jangan-jangan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Te ngaa Yesus ne'a lii padhai rèngu. Ka Na peka, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka miu padhue dhoka roti di! Miu me'a mere boe ngaa dhu Ja'a peka na, do? Mema kahadhu miu kateme.<bt>But, Yesus knew what they were discussing. And He said, saying, "Why are you(PL) only discussing bread! You don't really know/understand what I am talking about, right? Your brains are really full (=dull-witted).</bt><v n="18" />Miu mèdhi dènge madha le, te ngaa mo'o boe me'a! Èci èèna ka dènge miu mèdhi mèka. Miu tadèngi dènge ro'a dhilu le, te ngaa mo'o boe nanene. Èci èèna ka dènge miu tadèngi mèka. Miu bhèlu le, do?<bt>You have seen with your eyes, but you don't really understand! It's like you haven't.yet seen. You have heard with your ear holes, but you dont want to listen [with understanding]. It's like you haven't.yet heard. Have you forgotten, or what?</bt><note reference="8:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yermia 5:21, Yeskial 12:2, Markus 4:12</note><v n="19" />Roti lèmi bua dhu Ja'a pamae kore ka hia dhèu lèmi riho sèra ra'a, si? Ca hari ni, miu pakaboko mere roti dhu risi sèra pèri soe?&gt;&gt;<bt>The five fruit of bread which I broke up and gave to the 5,000 to eat. And after you gathered up how many baskets of extra bread?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kahadhu = otak topo = tumpul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kahadhu = otak topo = tumpul</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka ra dhaa, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Canguru dua soe, Ama.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered, saying, "12 baskets, Papa."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ka na karèi hari, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu sanèd'e era lod'o Ja'a pamae kore roti pèri bua sèra, ka hia dhèu èpa riho ra'a sa, do aad'o? Miu pakaboko mere sisa pèri soe hahake?&gt;&gt;<bt>And He asked again saying like this, "Do you still remember when I broke apart those several fruit of bread, and gave it to 4,000 people to eat, or not? You gathered up how many large.baskets of leftovers?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka ra dhaa, na, &lt;&lt;Pidhu, Ama.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered, "Seven, Papa."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Hèia Na peka, na, &lt;&lt;Mema tare'a! Miu mèdhi dènge madha le. Te ngaa, nga tao ka miu me'a mèka koasa Ja'a kapua nèti mia?&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, He said, "That's right! You have seen with your eyes. But how is it that don't you understand My power."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus puri-pa'èle dhèu bèdhu ètu rae Betsaida<bt>Yesus heals a blind person in the village of Betsaida</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ropa Yesus si d'ai rae Betsaida, dhèu rèti dhèu bèdhu èci mai asa Yesus. Ra manèngi sèna ka Yesus pa'èle musi madha dhèu bèdhu ne.<bt>When Yesus (coll) arrived at the village of Betsaida, people brought a blind man in front of Yesus. They requested that Yesus heal the eyeballs of this blind man.</bt><v n="23" />Ka Yesus kadhèi nare kacui-aai dhèu ne, ka dua ra lasi asa li'u rae. Èle èèna ka, Yesus sabhuu ilu mi musi madha dhèu ne, hèia Na g'ag'e. Ka Na karèi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Samia? Èu mèdhi le, do dhae?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus took the hand of the aforementioned person, and the two of them went outside the village. After that, Yesus spit saliva on the eyeballs of this aforementioned person, and He touched [them]. And He said, "How is it? Can you already see, or not.yet?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kadhèi = gandeng, pegang ; dhèi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kadhèi = gandeng, pegang ; dhèi = ta'i, feces; kadai = ijuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ka dhèu èèna padoa kètu, ka na ladhe sa g'ana-kariu, hèia na dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Oo! Ja'a kèdhi dhèu kako rango-rango era, nuka sèmi ana aaj'u dhu kako.&gt;&gt;<bt>And that person lifted [his head] and looked around to the right-left, and he answered saying, "Oo! I can see still in a haze people walking, they are sort of like trees!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rango-rango = samar-samar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">rango-rango = samar-samar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Hèia Yesus caro hari kacui-aai Na ca tèka mi musi madha dhèu ne'e. Ka na ladhe patae hari, ho neo ne'a, na, musi madha na be'a le, do dhae. Ne'e ne, heka nèdhi dènge mèu kèna.<bt>So then Yesus rubbed His fingers/hands once again on the eyeballs of this aforementioned person. And he saw clearly.</bt><v n="26" />Ka Yesus pua na lèpa, te ngaa pasanèd'e ne, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èu lamu ka, te ngaa madhutu j'ara leo. Re ia ka Betsaida.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus told him to return.home, but reminded him, saying, "You go one now, not back to Betsaida, but follow a different path."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="caro = gosok tangan pada wajah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">caro = gosok tangan pada wajah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus mangaku na, Yesus èèna, Kristus<bt>Petrus acknowledges/confesses that Yesus is Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:13-20; Lukas 9:18-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus si kako palème rae-rae ètu Kaisarea Pilipi. Ètu talora j'ara, Yesus karèi ana madhutu Na, peka na, &lt;&lt;Madhutu lii lolo dhèu, na, Ja'a ne, cee?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) walked around to the villages in Kiasaria Filipi. In the middle of the path.journey, Yesus asked His followers, saying, "According to what people are saying, who am I?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ka ra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu cahag'e peka, na, Èu ne, Yohanis tuka sarani dhu madhe le, te ngaa mamuri hari. Abhu cahag'e peka na, Èu ne, Elia, ca dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua uru sèra. Aa abhu cahag'e hari peka na, Ama ne, dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua dhu leo.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered Him, saying, "Some people say that You here are Yohanis the Tukang Baptiser who has died, but is alive again; some people are saying that You, are Grandpa Elia. But/and [te] some others again are saying, that Father (= you) ore one of God's spokemen from before."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhèu padhue-padhai li = UNS, transparent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhèu padhue-padhai li = UNS, transparent meaning, but probably needs teaching to reinforce association with 'prophets/jubir'.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 6:14-15, Lukas 9:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ka Yesus karèi hari rèngu, &lt;&lt;Madhutu a'abhu miu, Ja'a ne, cee?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus asked them again, "In your(PL) opinion/view, who am I?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Petrus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama ne, Kristus, dhu Ama Lamatua paj'uj'u nèti uru ka.&gt;&gt;<bt>Petrus answered Him, saying, "This Father, is Kristus, who God designated from long ago."</bt><note reference="8:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 6:68-69</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Hèia Yesus pasanèd'e si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Baku lolo mi cee-cee kahèi, ee!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then Yesus reminded/warned them, saying, "Beware that you not tell anyone else, ee!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus peka mema j'aj'èra dènge mamadhe Na<bt>Yesus tells about His suffering and death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:21-28; Lukas 9:22-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus mulai peka dènge ana madhutu Na sèra, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a ne, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a. Bèli-camèd'a Ja'a abhu j'aj'èra ae titu kèna, lula dhèu heka-dhèu heka Yahudi, kètu agama Yahudi, dènge mese agama sèra, aa'i-aa'i ra sèmi rare boe Ja'a. Ho èèna na, ra pamadhe Ja'a, te ngaa d'ai camèd'a, na,<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again to His followers, saying, "I here, am the *Child of Humans. In the future, I will encounter/get incredible suffering/difficulty. Cause2 from the all the heads of tribes, the fathers of religion, and the teachers of religion (coll), don't like Me. So therefore, they will kill Me, but on the third day (= day after tomorrow from day of reference), I will get.up/rise again."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apodokimastheenai: be evaluated and found inadequate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">apodokimastheenai: be evaluated and found inadequate and rejected</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara lii Yunani, ra ige mulai nèti: deo ne'e (=1), bèli (=2), camèd'a (=3), camèd'a èci (=4). De lii Yunani τῃ τρίτῃ ἡμέρᾳ <span class="Italic">(tei tritei heimera)</span> &lt;&lt;ètu lod'o ka tèlu&gt;&gt;, sasoa na ètu d'ara lii Dhao, nuka &lt;&lt;camèd'a&gt;&gt;. Sanèd'e, te Lamatua Yesus madhe lèke dènge hari Jumat (ige èci). Bèli èèna, nuka hari Sabtu (ige dua), Lamatua Yesus ètu d'ara ro'a dhèu madhe. Camèd'a, nuka hari Migu (ige tèlu), Lamatua Yesus mamuri hari. De madhutu a'ige lod'o ètu d'ara lii Dhao, na, Nèngu madhe dua mèda di, hèia Na mamuri hari.<bt>In the Yunani language, they begin counting from today (= 1), tomorrow (= 2), day.after.tomorrow (=3), day.after plus 1 (= 4). So (consequently), in the Yunani language, τῃ τρίτῃ ἡμέρᾳ (tei tritei heimera) “on the third day” means in the Kupang language, “the day after (tomorrow, next)”. Remember that, the Lord Yesus died on Friday (count one). Tomorrow/the next day, that is Saturday (count two), the Lord Yesus was in the grave. The day after(tomorrow/next), that is Sunday (count three), the Lord Jesus lived again/came back to life. So (consequently)according to the way that we-inc count days, na, He was dead for two nights, and then He came back to life.</bt></note>Ja'a mamuri hari.&gt;&gt;</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yesus peka boe dènge pahuni, hèia Petrus ère Ne asa karasa na, ka na kai, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama, baku padhai lii sèmi èèna! Ja'a ko'o boe dhèu tao Ama ku sèmi èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus spoke openly (lit. did not speak in secret), so Petrus pulled Him aside, and rebuked/forbade, saying, "Father, don't talk like that! I don't want people to do those things to Father."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="elders = kapala suku"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">elders = kapala suku</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Lii padhai lii Petrus èèna, madhutu boe dad'èi Ama Lamatua. Hèia Yesus kabib'a, ka ladhe asa ana madhutu dhu leo sèra. Ka Na nasa dènge Petrus, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Weh! Èèna lii dhèu aae nidhu! Èu pakaj'èu nèti ne'e! Èu madhutu dhoka dad'èi dhèu rai-haha di. Madhutu boe dad'èi Ama Lamatua!&gt;&gt;<bt>What Petrus said did not follow the will of God. So Yesus looked at the other followers (coll). And He was angry with Petrus, saying, "We! That is the voice of *Satan there! You get.away/far from here! You are only just following the will/desires of humans. [You are] not following the will/desires of God!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaa: Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">Satanaa: Devil</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus paroa dhèu ae sèra ho mai pakaboko dènge ana madhutu Na. Ka Na aj'a si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu neo madhutu Ja'a, hud'i taha taruu bèli-bèli. Nèngu hud'i tèke eele dad'èi na, ho madhutu dad'èi Lamatua di. Masi ka dhèu neo pamadhe ne, te ngaa nèngu hud'i taha taruu kahèi, nuka sèmi dhèu pasae aj'u palolo-palèbha nèngu unu na ho la'e asa era ra pamadhe ne.<bt>After that, Yesus summoned the many people who were there, and gathered His followers. And He taught them saying, "People/the person who follows me must continue to endure through suffering/difficulty. [S/He] must leave behind his/her desires to follow the desires of God2. Death, even that, whatever happens! (= follow God's desires even if it leads to death, but CHECK). In the same way, even if s/he has to carry a burden to the point of death, that is also good.</bt><note reference="8:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:38, Lukas 9:23, 14:27</note><v n="35" />Te dhèu dhu mamuri dhoka lalau ngi'u aae na di, bèli-camèd'a mamuri nèngu ele iie d'ara! Te ngaa dhèu dhu sadia madhe lula madhutu Ja'a, aa lula na peka-padhai j'ara mamuri Ama Lamatua, bèli-camèd'a nèngu abhu mamuri dhu ma'ète boe dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>A person who dies because s/he follows Me, will live continually with God2. But a person who lives only just to take.care.of himself, in the future will lose everything!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERMS: Mt 16:21-28, Lk 9:22-27"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">TERMS: Mt 16:21-28, Lk 9:22-27</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dhèu dhu madhe lula madhutu Ja'a, na mamuri taruu dènge Lamatua. Te ngaa, dhèu dhu mamuri lalau dhoka ngi'u aae na di, bèli-camèd'a sèra sa ele iie aa'i mèu-mèu!"><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-11-22 04:04:44Z" status="Anyone">OV</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:39, Lukas 17:33, Yohanis 12:25</note><v n="36" />Mi nanene, ee! Ladhe èu abhu aa'i isi rai-haha ne, te ngaa Ama Lamatua core eele èu, a'oto na ngaa?<bt>So listen up, ee! Even though [masi ka] you own everything on this earth, but God throws you out, there is no benefit/gain, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="psykhees: this is not eternal life,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">psykhees: this is not eternal life, the life characteristic of the age to come; it's life as a person has it right now</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Masi ka èu bau mèti aa'i kakaja rai-haha ne, te ngaa bisa boe pasilu dènge samanga èu.<bt>Even if you get carry all the wealth on this earth, but you cannot exchange it for your *soul.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Èle èèna ka Yesus paroa dhèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Èle èèna ka Yesus paroa dhèu ae-ae dhu ètu èèna, pakaboko dènge ana madhutu Na. Ka Na aj'a si peka na, "Dhèu dhu neo madhutu Ja'a, hud'i mèke ku babia dènge j'aj'èra, ho madhutu Ja'a bèli-bèli. Nèngu hud'i tèke eele dadèi nèngu, ho madhutu dadèi Lamatua. Madhe, èèna ka o, ngaa-ngaa tao boe! Sama sèmi dui j'aj'èra toke madhe èèna ka o, be'a hei.; <span class="Bold">36:</span> Mi nanene, ee! Dhèu dhu abhu kakaja rai-haha ne'e, aa'i-aa'i ra, te Lamatua sèmi boe dhèu na, na a'oto na aad'o si?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ngee; |b37:|r da'u = carry (a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ngee; <span class="Bold">37:</span> da'u = carry (a little); bau = carry a lot</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antallagma tees psykhees autou: something you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">antallagma tees psykhees autou: something you pay to get back something in exchange (for your life): there is nothing that would compensate you for such a loss.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Sanèd'e paie! Dhèu ètu rai-haha limuri ne, bhelu-katub'a rupa-rupa. Rèngu pusi-pahae boe madhutu Ama Lamatua. De cee dhu makae madhutu Ja'a, do makae madhutu lii holo-nori Ja'a, bèli-camèd'a Ja'a makae kahèi mangaku nèngu ètu madha Ama Lamatua. Te Ja'a, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a ne, bèli-camèd'a mai hari nèti sorga, palere dènge ana pajuu Ama Lamatua sèra. Ji'i puru mai dènge dadedha Ama ku, heka dhèu re'a mèu kèna, Ja'a ne cee.<bt>Remember well (=think and try to understand)! People on this earth recently are incredibly evil. Recently people no longer value about God. People who are ashamed to know2 Me, and are ashamed to tell My teaching/word, in the future, I will also be ashamed, to know2/acknowledge him in front of God. I am the *Child of Humans, and in the future will come again from *heaven (loan), together with *angels (servants of God). When we(exc) descend coming, it will be with the great power of my Father, and so then you will know exactly who I am!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ngèti = 1p-bring ; pahae ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ngèti = 1p-bring ; pahae = menghargai ; palere = sama-sama</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Miu baku bhèlu lii padhai lii Ja'a ne. Abhu nèti miu cahag'e dhu madhe mèka, pe mèdhi Ama Lamatua nèd'u paredha dènge koasa kapai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Watch out lest you forget what I have told you! Some of you(PL) will live until you see God holding power/government with great power."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nèd'u = 3s-hold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">nèd'u = 3s-hold</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ètu ledhe Lamatua Yesus leko-leo, aa mèdha-papake Na pudhi kale'e<bt>The Lord Yesus changes, and also His clothes are clean-white on the top of a mountain</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:1-13; Lukas 9:28-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Èle èna lod'o, hèia Yesus gale nèti Petrus, Yakobis, Yohanis, lasi asa ledhe èci dhu dhèu pea boe. Ropa d'ai ledhe èèna, rèngu ladhe, na, Yesus leko-leo.<bt>After six days, Yesus invited Petrus, Yakobis, Yohanis, to go up on top of a mountain where nobody lived. When they arrived at the top of that mountain, they saw that Yesus had completely changed.</bt><v n="3" />Aa mèdha-papake Na pudhi kale'e. Abhu mèka mèdha dhu pudhi sèmi èèna ètu rai-haha ne.<bt>And His clothes were clean-white. There is nothing else that white on this earth.</bt><v n="4" />Cag'ag'a laa, rèngu rèdhi Yesus padhai lii dènge Elia dènge Musa.<bt>Suddenly they saw Yesus talking with Grandpa Elia and Grandpa Musa there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Ka Petrus si madha'u bia. Hèia Petrus malaa, ka na padhai lii ore leli. Hèia na peka dènge Yesus, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Èdhi ètu era ne'e, be'a titu kèna! Hua iia risi, ji'i tao paleo tèlu bua, cue hia Ama, cue hia Musa, aa cue hari hia Elia.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Petrus mob were terrified. Then they were confused, and Petrus spoke thoughtlessly. And he said to Yesus, "Father! We(inc) are here, that's really good! It would be really good if we(exc) make three lean-to's, one for Father, one for Grandpa Musa, and one other for Grandpa Elia."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ore = sembarang; leli = sembarang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ore = sembarang; leli = sembarang, directionless, aimless;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Nèbhu boe ka, ra'i-liru puru mai sarimu nare si. Hèia ra tadèngi lii èci nèti ra'i-liru èèna, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mi nanene! Yesus ne, Ana pasue Ja'a. Miu nanene paie Ne!&gt;&gt;<bt>After a little bit, a cloud descended and blanketed them. Then they heard a voice from the aforementioned cloud, saying, "You(PL) Listen! This Yesus, is my favoured/beloved Child. You [must] listen well to Him!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sarimu &lt; salimut = envelope, wrap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sarimu &lt; salimut = envelope, wrap (in clouds)</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:2-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Petrus 1:17-18; Mateos 3:17, Markus 1:11, Lukas 3:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ropa tadèngi lii èèna, Petrus si laladhe palème, te ngaa rèdhi heka dhèu leo ètu èèna. Ate dhoka Yesus mesa Na.<bt>When they heard the aforementioned voice, Petrus (coll) looked around, but they didn't see any other people there any more. All that remained was only Yesus by himself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ate = sisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ate = sisa</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na sèra puru nèti ledhe èèna. Ka Yesus kai si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ngaa dhu miu mèdhi deo na, baku lolo dènge dhèu èci sa. Ja'a, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a ne, hud'i madhe uuru ku. Ho lod'o d'ai Ja'a mamuri hari, na, miu heka lolo dènge dhèu leo kèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus and the followers descended from the top of that mountain/hill. Yesus forbade them saying, "What you(PL) have just seen, be careful not to tell a single person. I, the Child of Humans, must die first. When the day/time comes for me to live again, only.then can you tell other people."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Rèngu tèke pa'èra lii moa èèna ètu d'ara ra. Ra ale boe dènge dhèu èci sa. Te ngaa tèlu ra pakarèi isi-aanga, &lt;&lt;Na padhai lii ngaa ne, peka na, &lt;Nèngu mamuri hari nèti mamadhe&gt;? Tasamia, ee?&gt;&gt;<bt>They took that promise to heart (lit. left it firmly in their insides); they didn't tell a single person. The three of them asked their friends, "So, what He just said here, was He saying He's going to live again from death? How is that, ee?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="li moa = janji"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">li moa = janji</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Hèia ra karèi Ne, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mese agama sèra peka na, &lt;Elia hud'i mai uru ku, heka Kristus mai kèna.&gt; Te ngaa madhutu Ama, tare'a, do aad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>So they asked Him, saying, "Teachers of religion (coll) say Grandpa Elia must come first, only.then will Kristus come. But according to Father, is that true, or not?"</bt><note reference="9:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Meliaki 4:5, Mateos 11:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mema tare'a. Elia hud'i mai uuru ku, ho bhoke j'ara hia Kristus, dhèu dhu Ama Lamatua paj'uj'u karèi nèti uru ka. Te ngaa tasamia? Miu me'a mèka ngaa dhu suri rare le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua, lula-nèti Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a? Dhu suri rare le, peka na, ladhe lod'o Na mai, dhèu paj'èra Ne, toke ra pamadhe Ne.<bt>So then Yesus answered saying, "It's really true. Grandpa Elia must come first, to open the way for Kristus, the person who God designated from long ago. But, how about this? Don't you(PL) know any more what they have written inside the Writings of God, about that Child of Humans? That they wrote saying when His day came, people would cause difficulty/suffering for Him, and they kill Him.</bt><v n="13" />Nèti èèna ka, miu pasa paie dhilu miu! Elia mai le. Te ngaa dhèu paj'èra ne madhutu dad'èi rèngu. Èèna lèke dènge ngaa dhu baki-baki èdhi sèra suri tèke le karèi nèti uuru ka.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, you(PL) must fasten your ears well, ee [implies w/goal to understand]! Grandpa Elia has already come. But people caused him difficulty/suffering according to their desires/as they pleased. That fits what our(inc) forefathers (coll) already since wrote long ago."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle ana èci dhu nidhu tao<bt>Lord Yesus heals the sickness of a child that had been affliicted by evil.spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:14-21; Lukas 9:37-43a)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ropa Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na, dhèu tèlu sèra, paraga hari dènge ana madhutu leo sèra, ka ladhe rèdhi dhèu ae pakaboko ètu èèna. Dhèu ae sèra mai ho ra neo nanene ana madhutu Yesus dhu leo sèra pab'ala lii dènge mese agama ètu èèna.<bt>When Yesus and His followers, the three of them, met again with the other followers, they saw many people gathered in that same place. Those many people had come to listen to the other followers debate/discuss with the teachers of religion of that place.</bt><v n="15" />Ropa dhèu ae sèra ladhe rèdhi Yesus, ka ra cag'ag'a, te rèngu neo laa, na, Yesus ètu ledhe era. Hèia ra rai mai soru Ne.<bt>When those many people saw Yesus, they were surprised, cause they thought Yesus was still on top of the mountain. So then they came in front of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pabala = debat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pabala = debat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Hèia Yesus karèi si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Miu pab'ala lii ngaa na?&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus asked them saying, "What are you(PL) debating here?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dhèu èci nèti talora dhèu ae sèra ara sa madha, ka na dhaa, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama, mu nanene ku laa! Ja'a mai kèti ana mone ja'a dhu pèd'a, ho Ama ku puri-pa'èle ne. Nèngu lii aad'o, bisa boe padhai lii, lula nidhu tao ne.<bt>One person from among the many people moved forward in front of [Him], and answered, saying, "Father, listen a second! I came bringing a son of mine here who is sick, so that Father could heal him. He is without voice, and cannot speak, because3 an evil.spirit has afflicted him.</bt><v n="18" />Ladhe nidhu maso asa d'ara ngi'u na, na hake ngi'u ana ne mi rai. Ho hèb'a na horo karaka, na na'e ngutu na kico-kico sèna. Ho ngi'u na patèku sèmi aj'u. Ja'a manèngi le ana madhutu Ama ku babège eele nidhu èèna. Te ngaa ra bisa boe.&gt;&gt;<bt>When the evil.spirit enters his body, he throws.down.forcefully on the ground the body of this child. And his mouth foams, and his teeth make.sound.of.teeth.grinding. His body becomes stiff like wood. I've already requested Father's followers to evict that evil.spirit. But they can't."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hèb'a horo karaka = mulut berbusa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hèb'a horo karaka = mulut berbusa ; kadi ngutu ciru-ciru = bunyi makan gigi; katè'ku = kaku; giso-giso = teeth grinding in anger (makan gigi); kico-kico = sound of teeth grinding; kèru-kèru = sound of eating field corn;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ropa Na nanene nare, hèia Yesus jèke si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Heh! Miu seli-kolane! Ja'a aj'a miu pahari-pahari, te ngaa miu me'a boe ngaa-ngaa. Miu parcaya èra boe mi Ja'a! Ja'a mate miu nèbhu sange mia hari ku? Mèti ana èèna asa ne'e mai!&gt;&gt;<bt>When He finished hearing them, then Yesus spoke.angrily, saying, "He! You(PL) are too much! I teach you every day, but you don't understand anything. As for Me, you don't believe strongly/capably. How long do I need to be patient with you still. Bring that child here now!"</bt><v n="20" />Hèia ra sa'u rèti ana èèna asa madha Yesus. Te ngaa ropa nidhu ladhe nèdhi Yesus, na kalabhe ana ne mi rai, ka ana ne bèbhe kapod'e ètu rai, aa hèb'a na horo karaka.<bt>So they carried that child in front of Yesus. When the evil.spirit saw Yesus, he threw down the aforementioned child on the ground, and that child fell rolling around, and his mouth foamed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kolane = keterlaluan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kolane = keterlaluan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ka Yesus karèi ama na, &lt;&lt;Nèngu sèmi ne'e ne, pèri lod'o kèna?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus asked his father, "He's been like this here, for about how long?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka ama na dhaa, &lt;&lt;Karèi nèti ana iiki ka mai.<bt>And his father answered, "Since he was small onward.</bt><v n="22" />Nidhu èèna nèbhu ae le neo pamadhe ana ne'e. Na tule ne pèri-pèri hari kèna asa d'ara ai, aa na pacène le kahèi asa d'ara èi. De Ama ku sue ja'a. Ladhe bisa, na, Ama puri-pa'èle ku ana ja'a la.&gt;&gt;<bt>That evil.spirit has for a long time wanted to kill this child. He often shoves him into the fire, and he has also tried to drown him in water. So [De] Father please love/pity now. If [you] can, Father heal this child now."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka èu peka na &lt;ladhe bisa&gt;? Ja'a bisa tao aa'i mèu-mèu, te ngaa hud'i èu parcaya uuru ku!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered him, saying, "Why do you say, 'if you can'? I can do anything/everything, but you must believe first!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Nèti èèna ka, mone èèna dhaa dènge oe tangi, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama, mema ja'a parcaya, te ngaa pa'èra hari ku lalèka ja'a ne'e!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, this man answered with tears, saying, "Father, I really believe, but strengthen again this *faith of mine!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ropa Yesus nèdhi dhèu ae mai lingu, ka Na paredha nidhu èèna, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Heh! Nidhu bhelu! Kalua pakaj'èu ka nèti ana ne'e! Sèna ka na bisa tadèngi aa na padhai lii kahèi. Èu baku maso ia ka asa d'ara ana ne'e!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus saw the many people who came around, He commanded that evil.spirit, saying, "He! *Evil evil.spirit! Come out [and] go far from this child! So that he can hear, and he can speak. You may not enter again into this child!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ropa nidhu tadèngi lii Yesus, hèia na pakèce. Ka na hake ana ne mi rai, ka na rèbha-rèbha sène, heka nidhu kalua nèti d'ara ana èèna kèna. Ana èèna kalau heka, nuka sèmi dhu madhe le. Ka dhèu ètu sèra sa peka, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Waa! Ana ne madhe le!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the evil.spirit heard the voice of Yesus (or: what He said), then he screamed. And he threw.down the aforementioned child on the ground shaking/trembling, and that evil.spirit came out from inside that child. That child was motionless for awhile, something like a dead person. And the people there said, saying, "Na! This child is dead!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Te ngaa Yesus kèpe kacui-aai ana ne, ka Na pakèd'i ne. Hèia na kèd'i dènge ka.<bt>But Yesus took.hold of his hand, and He stood him up. And so he stood up right then.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na, tèke eele era èèna, lasi dhuli èmu cue. Ètu èmu èèna, rèngu mesa ra, ka ra karèi Yesus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Nga tao ka ji'i bisa boe babège eele nidhu èèna?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus and His followers left that place behind, and went [and] stopped.in at a house. At that aforementioned house, they were alone, and they asked Yesus, saying, "Father! Why could we not evict that evil.spirit?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Hèia Yesus peka dènge si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Mi nanene paie! Nidhu sèra mema bhelu. De ladhe miu manèngi boe a'èra nèti Lamatua, na, miu bisa boe babège eele nidhu sèmi èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus spoke to them, saying, "Listen well! Those evil.spirits are truly evil. So if you(PL) do not request strength/power from God2, you will not be able to evict evil.spirit who are evil like them."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus peka mamadhe Nèngu ca tèka hari<bt>Yesus speaks about His death once again</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:22-23; Lukas 9:43b-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Èle ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na tèke eele era èèna, lasi taruu asa propensi Galilea. Lod'o èèna, Yesus d'èi boe dhèu re'a Nèngu ètu èèna,<bt>After that, Yesus and His followers left that place behind, and continued on to the province of Galilea. Yesus didn't want people to know He was there,</bt><v n="31" />lula Na neo aj'a ana madhutu Na di. Ka Na lole dènge si, &lt;&lt;Nèbhu heka dhèu pahie eele Ja'a dènge dhèu leo. Hèia ra pamadhe Ja'a, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a ne. Mema Ja'a madhe, te ngaa d'ai camèd'a, Ja'a mamuri hari.&gt;&gt;<bt>because He just wanted to teach His followers. And He told them, "In a short time (lit. not long) a person will sell Me off to other people. And they will kill Me, the Child of Humans. I will really die, but on the third day (= two days after reference day) I will live again."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lodo ka tèlu = hari yg"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">lodo ka tèlu = hari yg ketiga (day after tomorrow); but tèlu lodo = three more days</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara lii Yunani, ra ige mulai nèti: deo ne'e (=1), bèli (=2), camèd'a (=3), camèd'a èci (=4). De lii Yunani τῃ τρίτῃ ἡμέρᾳ (tei tritei heimera) &lt;&lt;ètu lod'o ka tèlu&gt;&gt;, sasoa na ètu d'ara lii Dhao, nuka &lt;&lt;camèd'a&gt;&gt;. Sanèd'e, te Lamatua Yesus madhe lèke dènge hari Jumat (ige èci). Bèli èèna, nuka hari Sabtu (ige dua), Lamatua Yesus ètu d'ara ro'a dhèu madhe. Camèd'a, nuka hari Migu (ige tèlu), Lamatua Yesus mamuri hari. De madhutu a'ige lod'o ètu d'ara lii Dhao, na, Nèngu madhe dua mèda di, hèia Na mamuri hari.</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yesus padhai lii sèmi èèna, te ngaa ana madhutu Na sèra malaa. Rèngu bani heka karèi sasoa lii padhai lii Nèngu.<bt>Yesus spoke like that, and those followers were amazed/confused. They did not have the courage to ask again the meaning of what was just said.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana madhutu Yesus pasisu cee dhu kapai risi<bt>Yesus' followers argue/debate about who is more important</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 18:1-5; Lukas 9:46-48)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus si lasi d'ai Kapernaum. Ropa ra maso asa d'ara èmu èci, Yesus karèi si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Deo na miu pasisu ngaa ètu talora j'ara?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) went on [until they] arrived at Kapernaum. When they went into a house, Yesus asked them, saying, "Just now, what were you)PL) arguing about in the middle of the road/journey?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Èci sa bani boe dhaa, lula ètu talora j'ara deo na, rèngu ako pasala d'ara, nèti ra pasisu, cee ka dhu kapai risi ètu talora rèngu.<bt>Not one of them had the courage to answer, because just recently in the middle of the road/journey they had continued their discussion, debating who was the most/more important among them.</bt><note reference="9:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Hèia Yesus madhèdi, ka Na holo si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Cee dhu neo j'aj'i dhèu kapai, mamuri nèngu hud'i sama sèmi dhèu haha dhu lalau-lalo'o dhèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus sat, and He taught/advised them, saying, "Whoever wants to become an important person, his/her life must be like that of a low-class servant (lit. child who serves people)."</bt><note reference="9:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 20:26-27, 23:11, Markus 10:43-44, Lukas 22:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus sa'u nare ana iiki èci, ka la'e asa talora rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra. Hèia Na peka, aku Nèngu na,<bt>After that, Yesus picked up a small child, and took [it] into the middle of them all, and He said, saying,</bt><v n="37" />&lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu madhutu Ja'a, ho na lalau-lalo'o dhèu sèmi ana iiki ne, èèna sama sèmi nèngu lalau-lalo'o Ja'a kahèi. Aa nèngu lalau-lalo'o Ama ku kahèi, dhu pua Ja'a mai asa rai-haha ne.&gt;&gt;<bt>"The person who follows Me, to pay.attention.to/ see.to.the.needs.of a person like this child here, it is the same as if s/he pay.attention.to Me also. And s/he pay.attention.to [the] Father who sent Me to come here to this earth."</bt><note reference="9:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:40, Lukas 10:16, Yohanis 13:20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Cee dhu lab'a boe èdhi, nèngu dhèu èdhi<bt>Whoever does not oppose us(inc), he is our person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 9:49-50)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Èle èèna ka, ana madhutu Yesus dhu ngara na Yohanis, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ca tèka ji'i ngèdhi ca dhèu pake kolongara Ama ku, ho na babège eele nidhu. Te ngaa ji'i kai ne, lula nèngu dhèu èdhi boe.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus' follower named Yohanis, said, "Father! Once we(exc) saw a person using Father's name2, for him to evict2 evil.spirits. But we forbade him, because he was a different person (=not one of us)!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Te ngaa Yesus dhaa, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Baku mi kai ne! Te dhèu dhu pake kolongara Ja'a, ho na tao tadha malaa, nèngu pa'ele iie boe kolongara Ja'a.<bt>But Yesus answered/responded, saying, "Don't you(PL) forbid him! Cause a person who uses My name, to do amazing signs, s/he is not destroying My name2/reputation.</bt><v n="40" />Ladhe nèngu palab'a boe dènge èdhi, nèngu na dhèu èdhi.<bt>If s/he is not opposing us(inc), s/he is our person.</bt><note reference="9:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:30, Lukas 11:23</note><v n="41" />De mi sanèd'e paie! Ladhe abhu dhèu ne'a, na, miu madhutu Kristus, ka na soru-bara miu, tatu Ama Lamatua bhèlu boe rui-j'aj'èra nèngu. Masi ka dhèu dhu hia miu èi iia ca galaa èèna ka, Ama Lamatua bhèlu boe tatao nèngu èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>So [De] remember well (=aim for understanding)! If there are people who know that you (coll) are a follower of Kristus, and they serve3 (look to your needs), God will not forget their efforts/difficulty. Even.if people who give you even a glass of water, God will not forget that deed of his/hers."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bhèlu = lupa; bhelu = jahat;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">bhèlu = lupa; bhelu = jahat; oo = pun</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:42</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Baku karihu dènge sasala!<bt>Don't play with sin/wrong</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 18:6-9; Lukas 17:1-2)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus padhai lii hari dènge ra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mage-mage, ladhe abhu dhèu dhu tao ana iiki èci kako sala j'ara, toke ana ne parcaya heka Ja'a! Be'a risi hia dhèu èèna, rare hadhu aae cue,<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again to them, saying, "If there is a person who does wrong to one small child, and [result] the aforementioned child no longer believe in Me, it would be best for for that aforementioned person that they take a huge stone, and tie it around his neck to drown him in the middle of the ocean.</bt><note reference="9:42" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;hadhu gili&gt; dhu ra pake mol are gandum.</note>ho èki mi ladha goro ne, ho pacène ne asa talora dhasi.</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ladhe èu tao sala pake kacui-aai èu, na, poro eele ne. Te be'a risi èu maso sorga dènge kacui-aai cabèka di. Baku d'ai ra core èu asa d'ara ai heo robhe-robhe dènge kacui-aai kateme.<bt>If you(sg) do wrong with/using your hand, cut it off. Which is better? Enter heaven2 with just one hand. Or, with both hands, but they burn you in the fire that burns fiercely hot (to the Max degree)? Certainly it would be better to enter heaven2 with just one hand. [NOTE: hand and fire are homophones].</bt><note reference="9:43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:30</note><v n="44" />[Naraka èèna, mema era j'aj'èra. Ai na madhe boe. Sèmi èèna kahèi, èru-èru kamoke dènge ra'a taruu ngaa-ngaa dhu hèu ètu èèna.]<bt>[Hell (BI loan) is truly a place of suffering. The fire there does not die. And similarly worms wiggle/squirm and eat continually whatever smell/rots there.]</bt><note reference="9:44" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara sasuri Markus lii Yunani asli dhu uru-uru tèka, suri boe ayat ne.<bt>In the oldest writings of Markus in the Yunani (=Greek) language, this verse (loan) is not written.</bt></note><v n="45" />Ladhe èu tao sala pake haga èu, na, poro eele ne. Te be'a risi èu maso sorga dènge haga cabèka di. Baku d'ai ra core èu asa d'ara ai heo robhe-robhe dènge haga kateme.<bt>If you(sg) do wrong with/using your leg/foot, cut it off. Which is better? Enter heaven2 with just one leg. Or, with both legs, but they burn you in the fire that burns fiercely hot (to the Max degree)? Certainly it would be better to enter heaven2 with just one leg.</bt><v n="46" />[Naraka èèna, mema era j'aj'èra. Ai na madhe boe. Sèmi èèna kahèi, èru-èru kamoke dènge ra'a taruu ngaa-ngaa dhu hèu ètu èèna.]<bt>[Hell (BI loan) is truly a place of suffering. The fire there does not die. And similarly worms wiggle/squirm and eat continually whatever smell/rots there.]</bt><note reference="9:46" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara sasuri Markus lii Yunani asli dhu uru-uru tèka, suri boe ayat ne.<bt>In the oldest writings of Markus in the Yunani (=Greek) language, this verse (loan) is not written.</bt></note><v n="47" />Ladhe èu tao sala pake musi madha èu, na, ed'o eele ne. Te be'a risi èu maso sorga dènge musi madha cabèka di. Baku d'ai ra core èu asa d'ara ai heo robhe-robhe dènge musi madha kateme.<bt>If you(sg) do wrong with/using your eyeball, gouge it out. Which is better? Enter heaven2 with just one eyeball. Or, with both eyeballs, but they burn you in the fire that burns fiercely hot (to the Max degree)? Certainly it would be better to enter heaven2 with just one eyeball.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ai1 = hand; ai2 = fire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ai1 = hand; ai2 = fire ; heo robhe-robhe = menyala panas tinggi; <span class="Bold">44:</span> ; <span class="Bold">46:</span> terkesan di hati; kamoke = squirm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ladhe èu tao sala dènge ai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ladhe èu tao sala dènge ai èu, na poro eele ne. Te be'a risi, èu maso sorga dènge ai cabèka di. Te ngaa ra core boe èu asa dara ai, dhu heo lo'a-lo'a dènge kacui-aai tesa.; <span class="Bold">45:</span> Ladhe èu tao sala pake haga èu, poro eele haga deo na. Te be'a risi èu maso sorga dènge haga cabèka, nèti èu dènge haga dua era, te ngaa ra pèci èu sa dara ai naraka.; <span class="Bold">47:</span> Ladhe musi madha èu tao sasala, na edo eele musi madha èèna. Be'a risi èu maso sorga, dhoka dènge musi madha cabèka, nèti ra core èu, asa dara naraka dènge musi madha dua bèka.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:47" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:29</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="48" />&lt;Naraka èèna, mema era j'aj'èra.<bt>'Hell (BI loan) is truly a place of suffering.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ai na, madhe boe.<bt>The fire there does not die.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sèmi èèna kahèi, èru-èru kamoke dènge ra'a taruu ngaa-ngaa dhu hèu ètu èèna.&gt;<bt>And similarly worms wiggle/squirm and continually eat whatever smell/rots there.'</bt><note reference="9:48" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 66:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />A'aj'a Ja'a ne, mema bia. De ladhe cee dhu madhutu Ja'a, nèngu hud'i taha taruu, sèmi dhèu dhu neo paga sisi hud'i masi uuru ku, sèna ka sisi paga èèna taha nèbhu.<bt>This teaching of Mine is really heavy. So whoever it is that follows Me, s/he must endure/last/persevere, like a person who is smoking meat must first put the salt on, so that the aforementioned smoked meat lasts for a long time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="order paga sisi (VO) &gt; sisi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">order paga sisi (VO) &gt; sisi paga (incorporated O?)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Masi mema be'a. Èdhi pake ho pasèro nganga'a. Te ngaa ladhe masi sèro heka, guna na ngaa? Dhoka bhori eele di. Miu hud'i j'aj'i sèmi masi kahèi, sèna ka mamuri pasue dènge dhèu leo aa'i-aa'i.<bt>Salt is good. We(inc) use it to pickle/spice food. But if the aforementioned salt no longer pickles, what use/good is it anymore? Only just throw it away. You(PL) must also be/become like salt, so that you live in mutual.love with all other people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">De mi pasisu ia ka, peka na, cee ka dhu kapai, aa cee ka dhu ana iiki.&gt;&gt;<bt>So you need to stop arguing about who is important, or, who is a small child (=insignificant)."</bt><note reference="9:50" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:13, Lukas 14:34-35</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu Parisi tenge j'ara ho neo pamanahu Lamatua Yesus lula-nèti pa'ia-pa'ela<bt>Marriage-divorce</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:1-12; Lukas 16:18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus si lasi asa propensi Yudea dènge era-era ètu cabèka dhimu loko Yarden. Ètu mia-mia, dhèu ae mai lingu rare Yesus. Hèia Na aj'a si, sèmi biasa.<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) went to the province of Yudea and the places on the east side of the Yarden river. Many people came [and] gathered around Yesus. So He taught them, as usual.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Dhèu Parisi pèri-pèri mai neo pamanahu Ne. Ra karèi Ne sèmi ne'e ka, &lt;&lt;Madhutu a'abhu agama èdhi, ladhe mone dhu dènge le d'ara èmu, bisa pa'ia hari, do aad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>Several Parisi people came wanting to drop Him (=bring Him down). They asked Him like this, "According to the regulations2 of our (inc) religion, if a man has married, can he divorce again, or not?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pacèri = pa'ia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pacèri = pa'ia</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exestin: is it permitted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">exestin: is it permitted</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Miu sanèd'e, do? Atora dhèu èmu-kamali dhu Musa hia èdhi uru èèna, tasamia?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered them like this, "Do you(PL) remember how the teaching goes which Grandpa Musa gave us long ago?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nanori Musa peka, dhèu bisa pa'ia-pa'ela, sad'i dhèu mone tao uru ku sasuri pa'ia dènge dhèu èmu na.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered Him like this, "The teaching of Grandpa Musa said, a person can divorce2, as long as the man first gives a divorce letter to his wife."</bt><note reference="10:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 24:1-4, Mateos 5:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Hèia Yesus b'ala si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nanene, ee! Musa suri sèmi èèna, lula miu kètu hadhu.<bt>So then Yesus responded to them, saying, "Listen, ee! Because you(PL) lot are stubborn (lit. stone heads), because2 of that, Grandpa Musa wrote like that.</bt><v n="6" />Baku bhèlu lii lolo dhu uru tèka, lod'o Lamatua paj'aj'i dedha-liru dènge rai-haha! Dhu suri tèke, peka na,<bt>Don't forget! Cause that which has been written says,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ama Lamatua paj'aj'i dhèu rai-haha, mone dènge bhèni.<bt>'God2 created/made male person and female person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="'Lamatua paj'aj'i dhèu rai-haha na, mone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">'Lamatua paj'aj'i dhèu rai-haha na, mone dènge bhèni.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 1:27, 5:2</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="7" />Nèti èèna ka, dhèu mone tèke eele ina-ama na,<bt>Because2 of that, a male person should leave behind his mother-father,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ho mamuri d'ara èci dènge dhèu èmu na,<bt>to go stay/live united/together with his wife,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">
      <v n="8" />sèna ka dua ra j'aj'i mi èci.&gt;<bt>so that they two become one.'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Check against 1 Cor 6:16 and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">Check against 1 Cor 6:16 and other parallels.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 2:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ladhe Lamatua pa'èci le rèngu dua ra, dhèu rai-haha baku pacèri eele si!&gt;&gt;<bt>If God2 has already united the two of them, humans should not divorce/separate them!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na lasi mesa ra asa d'ara èmu cue. Ètu èèna, rèngu karèi Ne lii aj'a deo sa.<bt>After that, Yesus and His followers went alone into a house. There the followers (coll) asked Him about that recent teaching.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu mone cee dhu ia eele dhèu èmu na, ho na madhèdi hari dènge dhèu bhèni leo, nèngu bersina.<bt>Yesus answered saying, "Whatever male person who has divorced his wife/spouse, and then sits/lives again with a different female person, he has *done the wrong way/path (=euphamism for adultery).</bt><v n="12" />Èci èèna ka, dènge dhèu bhèni. Ladhe nèngu ia eele dhèu èmu na, ho na leo hari dènge mone leo, nèngu bersina kahèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>It is the same with a female person. If she has divorced her spouse, to marry again with a different man, she has also done the wrong way."</bt><note reference="10:11-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:32, 1 Korintus 7:10-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus hia lii mèngi-nale mi ana iiki<bt>Lord Yesus gives a *blessing (word which are very good) to children (coll)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:13-15; Lukas 18:15-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ca tèka, dhèu rèti ana-ana rèngu asa Yesus. Ra manèngi sèna ka Yesus sabaj'a hia si, ho hia lii mèngi-nale. Te ngaa ana madhutu Yesus kai dhèu sèra.<bt>Once, people brought their children to Yesus, requesting that Yesus pray2 for them, to give them words of blessing2. But Yesus' followers forbade/prevented those aforementioned people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sabaj'a = pray; lii dhu nèti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sabaj'a = pray; lii dhu nèti hua iia = omong kasi berkat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Yesus ladhe nèdhi sèmi èèna, ka Na nasa dènge ana madhutu Na sèra, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Hud'i laa ana iiki sèra mai asa Ja'a. Baku magee si. Te dhèu sèmi sèra ka dhu j'aj'i dhèu unu Ama Lamatua.<bt>Yesus saw them doing that, and so He was angry with those followers. So He said, "It must be that these small children come to Me. Don't you(PL) forbid them. Cause people like them, are/become owned by God2.</bt><v n="15" />Miu sanèd'e paie! Dhèu cee dhu neo mai asa katanga-madha Lamatua, d'ara na kateme hud'i d'èi paraga dènge Ne, èci èèna ka ana iiki dhu d'ara d'èi paraga dènge ina-ama ra. Ladhe sèmi boe èèna, rèngu bisa boe j'aj'i dhèu unu Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>Listen well! Whoever wants to come before God2, must want with their insides to meet/be together with Him, just like a small child wants to meet/be together with their mother-father. If it is not like that, they cannot be/become owned by God2."</bt><note reference="10:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:3</note><v n="16" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus liku nare ana iiki se, ka Na tao kacui-aai Na mi dedha kètu ana iiki se èci-èci, ho Na hia si lii mamèngi.<bt>After that, Yesus embraced those small children, and He put His hand on top of each of the heads of these small children, to give them words of blessing (words that are very good).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="magee = prevent/interfere, menghalangi.; |b15:|r dèi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">magee = prevent/interfere, menghalangi.; <span class="Bold">15:</span> dèi dara = rindu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu kaja tenge j'ara ho mamuri taruu dènge Ama Lamatua<bt>A rich man looks for a way to live continually with God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:16-30; Lukas 18:18-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ropa Yesus si neo pakèd'i, dhèu kaja èci rai mai neo paraga dènge Ne. Hèia na pacud'u ètu madha Yesus, ka na karèi Ne, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama mese dhu hua iia! Ja'a neo karèi ciki. Ja'a tao tasamia, sèna ka ja'a ke'a tare'a-re'a, na, ja'a ne maso sorga ho mamuri taruu pa'èci dènge Ama Lamatua?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (coll) wanted to leave, a rich person came hurrying up wanting to meet with Him. And he bowed (head) in front of Yesus, and asked Him, "Father [+affection] teacher who is most excellent/respected! I want to ask something small. It's like this, like I truly want to know how I can enter heaven2 to live continually together with God?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka èu ne peka na, Ja'a ne &lt;hua iia&gt;? Dhèu rai-haha ne èci sa dhu hua iia boe. Dhoka Ama Lamatua di dhu hua iia.<bt>So Yesus answered/responded saying, "Why do you say that I am 'most excellent/respected'? There is not even one human who is most excellent. Only just God, who is most excellent.</bt><v n="19" />Èu me'a le, lii paredha Ama Lamatua sèra nèti uru ka, dhu peka na:<bt>Do you remember or not, God's commands from long ago, which say:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Baku pamadhe dhèu;<bt>'Don't kill people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Baku tao j'ara makae dènge dhèu dhu dhèu èmu-kamali boe èu;<bt>Don't do the wrong way with a person's spouse (=adultery);</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Baku mana'u;<bt>Don't steal;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pagogo-pagero = things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pagogo-pagero = things</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Baku j'aj'i sakasii kapod'e-kabèli;<bt>Don't be a court.witness (loan) that rolls around (=a witness that makes up stories);</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sakasii leko monya;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sakasii leko monya;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Baku monya ho parame more mèdha-panyau dhèu;<bt>Don't deceive with purpose to snatch away people's belonging;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leko-monya ; mèdha-panyau (change vowel elsewhere)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">leko-monya ; mèdha-panyau (change vowel elsewhere)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aa pakab'ua ina-ama èu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>And honour/appreciate/value your(sg) mother-father.'"</bt><note reference="10:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 20:12-16, Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 5:16-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Dhèu èèna dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Tare'a, Ama Mese! Nèti ana ngèru ka mai, ja'a madhutu le lii paredha sèra aa'i-aa'i si.&gt;&gt;<bt>The aforementioned person responded, saying, "True, father teacher! From the time I was young onwards, I have followed all of those commands."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Yesus rasa kasia dènge dhèu ne'e, hèia Na peka, &lt;&lt;Tare'a! Te ngaa j'ara èci era. Lèpa ka asa èmu èu, lamu pahia aa'i su'i-kakaja èu. Kab'ua na lamu pala-bagi mi dhèu dhu unu boe ngaa-ngaa. Èle èèna, heka mai kèna, ho madhutu Ja'a. Pe bèli-camèd'a Lamatua pala-bagi hia èu hari kakaja-sasu'i dhu leo ètu sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus felt pity (assimilated loan) for this person, and so He said, "True! But there is still one way/requirement. Return to your home, and go sell everything you own. It's price/wealth/value go [and] divide up to the people who don't own anything. Then only.after that is done, come [and] follow Me. In the future God2 will give you again different wealth2 in heaven2."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="su'i-kakaja ~ kakaja-sasu'i = all classes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">su'i-kakaja ~ kakaja-sasu'i = all classes of wealth/belongings; kabua CIE with kapua</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ropa dhèu ne tadèngi nare lii padhai lii Yesus èèna, d'ara na laho mae-mae. La'e ka èmu dènge d'ara dhu pèd'a bia, lula nèngu dhèu kaja tare'a.<bt>When this person heard what Yesus had just said, his insides were completely destroyed. He went home with a heavily sick heart, because he was a very rich person.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Hèia Yesus ladhe la'e-mai, aa peka dènge ana madhutu Na sèra, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Mi nanene! Dhèu kaja carui titu kèna maso sorga!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus said to those followers, saying, "You(PL) listen! It's really difficulty for a rich person to enter heaven2!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="carui = sukar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">carui = sukar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00038C.tif" rtfFormat="width:8cm;textWrapping:none">Badha onta<bt>Onta (camel) animal</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ropa tadèngi rare lii padhai lii Yesus èèna, ana madhutu Na bingu. Ka Yesus tuhu hari lii padhai Na, &lt;&lt;Mi nanene paie! Mema carui ladhe dhèu neo j'aj'i dhèu unu Ama Lamatua. Baku ngee èèna mud'a!<bt>When they heard what Yesus said, his followers were confused2. And Yesus said one more time, "You(PL) listen well! It is really difficult for a person wanting to be/become owned by God. Beware lest you think it is easy!</bt><v n="25" />Dhèu kaja maso sorga ho j'aj'i dhèu unu Ama Lamatua, sama carui dènge badha onta ci'u dhu kapai maso asa oka na re ro'a j'aj'au.&gt;&gt;<bt>It is easier for an onta (loan-camel) animal to enter into/through the hole of a sewing.needle, but it is extremely difficult for a rich person to enter heaven2 to become [a person] owned by God."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ci'u = seekor; ciu = rabok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ci'u = seekor; ciu = rabok</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Lii padhai lii Yesus ne asa pamalaa dhèu se'e aa'i-aa'i si. Ka ra pakarèi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe tare'a sèmi èèna, cee ka dhu bisa abhu mamuri dènge Ama Lamatua?&gt;&gt;<bt>What Yesus said to them caused all those people to be amazed. And they asked each other, saying, "If it's really like that, who is it that is able to get continual life with God? (=saved)"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="soda = Rote 'selamat'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">soda = Rote 'selamat'</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Keep looking for 'save'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Keep looking for 'save'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ka Yesus ladhe si èci-èci, hèia Na peka, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Madhutu dhèu rai-haha, na, carui. Te ngaa baku bhèlu, madhutu Ama Lamatua, aa'i-aa'i bisa j'aj'i.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus looked at each of them, and He said, saying, "Following/according to humans, it is difficult. But, don't forget, following God, it can happen."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="according to human understanding, or human"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">according to human understanding, or human strength/ability, xxx is impossible; commentaries all favour ability to save</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Èle èèna ka, Petrus padhai lii, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama, ji'i tèke eele le ngaa-ngaa dhu j'aj'i unu ji'i, ho madhutu Èu. De ji'i abhu bab'ala na ngaa?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Petrus spoke, saying, "Father, we(exc) have left behind everything which is ours, to follow You. So what do we get as reciprocation?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29-30" />Ka Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a neo peka dènge miu sèmi ne'e: dhèu dhu madhutu Ja'a, aa tèke eele ina-ama na, a'ari na, ana-èpu na, oka-tedhe na, sasab'a-la'a na, dènge isi èmu aa'i-aa'i, ho la'e peka-padhai Lii Lolo Be'a Ama Lamatua mi dhèu ètu mia-mia, lèpa loo limuri, nèngu abhu hari ngaa-ngaa sèra, d'ai cangasu hari. Aa'i-aa'i dhu nèngu tèke eele sèra, èèna na nèngu abhu risi hari. Aa nèngu abhu j'aj'èra kahèi, lula madhutu Ja'a. Te ngaa ladhe d'ai lod'o èle rai-haha ne, nèngu mamuri taruu pa'èci dènge Ama Lamatua. Bab'ala nèngu, sèmi èèna ka.<bt>And Yesus answered them, saying, "I want to tell you like this: Whoever leaves behind their kin and their work, to follow Me, to go tell people the Good Word of God, will eventually (=returning in back day) get everything of it, 100 times. The person who leaves behind his/her mother-father, elder sibling-younger sibling, children-grandchildren, house, fields-lands, to.point.that s/he gets difficulty/suffering because follows Me, when arriving at the end of this world, s/he will enter heaven2 to live together with God. S/he will get reciprocated like that.</bt><v n="31" />Sanèd'e paie! Dhèu dhu padedha iisi, madhutu ngangee Ama Lamatua, limuri mai nèngu j'aj'i dhèu haha d'ai seli. Te ngaa dhèu dhu ngee, na, nèngu dhèu haha di, madhutu ngangee Ama Lamatua, limuri mai nèngu j'aj'i dhèu kapai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember well (=toward understanding)! A person who elevates himself (=arrogant/proud), the time will come when s/he becomes/is made like a small child. But, a person who humbles/lowers himself, the time will come when s/he is a person who is respected."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oka-tedhe = kebun; lod'o ~ lodo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">oka-tedhe = kebun; lod'o ~ lodo ~ loo</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ka Yesus dhaa si, peka na,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ka Yesus dhaa si, peka na, "Ja'a neo peka dènge miu sèmi ne'e: Cee dhu tèke eele a'ari dènge sasab'a la'a na, ho madhutu Ja'a, ho papeka lii nanori be'a nèti ama Lamatua, limuri mai na nèngu abhu cangasu hari. Dhèu dhu tèke ele isi èmu, ina-ama, a'ari, ana-ana, oka-teda, ka na abhu j'ara nèti na madhutu Ja'a, lodho kiamat na maso sorga ho mamuri pa èci dènge Ama Lamatua. Babala nèngu sèmi èèna ka.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 20:16, Lukas 13:30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ne'e ka tèlu hari kèna Yesus lole mamadhe Na<bt>This is the third time that Yesus tells about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:17-19; Lukas 18:31-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Lod'o èèna, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na lasi asa kota Yerusalem. Yesus kako uuru. Ana madhutu Na dhèu canguru dua dènge dhèu leo dhu kako pa'èci madhutu Ne re limuri. Rèngu sanèd'e lii padhai dhu Yesus peka dènge rèngu uru èèna, peka na, dhèu neo pamadhe Ne ètu Yerusalem. Nèti èèna ka, rèngu bingu dènge madha'u. Hèia Yesus paroa nare ana madhutu Na sèra mesa ra, ho Na peka hari dènge rèngu dhèu neo tao ngaa mi dedha Nèngu ètu Yerusalem.<bt>That time, Yesus and His followers went to the city of Yerusalem. Yesus was walking in front. His followers (coll) were remembering what Yesus had said to them before, and His followers with other people were walking together, and were confused2 and afraid. And Yesus summoned those followers, [and when] they were alone to say to them the deeds that people would do to Him in Yerusalem.</bt><v n="33" />Yesus peka dènge si, &lt;&lt;Mi nanene! Èdhi neo lati asa Yerusalem. Ja'a ne, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a. Ètu nèi, dhèu neo pahie eele Ja'a asa kètu agama Yahudi dènge mese agama sèra. Èle èèna, ra uku-ked'i pamadhe Ja'a. Ra tule eele Ja'a asa dhèu leo dhu tadhe boe Ama Lamatua.<bt>Yesus told them, "You(PL) listen! We(inc) want to go/are going to Yerusalem. I here and the Child of Humans. People/a person is going to sell Me (=*betray) there, to the fathers of religion and the teachers of religion (coll). After that, they will punish Me with death. They will push Me away to other people who do not know2 God.</bt><v n="34" />Èle èèna ka, ra padhai lii pamakae Ja'a. Ra paru'e ilu mi Ja'a. Aa ra dhedhe pamae iisi Ja'a. Èle èèna, heka ra pamadhe Ja'a kèna. Mema Ja'a madhe tare'a. Te ngaa d'ai camèda, Ja'a mamuri hari.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, they will speak to cause Me shame. They will spit saliva at Me. And they will give My body a horrible beating. After that, in a short time they will kill Me. I will truly die. But, on the third day, I will live again."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="; |b34:|r ma ~ mi ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">; <span class="Bold">34:</span> ma ~ mi ; pamae = hancur di dalam</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Afta three days&quot; is not the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">"Afta three days" is not the same as "Day numba three." In Jewish counting, today is the day 1, tomorrow is day 2, day after is day 3. "Afta three days" could be day 4. CHECK.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:34" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara lii Yunani, ra ige mulai nèti: deo ne'e (=1), bèli (=2), camèd'a (=3), camèd'a èci (=4). De lii Yunani τῃ τρίτῃ ἡμέρᾳ (tei tritei heimera) &lt;&lt;ètu lod'o ka tèlu&gt;&gt;, sasoa na ètu d'ara lii Dhao, nuka &lt;&lt;camèd'a&gt;&gt;. Sanèd'e, te Lamatua Yesus madhe lèke dènge hari Jumat (ige èci). Bèli èèna, nuka hari Sabtu (ige dua), Lamatua Yesus ètu d'ara ro'a dhèu madhe. Camèd'a, nuka hari Migu (ige tèlu), Lamatua Yesus mamuri hari. De madhutu a'ige lod'o ètu d'ara lii Dhao, na, Nèngu madhe dua mèda di, hèia Na mamuri hari.</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yakobis dènge Yohanis manèngi ho j'aj'i dhèu kapai<bt>Yakobis and Yohanis request to be/become important people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:20-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Èle èèna ka, ana Sabadeus, nuka Yakobis dènge Yohanis, mai asa Yesus. Ka ra manèngi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama mese! Ji'i neo padhai lii dènge Ama ciki.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yakobis and Yohanis, the children of Sabadius, came to Yesus. They requested Yesus, saying, "Father teacher! We(exc) want to say a little something with Father."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ka Yesus karèi si, &lt;&lt;Miu neo ngaa?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus asked them, "What do you(PL) want?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Sèmi ne'e, Ama! Bèli-camèd'a, ladhe Ama mèd'u paredha, ji'i manèngi Ama pamadhèdi ji'i dua mi, èci re sebhe g'ana, èci hari re kariu, sèna ka ji'i paredha hèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered Him, saying, "It's like this, Father! When Father holds rule/governs, we request that Father seat the two of us (=give important positions), one on the right side, [and] one again on the left, so that we can also govern."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dispute as to whether Ama mèd'u"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dispute as to whether Ama mèd'u or Ama nèd'u in direct address.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Miu dua mi se me'a boe lii manèngi miu èèna. Èèna na, Ja'a abhu j'aj'èra ae. De tasamia? Miu ngee, na, miu se bisa pasae j'aj'èra dènge Ja'a toke madhe, do?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered them, saying, "The two of you don't understand what you are requesting. I here, am going to get/encounter many difficulties. So, how about it? Do you think that you can shoulder.carry difficulties with Me to the point of death, or [what]?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dui = leba ; pasae ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dui = leba ; pasae = wada</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-11-23 02:35:10Z">,</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:50</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ka ra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ji'i bisa, Ama!&gt;&gt;<bt>And they answered Him, saying, "We can, Father!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka Yesus b'ala, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mema, èèna na, miu pasae j'aj'èra kahèi, sama sèmi Ja'a.<bt>And Yesus responded to them, saying, "Yes, really you will also shoulder.carry suffering/difficulty, the same as Me/together with Me.</bt><v n="40" />Te ngaa cee dhu madhèdi re sebhe g'ana, do sebhe kariu Ja'a, èèna hak Ja'a aad'o. Te dhu hak ka Ama Lamatua dhu pama'ète mema le, na, cee-cee ka dhu madhèdi ètu era sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>But, whoever sits on the right side, or on My left side, that is not My right (assimilated loan); but it is the right of God. He has already decided who it is who will sit in those places."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ropa ana madhutu dhu leo sèra tadèngi lii manèngi Yakobis dènge Yohanis sèmi èèna, ka ra nasa bia.<bt>When the other followers (coll) heard what Yakobis and Yohanis had requested like that, they were really angry.</bt><v n="42" />Hèia Yesus paroa aa'i-aa'i si, ka Na peka, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu me'a le, sina ma? Dhèu-dhèu kapai dhu rèd'u paredha j'eli ana kabarai sèna ka rèngu bisa boe kalau-karèto. Dhèu kapai kabarai dhu tadhe boe Lamatua hia paredha risi eele, ka ana kabarai bisa heka doa kètu.<bt>So then Yesus summoned them all, and He spoke to them like this, "You already know/understand, right? The important people who hold power step.on the populace so that they can't are unable to move. Important people of populaces who do not know God2 give commands excessively, and the populace can no longer raise their heads.</bt><v n="43" />Te ngaa miu baku tao sèmi èèna! Nèti talora miu, cee dhu neo j'aj'i dhèu kapai, nèngu hud'i j'aj'i ku ana pua-paleha ho lalau dhèu leo.<bt>But, beware lest you(PL) also do like that. Whoever among you wants to be/become an important person, s/he must be a servant4 to serve other people.</bt><note reference="10:42-43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:25-26</note><v n="44" />Cee dhu neo j'aj'i dhèu kapai, nèngu hud'i tao ngi'u na sama sèmi ènu.<bt>Whoever wants to be head (Malay loan), s/he must make himself just like a servant2/lowly slave.</bt><note reference="10:43-44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:11, Markus 9:35, Lukas 22:26</note><v n="45" />Ja'a ne, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a. Ja'a mai hia boe dhèu lalau-lalo'o Ja'a. Te ngaa Ja'a mai ho lalau-lalo'o dhèu ae, dènge hia mamuri Ja'a ho sui kore dhèu ae nèti koasa sasala-sasigo rèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>I here am the Child of Humans. I didn't come for people to serve Me. But I came to serve many people, and to give My life to *redeem many people from their sins2."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'eli = injak2; |b45:|r soro iisi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">j'eli = injak2; <span class="Bold">45:</span> soro iisi ; sui = tebus, release/redeem stuff from pawnshop; sui nare sasala-sasigo</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus puri-pa'èle dhèu bèdhu èci ètu Jeriko<bt>Lord Yesus heals a blind person at Jeriko</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:29-34; Lukas 18:35-43)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na, dènge dhèu ae titu kèna kako lasi kota Jeriko. Ropa rèngu neo kako taruu, dhèu bèdhu èci madhèdi ètu sebhe j'ara, na kanata ai ho manèngi ngaa-ngaa nèti dhèu dhu kako re èèna. Ngara na Bartimeos, ana nèti Timeos.<bt>Yesus and His followers, with many other people walked on to the city of Jeriko. When Yesus wanted to continue walking on, a blind person sitting on the side of the path, he stretched out his hand to request something from the people who were walking along there. His name was Bartimeos, the child of Timeos.</bt><v n="47" />Ropa na tadèngi dhèu dhu kako mai sèra, Yesus nèti rae Nasaret na kahèi, ka na rodhe, peka na, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Ana-èpu Daud, ee! Ji'i mate Èu nèbhu ae le! Sue ku ja'a laa!&gt;&gt;<bt>When he heard the people who were walking coming (coll), [that] Yesus from the village of Nasaret was also there, he called out, saying, "Yesus! Descendent of Daud, ee! We(exc) have already waited for you for a long time! Love/pity me!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ropa ra nanene lii rodhe na, hèia dhèu sèra jèke ne, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èu mau-mau ku laa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing what he called out just then, the people scolded him, saying, "You be quiet now!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa na rodhe asa aae, peka na, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Ana-èpu Daud, ee! Sue ku ja'a laa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But increasingly louder he called out, saying, "Yesus! Descendent of Daud, ee! Love/pity me!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Hèia Yesus titu taha, ka Na peka, &lt;&lt;Mèti ku na mai sa ne'e!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then Yesus stood momentarily (=stopped while walking), and He said, "You(PL) bring him here!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka ra lasi peka dènge dhèu bèdhu èèna, peka na, &lt;&lt;Èu mau-mau ka laa! Te Ama mese paroa èu nèi. De mai lati ka!&gt;&gt;<bt>And they went [and] spoke to the aforementioned person, "You be quiet now! Cause Father teacher is summoning you now. So come on now!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ropa nanene nare, ka Bartimeos pèci eele sig'i kalolo na, hèia na kèd'i titu la'e paraga dènge Yesus.<bt>When he heard them, Bartimeos threw off his blanket/outer clothes, and he stood up [and] went to meet with Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Ka Yesus karèi ne, peka na, &lt;&lt;Èu parluu ngaa?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus asked him, saying, "What do you want?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dhèu bèdhu ne dhaa, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama, ee! Ja'a manèngi ho ja'a bisa kèdhi.&gt;&gt;<bt>The blind2 man answered, saying, "Father, ee! I request that I see again."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Yesus peka hari dènge ne, &lt;&lt;Lula èu parcaya, Ja'a bisa tao paie musi madha èu. Ne'e ne kahèi musi madha èu èle dènge! De lamu ka!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus spoke again to him, "Because2 you believe, I can make your eyeballs well, now also your eyeballs are healed! So go on now!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka musi madha Bartimeos èle dènge. Èle ka la'e madhutu Yesus.<bt>The eyeballs of the aforementioned blind2 man were healed, and he went [and] followed Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus si maso Yerusalem, ka dhèu ae koa-kio Ne sèmi dhèu kapai èci<bt>Yesus (coll) enter Yerusalem, and many people praise Him like an important person</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koa-kio = puja-puji (can be many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">koa-kio = puja-puji (can be many people, rame-rame; implies group activity)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:1-11; Lukas 19:28-40; Yohanis 12:12-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Ropa ra dètu dènge kota Yerusalem, ka ra dhuli uuru dua rae, ngara na Betfage dènge Betania, ètu sebhe ledhe Saitun.<bt>When they were near the city of Yerusalem, and they stopped.in first at two villages, named Betfage and Betania, on the slope of mountain/hill Saitun [Malay loan for 'olive'.]</bt><note reference="11:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ra pangare ledhe na, &lt;Saitun&gt;, lula ètu èèna abhu aj'u saitun ae dhu ra pacèli hua ne, ho rare èi mènyi. Ledhe Saitun èèna, ele boe kaj'èu nèngu ca kilometer nèti kota Yerusalem.<bt>They call this mountain/hill 'Saitun', because2 there there are many saitun trees, which they press the fruit to get oil. This Saitun mountain, its distance is only one kilometer from the city of Yerusalem.</bt></note>Ètu èèna, Yesus si mate ciki oo'e di. Ka Na pua ana madhutu Na dhèu dua lasi uuru.<bt>From there, Yesus (coll) waited just a little while. And Yesus sent two of His followers to go ahead.</bt><v n="2" />Na pua si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Miu dua mi lami uuru asa d'ara rae nèi. Ropa miu maso lami, miu mèdhi ana badha keled'ei ci'u, dhu ra èki ètu èèna, dhu dhèu dhae manya'e mèka. Lami ho lècu eele dhari a'èki na, ho ère mèti mai asa ne'e.<bt>And He told them, like this, "You(PL) two go on ahead into the village. When you enter there, you will see an offspring of a keledai animal, which is tied there, which a person has not.yet ridden on. Go and untie its tying rope, to pull take come (=bring it by its rope) here.</bt><v n="3" />Te ngaa ladhe dhèu karèi miu, &lt;Nga tao ka miu ère mèti ana keled'ei ne?&gt; Mi peka dènge si, &lt;Lamatua ji'i neo pake ne. Ladhe pake nare, na, Na hia hari mai.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But when a person/people ask you, 'Why are you taking this keledai offspring?' Then you say to them, 'Lord/master wants to use it. When finished using it, we(exc) He will see it gets back again.'"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapua ledhe = kaki gunung; oo'e"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kapua ledhe = kaki gunung; oo'e = sedikit ; karasa ledhe = lereng ; sebhe ledhe; <span class="Bold">2:</span> lècu = buka tali, untie</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00033C.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.5cm;textWrapping:none">Badha keled'ei<bt>Keledei (donkey) animal</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Èle èèna ka, ana madhutu Na dhèu dua sèra lasi, ka rèdhi ana keled'ei ci'u dhu èki tèke ètu madha èmu cue ètu sebhe j'ara. Ra lècu eele dhari èki na, ka ra ère rèti mai.<bt>After that, His two followers went, and they saw a keledai offspring, which was tied up in front of a house at the side of the road. They untied the rope tying it, and they pulled took came.</bt><v n="5" />Ka dhèu-dhèu dhu titu ètu èèna, peka na, &lt;&lt;We! Nga tao ka miu pakako mèti keled'ei dhèu?&gt;&gt;<bt>And people standing in that place said, "We! Why are you(PL) walking off with [another] person's keledei?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ka ra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua ji'i neo pake ne. Ho ladhe Na pake nare, na, ji'i ngèti hari mai.&gt;&gt; Ka dhèu sèra soro tèke si lasi pakako rèti ana keled'ei èèna.<bt>And they answered them, saying, "Our(exc) lord/master wants to use it. So when He is finished using it, we will bring it back again." And those people handed over to them to take the aforementioned keledai offspring.</bt><v n="7" />Hèia ra rèti ana keled'ei èèna asa Yesus. Ka ra hèle sig'i-kalolo rèngu mi dedha keled'ei, ka Yesus manya'e.<bt>After that, they went off [and] took the keledai offspring to Yesus. And they placed their blankets over the aforementioned keledai, to give Yesus to mount/ride on.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ji'i ngèti ;; |b7:|r manya'e ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ji'i ngèti ;; <span class="Bold">7:</span> manya'e = tunggang, ride an animal (ca'e for car, airplane, motor, ca'e)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00315C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10cm;textWrapping:none">Lamatua Yesus maso asa d'ara kota Yerusalem<bt>Lord Yesus enters the city of Yerusalem</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ropa oe maso d'ara kota, ka dhèu ae rare sig'i-kalolo, ka ra hèle mi dedha j'ara oka-hoo. Dhèu cahag'e lasi para rèu palam<bt>When they were almost entering the city, then many people took blankets/outer clothes and spread them on top of the highway (main road). Some people went and cut off palam</bt><note reference="11:8" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri Markus dhu uuru tèka, peka na, &lt;dadana-dadana&gt;. Te ngaa nèti sasuri Yohanis 12:13, èdhi te'a, na, rèu palam. Palam ne'e, oe sèmi nyiu sa, do aad'o na hènyi.<bt>The oldest writings of Markus say 'branches'. But2 we(inc) know from the writing of Yohanis 12:13 saying these were palam leaves. This palam, was similar to coconut or betelnut [trees/leaves].</bt></note>ètu sebhe j'ara, ho ra tao mi talora j'ara oka-hoo. Tatao sèmi èèna na, sama sèmi tadha èci dhu peka na, rèngu pakab'ua Yesus.<bt>leaves on the side of the road, to put them in the middle of the highway. Doing like this, was like a sign which said they were honouring Yesus.</bt><v n="9" />Dhèu cahag'e kako uru ètu madha Yesus; aa cahag'e kako limuri. Ka ra pa'oo, peka na,<bt>Some people walked ahead of Yesus; and some walked behind. And they happy.shouted saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tao = taruh (not bekin); sapo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tao = taruh (not bekin); sapo = sambut di pantai waktu orang turun dari perahu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Hosana!</span> Mai ti koa-kio kolongara Ama Lamatua!<bt>"Hosana! Let's praise the name2 God!</bt><note reference="11:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii rèngu peka na <span class="Italic">&lt;Hosana&gt;,</span> sasoa na, sèmi ne'e ka, &lt;mera-milu dènge karej'e-karae&gt;. Lii ne'e, biasa ra pake ho koa-kio Ama Lamatua.<bt>The word they were saying '<span class="Italic">Hosana</span>', its meaning is like this, 'peace [doublet] and happiness [doublet]'. This was a word they often used to praise God.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lamatua hia berkat mi dhèu dhu mai pake kolongara Na,<bt>God2 gives blessing2 to this Person who comes with His name2/reputation,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">lula Ama Lamatua hia Ne mai!<bt>because God has sent Him here!</bt><note reference="11:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 118:26</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Mai ti koa-kio kolongara Ama Lamatua!<bt>Hosana! Let's praise name2 of God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lula Lamatua neo pakèd'i hari paredha dhèu aae Daud!<bt>because2 God2 wants to make.stand again the government of King Daud!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Mai ti koa-kio kolongara Ama Lamatua!<bt>Hosana! Let's praise the name2 of God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lula Lamatua madhèdi nèd'u paredha ètu era dedha risi eele!&gt;&gt;<bt>because2 God2 is sitting holding power in the highest place!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ropa ra d'ai d'ara kota, ka Yesus si maso asa madha Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i. Ka Yesus ladhe palème era Èmu èèna. Te ngaa, lula lod'o nihia ae le, ka ra lèpa hari asa rae Betania.<bt>When they arrived in the city, Yesus (coll) went in front of the *Temple (=Base/Primary House of Worship). [CHECK this key term, as there was disagreement as to level of satisfaction between group from Ndao (who all liked it) and group from Kupang (two of whom didn't, and wanted a Malay loan for 'central' to replace 'base')]. And Yesus looked carefully around the place of that House. Because the sun was already late.afternoon, they went.back to the village of Betania.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Èmu Manèngi-Mangaj'i Pusat = Temple (NK);"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Èmu Manèngi-Mangaj'i Pusat = Temple (NK); Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i = Temple (UNS-NN); kapua = lahin, batang, pokok, pointed to base of tree</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00250C.tif" rtfFormat="width:11cm;textWrapping:none">Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i Ama Lamatua<bt>God's *Temple (Central House of Worship)</bt></fig>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus pua aj'u èci ho baku hua<bt>A tree which has no fruit</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="saseo (dhèu) = curse, kutuk, (\oe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">saseo (dhèu) = curse, kutuk, (\oe humans as objects); suba = sumpah (broader, generic); soo = sumpah minta kutuk, sumpah serapa, ; dhoo = sumpah, kutuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Asa bèli mad'ae aae èèna, ka rèngu kalua nèti Betania lasi asa Yerusalem. D'ai talora j'ara ka Yesus manganga.<bt>The next morning, they left from Betania and went to Yerusalem. In the middle of the journey Yesus was hungry.</bt><v n="13" />Ka Na ladhe nèdhi ana aaj'u èci ètu sebhe j'ara. Hua aj'u na, dhu dhèu ra'a.<bt>And He saw a tree by the side of the road. The fruit of this tree was what people ate.</bt><note reference="11:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii Idhonesia peka na, &lt;aj'u ara&gt;, nèti lii Yunani dhu peka na, <span class="Italic">sukei.</span> Te ngaa Alkitab peka aj'u èci ètu nèi, dhu dhèu ra'a hua na. Ètu Idhonesia bèka dhimu, dhèu ra'a boe hua aj'u &lt;ara&gt;. De aj'u ara ètu Alkitab leko-leo dènge aj'u ara ètu ne'e.<bt>The Indonesia language says 'ara tree', while the Yunani language says '<span class="Italic">sukei</span>'. But the Alkitab (=*Bible) says that was a kind of tree which people ate its fruit. In the eastern part of Indonesia, people do not eat the fruit of the 'ara' tree. So the ara tree in the Bible, is not the same as the ara tree here.</bt></note>Yesus la'e padètu ho neo ne'a aj'u na, hua do aad'o. Na ladhe aj'u èèna hua boe cue sa. Te mema d'ai mèka hèru hua. Rèu heka mare kèna.<bt>Yesus went near wanting to know that tree, [whether] fruit or not. He saw that this tree didn't even have one single fruit. But4 It was actually not.yet the month/season for fruit. It was just beginning to leaf.</bt><v n="14" />Ka Yesus peka mi aj'u èèna, &lt;&lt;Lula èu hia boe Ja'a hua, mulai ti deo ne'e, èu bisa heka hia hua èu asa dhèu leo!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus said to that tree, "Because2 you(sg) did not give Me fruit, beginning from just now, you cannot again give your fruit to another person!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ti &lt; nèti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ti &lt; nèti</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ana madhutu Yesus sèra tadèngi Na padhai lii dènge nasa sèmi èèna.<bt>Yesus followers (coll) heard Him speak with anger like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus maso asa Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i, ka Na pa'ele iie era pahia-pahèli<bt>Yesus entered into the Temple, and He destroys the selling-buying place</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tule paguri eele = merubuhkan (meja);"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tule paguri eele = merubuhkan (meja); era pahia-pahèli = pasar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:12-17; Lukas 19:45-48; Yohanis 2:13-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Yesus si kako taruu asa Yerusalem, d'ai nèi ka Yesus maso asa Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i. Ètu madha Èmu èèna, dhèu tao pasa ho ra pahia koro j'aha dhu biasa dhèu pake tao korban ho ra sabaj'a. Ropa Yesus nèdhi sèmi èèna, ka Na lalèta si asa li'u. Na tule eele mei dhu ra pake ho pasilu doi sèra, aa Na tule paguri eele bagu dhu ra pake pahia manu-bhui sa.<bt>Yesus (coll) walked on to Yerusalem, [and] arriving there Yesus entered the Temple. In front of that House (=yard) people had made a market (assimilated loan) for them to sell dove/pidgeon birds which people normally used to make *sacrifice (loan) for them to pray2/worship. When Yesus saw them like that, He evicted them outside. He pushed over the tables they used to exchange their money, and He pushed collapsed the benches (assimilated loan) which they used to sell birds.</bt><v n="16" />Ka Yesus kai si aa'i-aa'i ra, sèna ka ra rèti ia ka mèdha rèngu re d'ara madha Èmu èèna.<bt>And Yesus forbade them all, so that they should not.again bring their things to make a market in the yard of that House.</bt><v n="17" />Ka Na aj'a si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Miu me'a le lii dhu dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua suri tèke le, peka na: &lt;Ja'a tao èmu ne'e, sèna ka suku aa'i-aa'i mai sabaj'a ètu ne'e.&gt; Te ngaa miu tao Èmu ne j'aj'i era pakaboko dhèu parapo.&gt;&gt;<bt>And He forbade them, saying, "You(PL) already know the words that God's spokesperson has written, saying: 'I make this house, so that people from all sorts of other regions can come [and] pray2 here.' But you have made this House become a place of gathering for robber people."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sabae = ; sabaj'a = ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sabae = ; sabaj'a = ; koro j'aha = burung pompa; pakabèli; lege = balik</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 56:7, Yermia 7:11</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01787b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ropa kètu agama Yahudi dènge mese agama sèra re'a rare tatao Yesus sèmi èèna, ka ra nasa dènge Ne. Ka ra tenge j'ara ho neo pamadhe Ne. Te ngaa ra madha'u, lula dhèu ae dhu d'èi lii holo-nori Yesus.<bt>When the fathers of religion and the teachers of religion (coll) found out what Yesus had done like that, they were angry with Him. And they looked for a way wanting to kill Him. But they were afraid, because many people liked the teachings of Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />D'ara lod'o cèna sa, Yesus si kalua hari nèti kota Yerusalem lèpa lasi j'unu asa rae Betania.<bt>When the sun was going down, Yesus (coll) left again from the city of Yerusalem [and] went to sleep in the village of Betania.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ladhe miu parcaya dènge d'ara kateme, Ama Lamatua dhaa lii manèngi miu<bt>If you(PL) believe with your whole insides, only.then will God answer/respond to your request</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abho uuru ku dhèu, heka Ama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Abho uuru ku dhèu, heka Ama Lamatua hia abho mi èu kèna; <span class="Bold">19:</span> Forgive people first, only.then will God *give forgiveness to you(sg)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="two kinds of forgive here; we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">two kinds of forgive here; we can lupa buang orang pung salah, but we cannot hapus buang orang pung salah; we can only forgive them; only God can hapus buang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:20-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20-21" />Bèli mad'ae èèna, Yesus si lasi hari asa Yerusalem. D'ai talora j'ara, ka ra rèdhi aj'u dhu Yesus padhai lii med'a na. Ka ana madhutu Yesus sèra malaa, lula rèngu rèdhi aj'u èèna mango le d'ai amo. Hèia Petrus sanèd'e lii padhai lii Yesus med'a na. Ka na peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ladhe ku! Aj'u dhu Ama dhoo med'a na, madhe le!&gt;&gt;<bt>The next morning, Yesus (coll) went again to Yerusalem. Arriving at the middle of the journey, they saw the tree which Yesus had spoken, yesterday (=the previous day). And Yesus followers were amazed/confused, because2 they saw that tree was already dry from roots.So then Petrus remembered what Yesus had said yesterday. And he said, "Father! Look here a sec! The tree which you *cursed yesterday is already dead!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="med'a = kemarin; |b21:|r dhoo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">med'a = kemarin; <span class="Bold">21:</span> dhoo = sumpah, kutuk ; (n) li dhoo</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Tare'a, we! Sad'i miu parcaya Ama Lamatua sèmi èèna, na, j'aj'i kahèi.<bt>Yesus answered/responded to him, saying, "True, we! As long as you(PL) believe God like that, it [can/will] also happen.</bt><v n="23" />Ladhe miu parcaya dènge d'ara kateme, miu bisa pua ledhe hia na pidha asa d'ara dhasi. Pe Lamatua pidha eele ledhe èèna, sad'i miu baku parcaya dènge d'ara cabèka. Miu parcaya mi Ama Lamatua, hud'i dènge d'ara kateme ku.<bt>Like you believe with your whole insides (wholeheartedly), you can tell/order a mountain to move into the ocean. And God2 will move away the aforementioned mountain, as long as you don't believe half-heartedly. [When/if] you believe God, it must be with firm insides (implies convinced, not doubting).</bt><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 17:20, 1 Korintus 13:2</note><v n="24" />Baku bhèlu! Sad'i miu parcaya dènge d'ara kateme, ngaa dhu miu manèngi, tatu Ama Lamatua bisa hia miu.<bt>Don't forget, ee! As long as you believe with firm insides, that which you just requested has been gotten, truly God gives it to you.</bt><v n="25" />Ladhe dhèu èci sabaj'a, aa te ngaa na tèka d'ara era dènge dhèu leo, nèngu hud'i la'e pabe'a uuru ku dènge dhèu èèna. Ladhe miu tao sèmi èèna, Ama miu ètu sorga heka saku eele sasala miu kèna.<bt>But3 when a person is praying2, but he begrudges/is annoyed with/angry with another person, he must first go make.right with the aforementioned person. If [you do] like that, your[PL] Father in heaven2, only.then will wipe away his wrongs. [CHECK: Let's check the change from third person singular to second person plural.]</bt><v n="26" />[Ladhe abhu nèti miu dhu tèka d'ara dènge dhèu, ho mo'o boe hia abho, na, tatu Ama miu ètu sorga no'o boe pabhèlu eele sasala miu kahèi.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[If you(PL) begrudge a person, so you don't want to give forgiveness, then your Father in heaven2 will also not wipe away your wrongs].</bt><note reference="11:26" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani dhu asli dhu uru tèka, suri boe ayat 26.<bt>The old(est) writings in the Yunani language do not enter verse (loan) 26.</bt></note><note reference="11:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 6:14-15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ra pakarèi hak Lamatua Yesus<bt>They dialogue.asking.each.other the right of the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:23-27; Lukas 20:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus si lasi taruu. Ropa d'ai Yerusalem, ka ra maso hari asa Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i. Ropa maso asa madha Èmu èèna, kètu agama Yahudi, mese agama, dènge dhèu heka-dhèu heka Yahudi sèra mai,<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) continued on. When they arrived at Yerusalem, they entered again into the *Temple. When they entered that Temple yard, the fathers of religion and teachers of religion came,</bt><v n="28" />ka ra karèi Yesus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Cee ka dhu pua èu mai tao maruru ètu ne'e med'a na? Cee ka hia èu hak!&gt;&gt;<bt>and they asked Yesus, saying, "Who was it that sent you(sg) to make that noisy.chaos here yesterday? Who gave you that right!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Te ngaa Yesus ne'a, na, rèngu neo tenge j'ara ho pamanahu Ne. Ka Na b'ala si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a neo karèi miu kahèi. Miu dhaa uuru ku Ja'a, heka Ja'a dhaa miu kèna.<bt>But Yesus knew that they were looking for a way to cause.fall Him. And He responded to them, saying, "I also want to ask you(PL). You answer Me first, only.then with I answer you then.</bt><v n="30" />Ja'a neo karèi miu sèmi ne'e: miu aa'i-aa'i mi tadhe Yohanis, tuka sarani èèna, sina ma? Cee ka dhu pua nèngu la'e sarani dhèu? Lamatua do, dhèu rai-haha?&gt;&gt;<bt>I want to ask you like this: You all know2 Yohanis, the Tukang Baptiser, right, don't you. Who was it that told him to go *baptise people. Did God2 send [him], or humans?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="contrastive, cleft-focus @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">contrastive, cleft-focus @@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ra pajiko la'e-mai, ka ra padhue, peka na, &lt;&lt;Eea! Nara èdhi le! Ladhe èdhi dhaa, peka na, &lt;Ama Lamatua ka dhu pua Yohanis,&gt; na b'ala hari, peka na, &lt;Nga tao ka miu parcaya boe Yohanis!&gt;<bt>They weighed.options going-coming, and they discussed saying, "Eea! He's got us(inc)! If we answer saying, 'God is the one who sent/ordered Yohanis,' he will then respond saying, 'Why didn't you believe Yohanis!'</bt><v n="32" />Te ngaa èdhi bisa boe peka kahèi, na, &lt;Dhèu rai-haha dhu pua ne.&gt; Te aad'o na, dhèu ae tao dènge èdhi. Lula dhèu ae parcaya, Yohanis èèna, dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>But we also can't say, 'Humans are the ones who sent him.' Cause whatever else, the very many people (coll), will do us in. Because2 many people believe that Yohanis was God's spokesperson."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ka ra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ji'i nge'a boe!&gt;&gt;<bt>And they answered, saying, "We(exc) don't know!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka Yesus dhaa hari si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe sèmi èèna, Ja'a ko'o boe peka kahèi, cee ka dhu pua Ja'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>So then Yesus answered/responded them again, saying, "I also don't want to say, who it was that sent Me."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii pakasame lula-nèti dhèu sab'a oka anggor<bt>The *example/parable of people working the anggor (loan-grape) field</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:33-46; Lukas 20:9-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Èle ka, Yesus padhai lii hari dènge kètu agama Yahudi, mese agama, dènge dhèu heka-dhèu heka ad'a Yahudi sèra. Ka Na lole pake lii upama èci, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu èci la'e tao oka ho neo sèla anggor ètu dedha rai na. Ka na tao tedhe reo nare oka èèna, aa tao bak cue ho kanate èi anggor asa d'ara la'e kahèi. Hèia na patitu èmu madhenga oka cue dhu dedha. Èle èèna ka, na hia dhèu leo seb'a oka èèna, ho ra pabagi èi anggor. Hèia na pakèd'i asa rai leo la'e.<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again with the fathers of religion and the teachers of the Jahudi religion (coll). And He told them an example/parable, saying, "A person went [and] made a field to plant anggor (loan-grapes) on his land. And he made a fence around the aforementtioned field, and also made a tub to catch.liquid the anggor juice in it. And he erected a field guard house which was tall. After that, he rented that field to other people, so they could divide up the anggor juice. Then he left and went to another region.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èmu maa = rumah jaga kebun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">èmu maa = rumah jaga kebun yg ukuran kecil; karab'a = bak</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 5:1-2</note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00103C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10cm;textWrapping:none">Oka hua anggor, èmu madhenga dhu dedha, dènge bak ho kanate èi anggor asa d'ara la'e<bt>Field of anggor fruit, high guard house, and tank for collecting grape juice inside it</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Lod'o d'ai hèru puu-g'ètu hua anggor, ka lamatua oka pua ana paleha na èci la'e asa dhèu sab'a oka sèra, ho na manèngi pala na.<bt>When the month/season for harvesting [doublet] the anggor fruit arrived, the aforementioned *lord/master/owner of the land sent one of his servants4 to those people who were working the field (coll), to request his portion.</bt><v n="3" />Ropa d'ai nèi, ka dhèu seb'a sèra kèpe rare, ka game ne. Hèia ra pua ne lèpa dènge ai hua da'u-da'u.<bt>When he arrived there, those working people grabbed him, and beat him up. And then they sent him back home empty-handed (=with nothing to show for his efforts relating to the purpose of his journey)..</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="puu-g'ètu, not pu-bètu ;; |b3:|r ai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">puu-g'ètu, not pu-bètu ;; <span class="Bold">3:</span> ai hua (da'u-da'u) = tangan kosong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ka lamatua oka pua hari ana paleha leo èci. Te ngaa dhèu seb'a sèra dhedhe panu'a kètu na. Ka ra pamakae ne, dènge magèle eele ne.<bt>And the lord of that field sent another servant4 again. But those working people hit him on his head causing fresh.wounds. And they shamed him, and evicted4 him.</bt><v n="5" />Hèia lamatua oka èèna pua hari ana paleha leo èci la'e. Te ngaa dhèu seb'a sèra hake pamadhe ne. Ra tao samia èèna ka, lamatua oka pua taruu ana paleha na la'e. Te ngaa dhèu seb'a sèra game cahag'e, aa pamadhe cahag'e.<bt>That lord of the field, sent again another servant4. But those working people beat [and] killed him. Even though they kept doing the same thing, the lord of the land kept sending his servants4. But those working people, some they beat up, and some they killed.</bt><v n="6" />Ate eele dhodhoka ana mone mesa dhu pasue nèti lamatua oka. Lula na abhu heka j'ara dhu leo, ka lamatua oka na pua ana d'èlu na la'e. Na pajiko, peka na, &lt;Sèmi ja'a pua ana d'èlu ja'a la'e, na, rèngu sèmi rare dènge be'a, aa ra nanene ne.&gt;<bt>Eventually there remained only the beloved son alone of the aforementioned lord of the land. Because2 there was no other way, the lord of the land sent his abdominal.cavity child (=own flesh &amp; blood). He weighed the options, saying, "If2 I send my own flesh &amp; blood son, they will be good, and they will listen to (also=obey) him.'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tuku; |b6:|r ana dèlu = anak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tuku; <span class="Bold">6:</span> ana dèlu = anak kandung</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Hèia na pua ana na la'e. Ropa dhèu seb'a sèra rèdhi ana na mai, ka ra papeka isi-aanga ra, peka na, &lt;We! Mi ladhe ku laa! Mone heka nèi pua ana d'èlu na mai! Ladhe ama na madhe, nèngu ne'e ka dhu sèmi nare aa'i-aa'i mèdha pusaka ama na. De mai ti pamadhe ne, sèna ka èdhi tare pusaka na!&gt;<bt>So he sent his offspring. When those working people saw his offspring coming, they talked among themselves, saying, 'We! Take a look at this! The male (=boss) is now sending his offspring to come here! When the father dies, he this is the one who receives the inheritance (handed-down things, both goods and lands) of his father. So let's kill him, and then let's (inc) take his inheritance!'</bt><v n="8" />Ka aa'i-aa'i ra kèpe, ka ra pamadhe ne, hèia ra core eele ngi'u aae na asa li'u tedhe la'e. Lii pakasame ne, d'ai sange ne'e ka.&gt;&gt;<bt>And so they all grabbed, and they killed him, and they threw away his body over behind the fence [implies rubbish heap of the field]. this example, parable, has reached its limit."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sange = cela"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sange = cela</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus karèi dhèu kapai sèra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Madhutu ngangee miu, na, lamatua oka èèna tao dhèu seb'a sèra tasa mera mia? Madhutu ngangee Ja'a, tatu nèngu mai ho pamadhe aa'i dhèu seb'a sèra, sèna ka na hia dhèu leo hari seb'a oka anggor na.<bt>After tha, Yesus asked those important people saying, "According to your(PL) thinking, the aforementioned lord of the land will do what to those working people? (=how will he handle them?) If you follow My thinking, the male/boss will come and kill all of those working people, and then give to other people instead to rent that anggor field.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti baca le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua, peka na,<bt>We(inc) have all read, in the Writings of God, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Abhu hadhu cue dhu tuka hadhu sèra core eele le,<bt>'A stone which the stone masons (coll) had already thrown away,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te ngaa limuri ne, j'aj'i le hadhu padhèdi.<bt>later on, it became the main.support stone (=under the main house pole).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hadhu kapua = batu yg ditanam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hadhu kapua = batu yg ditanam keras, sonde bisa dicungkil, ada akar; hadhu sipa = patokan, lurus ; hadhu turu = monument; hadhu pad'èdi = placed in centre of house under central post; hadhu mera = flat stone</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Ama Lamatua mesa Na dhu pili nare, ka Na pamadhèdi hadhu ne.<bt>God himself is the one who chose it, and put this stone in place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nèti èèna ka, èdhi ladhe, na, be'a titu kèna!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, we(inc) see it, and it is exceedingly good!'"</bt><note reference="12:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 118:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dhèu kapai sèra re'a dènge, na, Yesus padhai lii paraga, pake lii pakasame èèna. Rèngu sèra sama sèmi dhèu seb'a oka anggor èèna. Hèia ra tenge j'ara ho neo kèpe Yesus. Te ngaa ra madha'u dènge dhèu ae dhu d'èi lii holo-nori Yesus. Ka ra kako eele Ne.<bt>Those important people understood that Yesus spoke about them, using that example. They were like those working people in the aforementioned anggor field. So then they looked for a way wanting to arrest Yesus. But they were afraid of the many people who liked the teachings of Yesus. So they left Him and walked away.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu neo sahèdhe Yesus dènge j'ara b'ae bea<bt>People want to ensnare Yesus with the way to pay tax (assimilated loan)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:15-22; Lukas 20:20-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Èle èèna ka, dhèu kapai Yahudi se pua pèri-pèri dhèu Parisi dènge dhèu nèti partei Herodes, lasi pakarèi dènge Yesus, ho ra neo sahèdhe Ne.<bt>After that, the important people of the Jahudi, sent several Parisi people and people from the Herodes group/party to go debate with Yesus, wanting to ensnare Him.</bt><v n="14" />Ka ra karèi Ne, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama Mese! Ji'i nge'a, na, d'ara Ama ku mola, aa d'èi boe kapod'e-kabèli. Ama me'a d'ara dhèu. Ama peka dad'èi Lamatua dènge mola-mola, lula Ama pili boe rèhu dhèu. De, ji'i neo karèi Ama ku ca j'ara. Madhutu atora agama Yahudi, èdhi bisa b'ae bea asa dhèu aae kapai dhu paredha Roma,<bt>And they asked Him, saying, "Father Teacher! We(exc) know that Father's insides are straight/pure, and there is no deceit (lit. twisting around). Father is the one who knows a person's insides. Father tells the will/ways of God truthfully, because Father doesn't choose the face of people (= doesn't modify what is said according to who is listening). Now, we want to ask Father a little bit. According to the regulations of the Jahudi religion, can we(inc) pay taxes to *Ceasar (the Top King of the Roma government),</bt><note reference="12:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dhèu aae kapai dhu paredha Roma, ra pangare ne &lt;Keser&gt;.<bt>The Top Boss of the Roma government, they call him 'Keiser'.</bt></note>do aad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>or not?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Te ngaa Yesus ne'a le, na, rèngu neo sahèdhe Ne, sèna ka Na padhai lii lab'a paredha Roma. Ka Yesus b'ala si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka miu neo sahèdhe Ja'a dènge lii karèi sèmi èèna! Cob'a pad'elo ku mi Ja'a doi pudhi cue!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus already knew that they wanted to bait Him, so He would speak opposing the Roma government. So Yesus responded to them speaking angrily, saying, "Why do you(PL) want to ensnare Me with a question like that! Please show Me a silver money!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pudhi = white; doi pudhi ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pudhi = white; doi pudhi = silver coin; leko = pancing, umpan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00166C.tif" rtfFormat="width:7cm;TextWrapping:none">Doi pudhi nèti paredha Roma<bt>Silver money from the Roma Government</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ka ra j'ole doi pudhi cue hia Ne. Hèia Yesus nare, ka laladhe. Ka Na karèi si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Rèhu dènge ngara cee ètu doi pudhi ne?&gt;&gt;<bt>And they stretched.hand giving Him a silver money. Then Yesus took and inspected. And He asked them, saying, "Face and name of who on this silver money?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rèhu ~ rohu = wajah, muka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">rèhu ~ rohu = wajah, muka</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ka ra dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Èèna dhèu aae kapai paredha Roma!&gt;&gt;<bt>And they answered Him, saying, "It is *Ceasar (Top King of Roma govt.)!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ka Yesus peka, &lt;&lt;Naa, ladhe sèmi èèna, ngaa dhu unu dhèu paredha, hia asa dhèu paredha la'e. Te ngaa dhu unu Ama Lamatua, hia asa Ama Lamatua la'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus told them, "Because3 of that, what is owned/under.custodianship of government people, give to the government people. But that which is owned by God, give (PL) to God."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kèri sèmi èna na = karena"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Kèri sèmi èna na = karena itu,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">check</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ropa tadèngi rare, lii b'ala Na, ka ra malaa, lula Yesus peka dhu lèke. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu sèra bisa heka sahèdhe Ne.<bt>When they heard that response, they were amazed, because2 Yesus spoke it right (lit. connected). Because2 of that, those people could no longer ensnare Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu madhe mamuri hari, aa dhèu paleo èmu ètu sorga, do aad'o?<bt>The problem/way of dead people living again, and marrying or not in heaven2?</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:23-33; Lukas 20:27-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Abhu partei agama dhu leo èci, ngara na partei Saduki. Rèngu aj'a, peka na, dhèu madhe bisa heka mamuri. Ca tèka, abhu dhèu Saduki pèri-pèri mai neo sahèdhe Yesus.<bt>After that, several people from a different party/group came again, wanting to ensnare Yesus. (These people were from the Saduki party, which teaches saying dead people cannot live again).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Èle èèna ka, dhèu pèri-pèri nèti partei leo sèra mai neo sahèdhe hari Yesus. Dhèu se'e nèti partei Saduki, dhu aj'a, peka na, dhèu madhe bisa heka mamuri."><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-11-23 04:22:38Z" status="Anyone">OV</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 23:8</note><v n="19" />Ka ra padhai lii dènge Yesus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama Mese! Musa suri tèke le hia èdhi atora, peka na: ladhe dhèu mone èci madhe tèke eele dhèu èmu na, te ngaa rèngu dènge boe kolo, na, ari dhèu mone na bisa leo nare hari bhèni balu èèna, sèna ka abhu kolo ho baku pa'ele kolongara a'a na dhu madhe èèna.<bt>And they spoke with Yesus, saying, "Father Teacher! Grandpa Musa wrote giving our(inc) regulations, saying: when a man dies leaving behind his wife, but they don't have children. The younger.sibling.same.sex of this aforementioned man can marry taking again that female widow, for the purpose to get children so that the name/reputation doesn't disappear of his older.sibling who died.</bt><note reference="12:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 25:5</note><v n="20" />Mema Musa aj'a sèmi èèna. Te ngaa ji'i neo karèi Ama sèmi ne'e: abhu dhèu pidhu dhu pa'a'ari. Mone uru leo uuru èmu, te ngaa madhe, abhu mèka kolo.<bt>This is what Grandpa Musa taught about that. But we want to ask you like this. There were seven people who were older-younger siblings to each other. The oldest male was the first to marry, but he died, not.yet getting a child.</bt><v n="21" />Ka ari na leo nare bhèni balu èèna. Nèbhu boe ka ari na madhe, te ngaa abhu boe kolo kahèi. Ari na ka tèlu, sèmi èèna kahèi; na leo nare bhèni balu èèna, te ngaa abhu mèka kolo, nèngu madhe.<bt>And his younger.sibling (yS) married taking the aforementioned female widow. Not long after that aforementioned yS died again (=too), but also didn't get a child. His third yS did the same also; he married taking the aforementioned female widow, but without yet getting a child, he died.</bt><v n="22" />Taruu-taruu sèmi èèna ka, d'ai ana limuri tèka madhe kahèi. Nèbhu boe, hèia bhèni balu èèna madhe.<bt>It kept on going like that, until the youngest child also died. Not long after that, the aforementioned female widow also died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paleo = pa-leo = REC-marry, homophonous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">paleo = pa-leo = REC-marry, homophonous w/ paleo (tent); <span class="Bold">19:</span> abhu boe kolo = (fig) tidak dapat turunan (lit. tidak dapat ujung pohon), well known metaphor; <span class="Bold">20:</span> pa- = recip; pa'a'a-ari; <span class="Bold">22:</span> ana limuri = anak bungsu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Naa! Ji'i neo karèi Ama sèmi ne'e: dhèu bhèni èèna, leo le dènge mone dhèu pidhu! D'ai lod'o èle rai-haha ne, ho Lamatua pamamuri hari dhèu madhe, bhèni ne j'aj'i dhèu èmu cee, nèti dhèu pidhu sèra?&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa! We(exc) want to ask you like this: that aforementioned woman, has married seven men! When arriving at the day of the end of this world, and God2 cause.live again dead people, that woman will be whose wife, from those seven people?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Lii karèi miu sèra, tadha, na, miu me'a iia mèka isi Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua! Miu me'a boe koasa Lamatua kahèi. De miu sala titu kèna!<bt>Yesus answered/responded, saying, "Your(PL) questions proove that you don't understand the content of the Writings of God! You also do not understand the power of God2. So you are really wrong! (has sense of 'out to lunch')</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Mi nanene! Sèmi ne'e: ètu sorga dhèu paleo boe èmu. Dhèu madhe aa'i-aa'i dhu Lamatua pamamuri hari, ra paleo heka èmu. Sèmi èèna kahèi, ana pajuu Ama Lamatua ètu sorga.<bt>Listen! It's like this! In heaven people will not reciprocally marry. Dead people who God2 cause.live again, they will not reciprocally.marry. In the same way also, *Angels (servant of God in heaven).</bt><v n="26" />Aa Ja'a peka mi miu lula-nèti dhèu madhe mamuri hari, do aad'o. Musa suri tèke lula-nèti ana aaj'u dhu ai na'e, te ngaa kèpu boe. Miu sanèd'e lii lolo èèna, do aad'o? Ropa ai na'e ana aaj'u èèna, Ama Lamatua peka dènge Musa, na, &lt;Ja'a ne, Ama Lamatua nèti bèi-baki èu, nuka Abraham, Isak, dènge Yakob. Toke d'ai sange ne'e, rèngu aa'i-aa'i manèngi-mangaj'i mi Ja'a era.&gt;<bt>But, about dead people who live again, I tell you like this. You really don't understand the story about the tree which fire had climbed, but it wasn't burned, which was written in the writings of Grandpa Musa. That story, says, God says to Musa, 'I here, am God of your forefathers, like Grandpa Abraham, Grandpa Isak, and Grandpa Yakob. They still worship Me, even up to now.'</bt><note reference="12:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 3:6</note><v n="27" />Èdhi te'a, na, bèi-baki èdhi sèra madhe nèbhu le. Te ngaa, lula Ama Lamatua peka nare le, na, Nèngu j'aj'i Lamatua rèngu era. Nèti èèna ka, èdhi te'a, na, rèngu mamuri hari le. De masi ka dhèu madhe le, te ngaa ra mamuri hari. De dhèu mamuri dhu manèngi-mangaj'i mi Ama Lamatua, te ngaa dhèu madhe aad'o, sina ma? Nèti èèna ka, ladhe miu kèpe taruu a'aj'a dhu peka na, dhèu madhe mamuri heka, èèna miu sala ae!&gt;&gt;<bt>So we(inc) know that our forefathers are not found already dead. But from what God has said, He is still their God2/Lord. Because of that, we know that they have lived again/are still living. So even though people have died, but (=nevertheless) they live again. So living people who worship God, are not dead people, right? Because of that, when you continue to hold the teaching which teaches, saying, dead people do not live again, you are really/grossly/major big.time wrong!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ami = hutan; bush, plural; (problem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">j'ami = hutan; bush, plural; (problem between Eng (singular) and BI samak duri (stand, plural) ; revise KM ??@@; pahaha iisi = merendahkan diri; era = masih, ada, tempat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii paredha ho sue Lamatua, aa sue dhèu leo kahèi<bt>The command to love/pity (?) God2, and love/pity other people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:34-40; Lukas 10:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ètu lod'o èèna, abhu mese agama èci dhu nanene Yesus padhai lii dènge dhèu nèti partei Saduki sèra. Madhutu a'abhu mese agama èèna, na, Yesus dhaa lèke le lii karèi rèngu. Hèia na karèi Yesus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: atora ad'a dènge lii paredha agama èdhi ae titu kèna. Madhutu a'abhu Ama, nèti lii paredha dhu mai nèti Musa, mia ka dhu hua iia risi?&gt;&gt;<bt>That day/time, there was a teacher of religion who was listening to Yesus speaking with those people from the Saduki party/group. According to the opinion of that teacher of religion, Yesus responded correctly/appropriately to their question. So he asked Yesus saying, "Father! I want to ask you like this: the regulations of customary laws and the commands of our(inc) religion are really many. According to your opinion, of the various commands which come from Grandpa Musa, which is the best/most significant?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="papuru = turunkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">papuru = turunkan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01744b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ka Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Lii paredha dhu hua iia risi, peka sèmi ne'e ka:<bt>So Yesus answered him, saying, "The command which is the best/most significant says like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Miu dhèu Isra'el aa'i-aa'i mi! Mi nanene paie!<bt>'All you(PL) Israel people! Listen well!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ama Lamatua èèna, mema Lamatua èdhi,<bt>God is truly our(inc) lord/master!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa Kètu èdhi kahèi.<bt>He is the only one alone,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Nèngu dhoka mesa Na di, lamatua leo aad'o.<bt>there is no other lord/master.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="30" />De miu hud'i sue <span class="Italic">risi eele</span> Ne nèti aa'i-aa'i.<bt>Therefore, you must love/pity Him <span class="Italic">exceedingly more</span> than you love/pity people, and everything else,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nèti èèna ka, miu hud'i d'èi pa'èci dènge Ne dènge d'ara kateme,<bt>and with your whole insides want to be together/united with Him continually,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa tadhe mèu Ne,<bt>and know2 Him (= understand character and what makes him tick),</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tadhe = kenal (can include deeper"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tadhe = kenal (can include deeper meaning of know)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dènge sab'a èra ho madhutu dad'èi Na.&gt;<bt>and work strongly to follow His will/ways.'</bt><note reference="12:29-30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 6:4-5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Aa lii paredha ka dua peka na:<bt>And the second command says:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Èu hud'i sue ku dhèu leo, sama sèmi èu sue ngi'u èu unu mu.&gt;<bt>'You(sg) must love/pity other people, just like you love/pity yourself.'</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dua paredha se'e ka dhu hua iia risi. Abhu heka lii paredha leo dhu risi eele nèti dua paredha se'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>These two commands are the most important (loan). There are no other commands which are better/more important than these two commands."</bt><note reference="12:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 19:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ka mese agama èèna b'ala hari, peka na, &lt;&lt;Tare'a! Ama ku peka lèke kèna. Te Ama Lamatua j'aj'i Kètu èdhi. Lamatua leo aad'o.<bt>And the teacher of religion responded again saying, "True! Father has spoken correctly/appropriately. God is our(inc) lord/master. There is no other Lord.</bt><note reference="12:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 4:35</note><v n="33" />Èdhi hud'i sue risi Ne, toke d'ara d'èi ho pa'èci dènge Ne, tadhe mèu Ne, dènge sab'a èra ho madhutu dad'èi Na. Èdhi hud'i sue dhèu leo kahèi sama sèmi èdhi sue ngi'u èdhi unu ti. Lamatua d'èi risi eele tatao sèmi èèna, nèti èdhi madhutu dhodhoka atora agama di. Tatao sèmi èèna be'a risi, nèti èdhi tèti badha ho lati tunu hia Lamatua, do tèti mèdha leo hia Ne.&gt;&gt;<bt>We must love Him more, to desire to be together with Him, know2 Him and Wrok hard to follow His will/ways. We also must love other people like we love ourselves. God is happier with that, than if we just only follow the regulations of religion. Doing that is better than if we take an animal to go burn give it to God2, or take other things [and] give them to Him."</bt><note reference="12:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 6:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ropa Yesus nanene nare dhèu ne dhaa sèmi èèna, ka Na pangee, na, mese agama ne ne'a dènge be'a le. Hèia Yesus peka na, &lt;&lt;Èu oe j'aj'i unu Ama Lamatua kèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus heard what the aforementioned man answered in that way, Yesus thought this teacher of religion already understood well. So Yesus said, "You are almost becoming owned by God." (=almost one of God's people).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Èle èèna ka, dhèu leo sèra bani heka pakarèi dènge Yesus, lula dhèu èci sa segi boe Ne.<bt>After that, other people were no longer bold to debate Yesus, because not one person could compete with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="segi = tanding"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">segi = tanding</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:28-34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:25-28</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus èèna, ana-èpu dhèu aae Daud, te ngaa Nèngu lamatua Daud kahèi<bt>Kristus, is a descendent of King Daud, but He is also Daud's lord/master</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:41-46; Lukas 20:41-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus aj'a dhèu ae sèra ètu Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i era. Ka Na karèi si, peka na, &lt;&lt;Madhutu ngangee miu, na, tasamia? Mese agama sèra aj'a, peka na, Kristus èèna dhu Lamatua paj'uj'u nèti uru ka mai. Madhutu ngangee rèngu, na, Kristus èèna dhoka ana-èpu Daud. Te ngaa a'aj'a sèmi èèna d'ai lèke mèu mèka.<bt>After that, Yesus continued teaching many people there in the *Temple. And He asked them, saying, "Following your(PL) thinking, how is it? Teachers of religion teach that Kristus is the person that God2 designated from long ago. According to their thinking, that Kristus is only Daud's descendent. But, that teaching is not.yet target.</bt><v n="36" />Lula, nèti uru ka mai, Roh Ama Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci pake Daud ho suri, peka na,<bt>Because from long ago, the *Holy Spirit of God used Daud to write saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="era = masih; lèke boe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">era = masih; lèke boe = sonde kena</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ama Lamatua peka le mi lamatua ja'a, na,<bt>'God has said to my lord/master,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Mai ho madhèdi mi era dhu hua iia, re bab'oa g'ana Ja'a.<bt>"Come and sit here in the respected/best place, right at my right side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Pe èèna na Ja'a tao musu èu pahaha iisi, toke ra bisa boe ded'e kètu mi èu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Later, I will make your enemy/ies lower themselves (also = humble) to where they can't lift their head to you."'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pacud'u = tunduk (bow head); rodo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pacud'u = tunduk (bow head); rodo kakara toke dai rai = (lit. merayap dgn dada di tanah) = takluk sepenuhnya; ma dedha = terhadap</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37a" />De èdhi te'a, na, dhèu aae Daud paroa Kristus èèna, peka na, &lt;Lamatua&gt; na. Nèti èèna ka, ladhe dhèu sèra peka, na, Kristus èèna dhoka ana-èpu Daud di, èèna d'ai mèka. Lula Nèngu èèna j'aj'i lamatua nèti Daud kahèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>So King Daud called Kristus his lord/master. Because of that, people who say that Kristus is only just the descendent of Daud, that is clearly not enough. Because He is also Daud's lord/master."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="De = Jadi, (but homophonous with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">De = Jadi, (but homophonous with a vulgar Rote word referring to intercourse)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus peka na, pajiko paie mese agama dhu kapod'e-kabèli sèra<bt>Yesus says to be really careful with the teachers of religion who are devious (coll)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 23:1-36; Lukas 20:45-47)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37b" />Ropa Yesus peka nare sèmi èèna, dhèu ae sèra d'èi titu kèna nanene Ne.<bt>When Yesus had said (what He had just said), many people (coll) wanted to listen to Him.</bt><v n="38" />Ka Yesus peka hari si, &lt;&lt;Miu hud'i pajiko paie ku mese agama. Rèngu d'èi pasia pake kodho madhera d'ai rai, lasi paraga dènge dhèu ae, sèna ka dhèu dhu rèdhi rèngu sèra, koa si, peka na, &lt;Ladhe ku laa! Dhèu sèra, dhèu kapai!&gt;<bt>And Yesus spoke to them again, "You(PL) must be really careful of these teachers of religion. They want to stroll around wearing clothes that are so long they touch the ground, [to] go meet with many people so people can see them and praise them saying, 'Take a look at this! Those people, are important people!'</bt><v n="39" />Ladhe sèmi rèngu maso asa èmu manèngi-mangaj'i, do lasi ra'a-sisi, ra tenge era madhèdi dhu be'a risi, sèna ka dhèu ae rèdhi si.<bt>Similarly when they enter a house of worship, or go to a feast, they look for the best/most important place to sit, so that many people can see them.</bt><v n="40" />De hua iia mi pajiko paie! Rèngu kapod'e-kabèli bhèni balu ho parame rare èmu bhèni balu sèra. Te ngaa ètu madha dhèu ae, rèngu pahuni bhabhelu ra sèra dènge j'ara titu ho sabaj'a pamadhera aae, sèna ka dhèu peka na, rèngu se dhèu mola. Te ngaa limuri mai, na, Ama Lamatua hia huku dhu bia risi asa rèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>So it would be good to be really careful! They twist (=deceive) female widows to rob away the houses of those widows. But in front of many people, they hide their evil and stand there making really long prayers. But eventually God will punish them really heavily."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pajiko paie = perhatikan secara awas;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pajiko paie = perhatikan secara awas; <span class="Bold">39:</span> re madha = place of honour facing dhèu ae, terkemuka; be'a risi = broader; <span class="Bold">40:</span> hua iia = 1) terhormat, 2) lebih baik... 3) mulia ; katange ; pahutu ; katanga = alat makan dari daun lontar, anyaman (like woven plate for paper plate)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bhèni balu hia doi kolete dhu ae risi<bt>A female widow gives collection (loan) money which is more</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 21:1-4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus la'e madhèdi patangara dènge boaraka derma ètu Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i. Na ladhe dhèu mai pamaso doi kolete asa d'ara boaraka èèna. Ka Na ladhe dhèu kaja sèra parèu doi ae.<bt>After that, Yesus went and sat facing the derma (loan-the box at church doors in which to put special offerings) container at the *Temple. He watched people enter who put in their collection money into that container. And He saw rich people (coll) dropping.in lots of money.</bt><v n="42" />Te ngaa abhu bhèni balu èci dhu dènge boe ngaa-ngaa èci sa mai manèngi-mangaj'i, ka na pamaso dua doi asa d'ara boaraka èèna. Dua doi dhu na pamaso èèna, kab'ua ciki ood'e di.<bt>But there was a female widow who didn't have anything at all came to worship, and she entered two moneys into that container. The two moneys that she put in had hardly any value.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boraka derma ; kapepe = boraka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">boraka derma ; kapepe = boraka anyaman dari daun; ana kapepe = dompet yg dianyam dari daun; boraka ~ boaraka; <span class="Bold">42:</span> ciki ood'e-ood'e / ciki o'e-o'e ; be = short form from boe; parao</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus gape ana madhutu Na, ka Na peka, &lt;&lt;Mi ladhe ku bhèni balu dhu dènge boe ngaa-ngaa nèi. Na pamaso dhoka dua doi di, te ngaa nèngu hia risi eele nèti dhèu leo sèra.<bt>After that, Yesus hand.summoned His followers, and He said, "Take a look at that female widow who doesn't have anything at all. She has just put in only two moneys, but she has given more that the other people.</bt><v n="44" />Dhèu leo sèra hia kolete nèti doi sisa rèngu. Te ngaa bhèni balu ne hia aa'i mèu-mèu doi nèngu asa Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>The other people give church.collection from their extra money. But this female widow gave completely all of her money to God2."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gape = same as KM; madha"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">gape = same as KM; madha panyau; <span class="Bold">44:</span> mèu-mèu = semua-semua</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus peka mema, na, bèli-camèd'a Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i guri eele<bt>Yesus speaks directly that in the future the *Temple will come apart/fall down</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:1-2; Lukas 21:5-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na sèra kalua nèti d'ara Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i. Ropa rèngu d'ai li'u, hèia ana madhutu Na èci paj'uj'u asa Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i, ka na peka, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ladhe ku Èmu ne'e! Ra tao rare, saraga bia. Ra pagod'o rare hadhu sèra, mera titu kèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus and His followers went out from the *Temple. When they arrived outside then, one of His followers pointed at the *Temple, and said to Yesus, "Father! Look at this House/Building here! They made it really nice/beautiful. They stacked those stones, really neatly!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pagod'o = susun berlapis-lapis; baris satu-satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pagod'o = susun berlapis-lapis; baris satu-satu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Èmu ne mema saraga titu kèna! Te nèbhu heka, dhèu paguri eele ne. Ka hadhu-hadhu sèra, èci sa pamadhèdi heka ètu dedha èci.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus answered/responded, "This House, is certainly very beautiful! But3 in not much more time, people will make it collapse. And those stones, not one will still be sitting on top of another."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tadha-tadha èle rai-haha<bt>Various signs of the end of the world</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:3-14; Lukas 21:7-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus si lasi asa ledhe Saitun, ka Na madhèdi ètu era dhu patangara dènge Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i. Hèia Petrus, Yakobis, Yohanis dènge Anderias mai padhai lii dènge Yesus.<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) went to the Saitun (=olive) mountain/hill, and He sat in a place facing the *Temple. Then Petrus, Yakobis, Yohanis and Anderias came to speak with Yesus.</bt><v n="4" />Ra karèi, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Lole hari ku, lii dhu Ama ku peka dènge ji'i deo na. Lod'o mia sèra sa j'aj'i? Aa tadha-tadha na, samia?&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked, saying, "Father! Tell [us] again, the words that Father just now said to us(exc). Which day(s) will those happen? And how are the various signs?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ha = Aa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ha = Aa</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Sad'i miu pajiko paie-iie, sèna ka baku lèke tipu.<bt>So then Yesus answered, saying, "As long as you are really-really careful, you should not get tricked/deceived2.</bt><v n="6" />Te ladhe èèna na, dhèu ae mai tèb'a kakara, ho ra peka na, &lt;Ja'a ne Kristus, Dhèu dhu Ama Lamatua moa nèti uru ka mai.&gt; Aa ra leko-monya dhèu ae.<bt>Cause when that [happens], many people will come thumping their chest, to say, 'I here am Kristus, the person who God promised from long ago.' And they will con many people.</bt><v n="7" />Ladhe miu mèdhi dhèu pamusu, do tadèngi lii lolo dhèu papara-pakèj'i dènge pakasiro ètu mia-mia, miu baku madha'u kahèi. Sèra sa hud'i j'aj'i uuru ku. Te ngaa lod'o èle rai-haha èèna dhae d'ai mèka.<bt>When you see people warring/being enemies to each other, or hear telling of people slashing-stabbing [doublet] and shooting each other everywhere, be careful that you not be afraid also. Those things must be like that first. But the day of the end of the world has not yet arriived.</bt><v n="8" />Dhèu nèti ca suku mai pamusu dènge suku leo, rai èci mai pamusu dènge rai leo. Ètu mia-mia, j'aj'i rai opo dènge kabake-manganga. Sèra sa j'aj'i tadha sama sèmi dhèu bhèni èci dhu kabake pèd'a neo nara iisi.<bt>People from one tribe, come and war with a different tribe, and one region comes and wars with another region. All over the place are earthquakes and famine [doublet]. Those things are signs, just like a woman whose abdomen is in pain wanting to give birth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="papara-pakèj'i = baku bunuh pake parang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">papara-pakèj'i = baku bunuh pake parang, keris; <span class="Bold">8:</span> neo nara iisi = about to give birth</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />De hua iia, na, miu mage-mage! Te èèna na dhèu mai kèpa miu, ho ra nuni asa dhèu paredha agama dhu pama'ète lii agama. Aa ra game miu ètu d'ara èmu-èmu manèngi-mangaj'i. Ho èèna na rèti miu asa madha dhèu dhu dènge koasa, lula miu madhutu Ja'a. Te ngaa be'a kahèi, ne'e ne miu abhu tebho ho peka kolongara Ja'a mi rèngu.<bt>So it's best that you(PL) be watchful/wary! Cause then people will come and arrest you, to drag you to those who govern religion who decide religious court.cases. And they will beat you inside the houses of worship. And the will take you in front of those who hold power, because4 you follow Me. But that's also good, cause this way you get an opportunity to tell My name/raputation to them.</bt><v n="10" />Te dhèu unu Ama Lamatua hud'i lasi uuru ku lole Lii Lolo Be'a Ja'a mi suku aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne, heka lod'o èle rai-haha ne d'ai kèna.<bt>Cause God's people will go first to tell My Story which is Good to all the tribes/clans on this earth, before the day of the end of the world arrives.</bt><v n="11" />Sanèd'e, ee! Ladhe ra èki rèti miu asa era pama'ète lii langu, miu baku madha'u, peka na, &lt;Èèna na ja'a neo padhai lii ngaa? Do, ja'a neo dhaa ngaa?&gt; Ladhe d'ai lod'o èèna, miu padhai lii madhutu ngaa dhu Roh Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua peka dènge miu.<bt>Remember, ee! When they arrest [and] tie you, to take you to the place where they decide cases, don't be afraid what you will answer/respond. When the day/time arrives for you to speak, you will say what the Spirit of God tells you to say. What you say then are not your words alone, but they come from the Holy Spirit of God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parisa; |b10:|r"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">parisa; <span class="Bold">10:</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ara = kesempatan?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">j'ara = kesempatan?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ladhe Lii Hua Iia nèti Ama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ladhe Lii Hua Iia nèti Ama Lamatua na, ra peka dènge suku aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne'e, na lod'o èle rai-haha na, heka dai kèna.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sanèd'e, ee! Ladhe ra kèpa èki miu, ho rèti asa era dhu pama'ète lii langu, baku madha'u lii ngaa dhu miu dhaa. Ladhe d'ai lod'o ho neo padhai lii, mi peka ngaa dhu Roh Ama Lamatua pua miu padhai lii. Lii padhai lii dhu miu peka èèna, nèti boe miu mesa mi, na, te ngaa na mai nèti Roh Ama Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci."><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-11-24 02:45:56Z" status="Anyone">OV</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:9-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:17-20, Lukas 12:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ètu d'ara èmu cue, ladhe abhu dhèu dhu parcaya Ja'a, èèna na a'ari nèngu tenge j'ara ho pamadhe ne. Sèmi èèna kahèi, ladhe abhu ana dhu parcaya Ja'a, èèna na ama d'èlu na tenge j'ara ho pamadhe ne. Sèmi èèna kahèi, ladhe abhu ina-ama dhu parcaya Ja'a, èèna na ana d'èlu rèngu tenge j'ara ho pamadhe si.<bt>In one house, if there is a person who believes in Me, you will see that his/her older-younger siblings (or kin) look for ways to kill him/her. In the same way also, if there is a father who believes in Me, his child will look for ways to kill him. In the same way also, if there is an offspring who believes in Me, his/her father and mother will look for ways to kill him/her.</bt><v n="13" />De èèna na, dhèu d'èi boe miu, taga miu madhutu Ja'a. Te ngaa dhèu cee dhu bisa taha toke d'ai èle lod'o èèna, tatu Ama Lamatua hia mamuri mi nèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>When it's like that, people will not like you(PL), because4 you follow Me. But whoever can endure until the end of days, s/he will get life with God."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="?? save here?; UNS equated this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">?? save here?; UNS equated this use of mamuri with 'salamat'.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mamuri-manèro = long life"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mamuri-manèro = long life</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:22</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">J'aga mamuri miu, te lod'o èle rai-haha dètu le [\s2]<bt>You(PL) guard/watch your lives, cause the day of the end of the world is already near</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:15-28; Lukas 21:20-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Yesus tuhu hari lii padhai Na, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èèna na, abhu dhèu èci dhu bhelu-katub'a risi eele mai. Ho na mai maso ka titu ètu era laluri ètu d'ara Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i, dhu madhutu iia-iia na, nèngu bisa boe ètu era èèna, ho na pahera era èèna. Nèti èèna ka, Ama Lamatua tèke eele era èèna. Ladhe miu mèdhi le sèmi èèna, na, mi pajiko paie-iie! (Cee dhu baca lii ne'e, pajiko paie kahèi!) Èèna j'aj'i mi tadha, peka na, lod'o-lod'o j'aj'èra, dètu ae le. Ladhe mèdhi sèmi èèna, na, dhèu-dhèu ètu propensi Yudea lega-rai asa kolo ledhe lasi.<bt>Yesus spoke again, saying, "You(PL) will see, a Person who it More than Evil. And he will come enter and stand in the borbidden/taboo place in the *Temple, which according to what is right, he cannot be in that place to defile it. Because of that God will no longer care about that place. When you see like that, you must be really careful, ee! (Whoever reads these words, must also be really careful!) That will be a sign which says the days of difficulty/suffering are already near. When you see like that, people in the province of Yudea should flee [doublet] to the top of the mountain.</bt><note reference="13:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 9:27, 11:31, 12:11</note><v n="15" />Rèngu hud'i rai pamèri-mèri, sèna ka baku abhu j'aj'èra. Ladhe dhèu mai le asa li'u, lèpa ia ka rare mèdha asa d'ara èmu.<bt>You must run quickly, so that you do not encounter difficulty. Whoever has gone out (of their house), should not go back to retrieve things from inside the house.</bt><v n="16" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, dhèu ètu d'ara oka, baku lèpa èmu rare mèdha-papake.<bt>In the same way, people in the fields, should not return home to retrieve their clothes.</bt><note reference="13:15-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 17:31</note><v n="17" />Dhu j'èra risi, dhèu bhèni dhu dènge babia, dènge ina dhu pasusu ana rara iisi hiu, lula rèngu rai rare boe.<bt>What is worse, are women who are pregnant, and mothers who are nursing newborn babies, cause they can't run well.</bt><v n="18" />De hua iia risi miu sabaj'a, sèna ka lod'o j'aj'èra sèra baku lèke dènge hèru èj'i lai.<bt>So it's better that you pray2, so that on that aforementioned day of difficulty, you do not get it/encounter it during rainy season [CHECK, if UNS's don't answer "cause then it's cold and wet", perhaps we should add the phrase "when it's wet (and miserable)"].</bt><v n="19" />Te j'aj'èra lod'o èèna, bia titu kèna! Mulai nèti Ama Lamatua tao rai-haha, toke d'ai sange ne'e, dhèu rèdhi mèka j'aj'èra dhu bia sèmi èèna. J'aj'èra bia sèmi èèna, lod'o limuri, j'aj'i heka hari.<bt>Cause that day of difficulty is really heavy! Beginning (assimilated loan) from when God created/made the earth, until now, people have not.yet seen suffering as heavy as that. Heavy suffering like that, will not happen again afterwards.</bt><note reference="13:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 12:1, Rai-haha Rupa Hiu 7:14</note><v n="20" />Ladhe Ama Lamatua pab'ab'e boe lod'o j'aj'èra sèra, abhu boe dhèu èci sa dhu mamuri. Te ngaa, taga Ama Lamatua sue dhèu dhu Na hag'e nare sèra, ka Na pab'ab'e lod'o-lod'o j'aj'èra sèra.<bt>If God does not make.short that day of suffering, there is not even one single person who could/would live. But because4 God loves/pities the people who He chose out (coll), He makes.short those days [here it's a singular deictic with a reduplicated 'day', indicating a variety or period seen as a unit.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhu madhutu iia na, = yg"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhu madhutu iia na, = yg biasanya; soro kabodho = membelakangi; <span class="Bold">15:</span> mai le sa li'u = kalua nèti dara èmu na; <span class="Bold">17:</span> dhèu bhèni dhu dènge babia = hamil; ana rara iisi hiu = yg baru dilahirkan; mera (IRR) &lt; mere (R); rara (IRR) &lt; rare (R); <span class="Bold">18:</span> hèru èj'i lai = musim hujan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ladhe lod'o d'ai na, miu tadèngi dhèu mai peka, aku rèngu na, &lt;Ladhe ku! Kristus ètu ne'e!&gt; Aa dhèu leo hari peka, aku rèngu na, &lt;Aad'o! Kristus ètu nèi!&gt; Miu baku nanene kahèi!<bt>When that day/time arrives, you(PL) will here people come saying, saying2, 'Kristus is now here!' And other people will say instead, saying, 'No! Kristus is over there!' Be careful that you not listen to them as well!</bt><v n="22" />Te ladhe èèna na, dhèu mai ho tèb'a kakara, peka na, &lt;Ja'a ne, Kristus!&gt; Aa cahag'e hari peka na, &lt;Ja'a ne, dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua.&gt; Èèna na ra tao tadha malaa ae-ae dènge koasa nidhu, ho kapod'e-kabèli dhèu. Rèngu patangi-tenge j'ara sèna ka dhèu unu Ama Lamatua lèke tipu kahèi!<bt>Cause when that [happens], people will come thumping their chests, saying, 'I here, and Kristus!' And some others again, saying, 'I here, am God's *spokesperson.' Then they will make many amazing signs with the power of evil.spirits, to deceive people. It's almost as if God's people might even get deceived!</bt><v n="23" />Nèti èèna ka, miu pajiko paie-iie! Mema lod'o j'aj'èra bia èèna d'ai mèka, te ngaa Ja'a pasanèd'e uuru miu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, you must be really careful! It is true that those heavy days of suffering have not yet arrived, but I have already reminded (=warned) you first!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mamai Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a [\s2]<bt>The coming of the Child of Humans</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:29-31; Lukas 21:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus peka hari dènge ana madhutu Na sèra, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe èle lod'o j'aj'èra sèra, na,<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again with His followers, saying, "When those days of suffering are over,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Madha lod'o j'aj'i maroga,<bt>'The sun will become dark,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa hèru heo heka.<bt>and the moon will no longer shine.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Madha lodo = matahari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Madha lodo = matahari</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 13:10, Yeskial 32:7, Yoel 2:10, 31, 3:15, Rai-haha Rupa Hiu 6:12</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="25" />Hua hètu-hua hètu bèbha nèti dedha-liru mai,<bt>The stars [+variety] will fall from the sky above,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa koasa-koasa ètu dedha-liru j'aj'i kaco-balo.&gt;<bt>In the same way, the various.powers of the sky above, will become chaotic (assimilated loan).</bt><note reference="13:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 34:4, Yoel 2:10, Rai-haha Rupa Hiu 6:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Èle èèna, heka dhèu ladhe rèdhi Ja'a, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a ne. Èèna na Ja'a mai dènge ra'i-liru nèti dedha. Hèia dhèu aa'i-aa'i ladhe rèdhi a'èra dènge dadedha Ja'a.<bt>After that, only.then will people see Me, this Child of Humans. Then I will come from the sky above. At that time every person will see My strength/power2 and my glory/goodness which is great.</bt><note reference="13:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13, Rai-haha Rupa Hiu 1:7</note><v n="27" />Ka Ja'a paredha ana pajuu Ama Lamatua nèti sorga, ho puru lasi oru-kaboko dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu Ja'a hag'e kore nèti mia-mia ètu rai-haha ne; nèti suu haa d'ai suu dhimu, nèti suu badae toke d'ai suu balèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>And I command God's servants from heaven2 (=angels) to descend [and] choose-gather all the people who I have separated out from everywhere on this earth-below; from the western tip until the eastern tip, from and northern tip al the way to the southern tip.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hua iia = glory; |b27:|r nètit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hua iia = glory; <span class="Bold">27:</span> nètit su rai-raii nèti haa, nèti dhimu, ; suu = ujung; badae = north (dae = darat); balèu = selatan (lèu = laut); oru = choose; <span class="Bold">27:</span> 5 Januari 2000</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lod'o-lod'o j'aj'èra, j'aj'i tadha mamai Lamatua Yesus [\s2]<bt>The days of suffering, are/become a sign for the coming of Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:32-35; Lukas 21:29-33)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus tuhu hari lii padhai Na, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a kore upama nèti ana aaj'u. Ladhe rèu na mulai karara, èèna tadha hèru hadhu dètu le!<bt>I take an example like a tree. When leaves begin to turn yellow, that is a sign that dry season (lit. rock season) is already near!</bt><v n="29" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, ladhe miu mèdhi lod'o-lod'o j'aj'èra sèra j'aj'i, sama sèmi lii peka Ja'a deo na, èèna j'aj'i mi tadha, peka na, mamai Ja'a dètu ae le.<bt>In the same way, when you(PL) see those days of suffering happening, just like I just said, that become a sign saying, My coming is already really near.</bt><v n="30" />Ne'e ne Ja'a peka dènge miu kèna! Nèti dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu mamuri se, èèna na abhu cahag'e dhu dhae madhe mèka, te lod'o-lod'o dhu pènu dènge j'aj'èra na d'ai le.<bt>Now, I have already told you about it! From all the people who are living now, some will not.yet die, but3 the days that are full of suffering will have already arrived.</bt><v n="31" />Masi ka liru dènge rai-haha ne ele, te ngaa lii holo-nori Ja'a ele boe, toke d'ai mia-mia la'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even.though this sky/heaven and earth disappear, but My Words/Sayings will not disappear no matter what happens (lit. until to whereever).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabucu-kabucu ; hèru hadhu = musim"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kabucu-kabucu ; hèru hadhu = musim panas (only see rocks); <span class="Bold">29:</span> use of ae here;; <span class="Bold">31:</span> masi ka = biarpun</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu èci sa re'a boe lod'o mamai Yesus [\s2]<bt>That day of Yesus coming, not even one person really knows</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:36-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yesus tuhu hari lii, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu èci sa re'a boe lod'o do jam dhu Ja'a mai hari. Ana pajuu Ama Lamatua ètu sorga sèra re'a boe kahèi. Ja'a mesa ku, ke'a boe kahèi. Dhoka Ama Ku mesa Na di, dhu ne'a.<bt>Not even one person knows the day or the hour (loan) when I come again. The servants of God in heaven2 (coll) even, they also don't know. Even I don't know either. [It is] only just My Father alone, who knows.</bt><note reference="13:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:36</note><v n="33" />Nèti èèna ka, miu aa'i-aa'i mi hud'i pajiko paie, lula miu me'a boe lod'o d'ai na.<bt>Because of that, all of you must be really careful, because the day/time arrives [when] you do not know.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Nèbhu heka, Ja'a laku tèke eele miu kèna, te ngaa èèna na Ja'a mai hari. Sama sèmi dhèu dhu la'e tèke eele èmu nèngu, ho la'e asa rai kaj'èu. Na pua ana-ana nèngu j'aga paie èmu. Aa na bagi hia si sasab'a. Ka na paredha ana madhenga èmu, sèna ka na j'aga paie, toke d'ai nèngu lèpa hari.<bt>Not long [from now], but3 I will go leaving you behind, but then I will come again. It is like a person who goes leaving behind his house, to go to a land far away. He orders his underlings to guard the house well. And he divides up their work/responsibilities. And he commands the watchman, to guard well until he comes home again.</bt><note reference="13:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:36-38</note><v n="35" />Miu hud'i j'aga mèda-mèu kahèi, lula miu me'a boe lod'o mia Ja'a mai hari, sama sèmi ana madhenga èmu ne'a boe lod'o lamatua èmu na lèpa. Lèpa lod'o nihia, talora mèda, oe mèu, lod'o rea, do lod'o nètu; miu me'a boe jam èèna.<bt>Even you(PL) must also guard day and night, because you do not know which day/time I will return again, just like the watchman of the house didn't know when that master of the house returns.home. Returns home in the afternoon, the middle of the night, early morning [while still dark], when the sun comes up, or in the middle of the day; you do not know that hour.</bt><v n="36" />Mage dhoka na mai sahèka, te abhu miu dhu bhèj'i luu era.<bt>Be careful lest he come suddenly, but3 encounters you still sleeping soundly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="palalu eele miu = tinggalkan menjadi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">palalu eele miu = tinggalkan menjadi yatim-piatu; <span class="Bold">35:</span> loo nètu = tengah hari; oras = not known by younger.; <span class="Bold">36:</span> luu2 = air laut naik (rising tide)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />De, ngaa dhu Ja'a peka dènge miu ne'e, Ja'a peka lème dènge dhèu leo kahèi, &lt;Miu hud'i pajiko paie, ho mi soru mamai Ja'a.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So, what I have said to you now, I say to other people as well, 'You(PL) must be really careful, for you to receive My coming.'"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sèmi = sambut, terima"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sèmi = sambut, terima</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">[D'ai sange ne'e ka, Lamatua Yesus padhai lii lula-nèti lod'o-lod'o j'aj'èra dhèu rai-haha, dènge ana madhutu Na sèra ètu ledhe Saitun.]<bt>That's the limit of the Lord Yesus speaking about the days of suffering for humans on the earth-below, with His followers (coll), on the Saitun mountain.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu aae-dhèu kapai tenge j'ara ho kèpe Lamatua Yesus<bt>Important people (coll) quietly look for a way to arrest the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:1-5; Lukas 22:1-2; Yohanis 11:45-53)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1-2" />Èle èèna ka, kètu agama Yahudi dènge mese agama sèra tenge j'ara neo kèpe Yesus dènge mau-mau. Te rèngu neo pamadhe Ne. Te ngaa ètu d'ara padhue èèna, ra peka na, &lt;&lt;Taha ku! Baku parai kèpe Ne, lula lod'o kalela dètu le. Mage dhoka dhèu ae sèra patao dènge èdhi.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, the fathers of the Jahudi religion (coll) quietly looked for a way that they could arrest Yesus, cause they wanted to kill Him. In their recent discussions they were saying, "Hang on a minute! Don't be too quick/hasty to arrest Him, because the group.holiday is already near. [WWe need to] be careful of those many people, lest they do us(inc) in."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lodo be'a = hari raya;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">lodo be'a = hari raya;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Rèngu padhai lii sèmi èèna, lula dii dua lod'o ka, d'ai lod'o kalela dhèu Yahudi, dhu biasa ra peka na, &lt;Paska&gt; dènge &lt;Pesta Roti dhu pake boe Ragi&gt;. Kalela se pasanèd'e rèngu lod'o bèi-baki ra kalua nèti rai Masir.<bt>They spoke like that because in just two more days, [they would] arrive at the group.holiday of the Jahudi.people, which they often call 'Paska (=Easter/Passover) Day' and 'The Day of making bread which doesn't use yeast (assimilated loan)'. These feast days, remminded them of when their ancestors got out of the Masir (=Egypt) region.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhei dhua pèd'u = ragi atau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhei dhua pèd'u = ragi atau bibit roti (ampas laruh dari lontar) ; dii = sisa (waktu)</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 12:1-27</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bhèni dhu pasuti èi hèu mèngi dhu kab'ua mi Lamatua Yesus<bt>The woman who oiled.hair of the Lord Yesus, with the expensive aromatic oil</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:6-13; Yohanis 12:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ètu rae Betania, abhu ca dhèu ngara na Simon. Uru èèna, dhèu madenge dènge ne, lula nèngu pèd'a kusta. Te ngaa limuri ne, èle le nèti papèd'a na.<bt>In the village of Betania, was a person named Simon. Formerly, people were grossed.out with him, cause he had the kusta (leprosy) disease. But later on he had been healed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèia lod'o kalela dhae d'ai mèka, na, Yesus dènge ana madhutu Na sèra lasi ra'a-rinu ètu èmu Simon. Ètu talora ra'a-rinu era, dhèu bhèni èci mai paraga Yesus. Nèd'u dènge boto èci dhu ra tao nèti hadhu. Isi boto ne, èi hèu mèngi asli dhu kab'ua titu kèna, dhu ra tao nèti amo aaj'u hèu mèngi.<bt>[Since] the time was approaching for that holiday, Yesus and His followers (coll) went to eat-drink at Simon's house. While they were in the middle of eat-dringking, a woman came in front of Yesus. She was holding a bottle (assimilated loan), which was made out of stone. The contents of this bottle was aromatic oil which was very expensive, which they made from an aromatic tree root.</bt><note reference="14:3-5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kab'ua èi hèu mèngi ne, èci èèna ka dènge gaji tuka d'ara ca tèu. Alkitab lii Yunani peka na, èi hèu mèngi ne, kab'ua na 300 <span class="Italic">denari</span>. Aa ngara na <span class="Italic">nardos</span>, dhu uru èèna, dhèu tao nèti amo aaj'u hèu mèngi. Alkitab lii Idhonesia peka na &lt;narwastu&gt;. Aa boto èèna, tao nèti hadhu dhu bisa pae. Boto ne kab'ua kahèi. Alkitab lii Yunani peka na, boto ne, ra tao nèti hadhu, ngara na <span class="Italic">alabastros</span>. Alkitab lii Idhonesia peka na, ngara hadhu ne &lt;batu pualam&gt;. Ladhe kahèi ètu <span class="Italic">Lukas </span>7:37-38.<bt>The price of this aromatic oil, was the same as the wages of a tradesman for a year. The Bible in the Greek language says that this aromatic oil had a worth of 300 <span class="Italic">denarii</span>. And its name was <span class="Italic">nardos</span>, which long ago they made from an aromatic tree root. The Bible in the Indonesian language calls this 'narwastu'. And the bottle was made from a stone that they chiselled/carved. This bottle was also expensive. The Bible in the Greek language says that this bottle was made from stone called <span class="Italic">alabastros</span>. The Bible in the Indonesian language says that this stone was 'the pualam stone' (=1. marble, 2. alabaster). See also Lukas 7:37-38.</bt></note>Hèia bhèni ne pamae hèb'a boto èèna, ka na pasuti èi hèu mèngi mi kètu Yesus, ho j'aj'i mi tadha, peka na, nèngu pakab'ua Yesus.<bt>So this woman broke open the mouth of the aforementioned bottle, and she dripped out the aforementioned aromatic oil on the head of Yesus. That was a sign that she respect/appreciate/valued Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pae"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pae</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Te ngaa ètu èèna, abhu dhèu leo dhu ra'a-rinu pa'èci kahèi. Ropa dhèu se rèdhi dhèu bhèni ne tao sèmi èèna, hèia ra nasa. Ka ra padhai lii padedha iisi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ngaa ka unu bhèni nèi? Na bhori eele èi hèu mèngi kab'ua aae èèna!<bt>In that place, there were also several people who were eating-drinking with them. When these people saw that women do like that, they were angry. And they spoke arrogantly, saying, "What's with this woman that she does this? (Lit. what possesses that woman). She is pouring away that aromatic oil that is so expensive!</bt><v n="5" />Be'a risi nèngu pahie èi hèu mèngi èèna, ho la'e papala doi ae sèra, mi dhèu dhu dènge boe unu. Te kab'ua èi hèu mèngi ne, èci èèna ka dènge gaji tuka d'ara ca tèu.&gt;&gt; Hèia ra jèke bhèni ne.<bt>It's would be better that she sell that aromatic oil, to divide up its large price to the people who have nothing. Cause the price of this aromatic oil, was the same as the wages of a tradesman for a year." And they scolded her harshly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bhèni balu ana lalu dènge dhèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">bhèni balu ana lalu dènge dhèu sala; dhèu-sala = orang malarat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Te ngaa Yesus b'ala lii rèngu, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu baku pasusa bhèni ne! Hud'i laa! Ja'a karej'e lula nèngu pasuti le ngi'u Ja'a dènge èi hèu mèngi ne'e!<bt>But Yesus responded to what they were saying, saying2, "You(PL) shouldn't be making things difficult for this woman! Let her do what she is doing to/for Me! Cause I am even pleased, that she is rubbing My body with this aromatic oil!</bt><v n="7" />Dhèu kasia sèra, bèli-bèli ètu talora miu. De lod'o mia èèna ka dhu miu lake mere, na, miu bisa soru-bara si. Te ngaa nèbhu heka, Ja'a pa'èci heka dènge miu.<bt>People who have nothing are among you daily. At any time you have the chance to help them. But I cannot be together with you continually.</bt><note reference="14:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 15:11</note><v n="8" />Mamuri Ja'a nèbhu heka ètu rai-haha ne. Dènge tatao bhèni ne, nèngu lalau ngi'u Ja'a, sama sèmi nèngu pahèu mèngi mema ngi'u aae Ja'a, ho padhane.<bt>My life is not much longer on this earth. With what the woman has done, it's like she is urusing My body (arranging, taking care of), as if she is directly making.aromatic My body, for burying.</bt><v n="9" />Miu patadhe, ee! Èèna na, ladhe dhèu lole Lii Lolo Be'a Ama Lamatua ètu mia-mia, na, ra palolo kahèi tatao be'a bhèni ne'e. Sèna ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i sanèd'e nèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>You(PL) make note of this, ee! Wherever the Word of God is told by people, the good deed of this woman people wil tell continually, to be a remembering to her."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ngi'u = 1) badan, tubuh 2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ngi'u = 1) badan, tubuh 2) mayat; dhèu sala = lexicalised, meaning poor people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ètu mia-mia Lii Holo Nori Ama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ètu mia-mia Lii Holo Nori Ama Lamatua dhèu lole, tatao be'a dhèu bhèni ne'e dhèu palolo taruu, j'aj'i lii pasanèd'e ne.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yudas pane'a lii dènge dhèu ho pahie eele Lamatua Yesus<bt>Yudas agrees with people to sell off the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:14-16; Lukas 22:3-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Èle èèna ka, abhu ca dhèu nèti ana madhutu Yesus dhèu canguru dua sèra, ngara na Yudas Iskariot. Nèngu kalua la'e tenge kètu agama Yahudi sèra ho neo pahie Yesus mi rèngu. Ropa na paraga dènge rèngu, ka na peka naneo na.<bt>After that, Yudas Iskariot, a person of Yesus' 12 followers (coll), went to meet with the fathers of religion wanting to sell Yesus to those people. Arriving at them, he told them his intention/plan. [DISCOURSE: Last sentence required by RL discourse to transition from irrealis plan in vs. 10 to reaction in vs. 11.]</bt><v n="11" />Lod'o kètu agama sèra tadèngi naneo Yudas, ka ra karej'e titu kèna. Hèia ra jaji, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe èu neo pahie Yesus dènge ji'i, tatu ji'i b'ae.&gt;&gt; Hèia Yudas kalua, ka na mulai tenge j'ara ho pahie Yesus.<bt>When the bosses heard Yudas' talk like.that, then they were very extremely happy. And they promised saying, &lt;&lt;If you sell Yesus to us, surely we-e will pay.&gt;&gt; Then Yudas went.out, and he begain to seek a way(negatively valued) to sell Yesus to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapua = bal-balak, pertama-tama, pokok bahasa,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kapua = bal-balak, pertama-tama, pokok bahasa, induk, pokok, dasar (lahin)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dèi dènge lii padhue deo na,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dèi dènge lii padhue deo na, ka ra pama'ète neo hia Yudas doi. Nèti èèna ka, Yudas mulai tenge lod'o dhu mèci ho pahie Yesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus na'a kalela Paska dènge ana madhutu Na<bt>Yesus eats Paska (Passover) with His followers</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:17-25; Lukas 22:7-14, 21-23; Yohanis 13:21-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Lod'o èèna, lèke dènge lod'o partama nèti lod'o kalela dhèu Yahudi. De d'ara lod'o èèna, rèngu tema tunu roti dhu dènge boe ragi, aa roro kahib'i-kalèbho kahèi. Hèia ana madhutu Yesus sèra mai karèi Ne, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Doe ne'e ne, lod'o kalela Paska èdhi kèna. De Ama neo ji'i lalau era kalela Paska ètu mia?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, His followers (coll) came and asked Yesus, saying, "Father! Today is the day of celebrating Passover. Where does Father want us(exc) to prepare to serve the Paska holiday?" Cause that day, is on the most important holiday of the Jahudi people. Arriving at that day, they bake bread that doesn't have yeast, and they ritual.slaughter goats-sheep [doublet].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari madha = Monday, hari pertama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hari madha = Monday, hari pertama (from Dutch mandag = Monday); kalela = merayakan; lodo kalela Paska; raroro = gergaji; ra roro = mereka sembelih /r-horo/; kèj'i = tikam</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Èle èèna ka, ana madhutu Na"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Èle èèna ka, ana madhutu Na sèra mai karèi Yesus, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Deo ne'e ne, lod'o kalela Paska kèna. Ama neo ji'i lalau era kalela Paska ètu era mia?&gt;&gt; Te lod'o èèna, lèke dènge lod'o kalela dhu hua iia risi nèti dhèu Yahudi. Dai lod'o sèmi èèna, rèngu tunu roti dènge boe ragi, dènge roro kahib'i-kalèbho.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Hèia Yesus pua ana madhutu Na dhèu dua, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu lami uuru ku asa d'ara kota. Ètu nèi, miu paraga dènge dhèu mone èci, dhu pasae èi d'ara g'ala iiki cue. Lami madhutu ne nèti limuri.<bt>So Yesus ordered two of His followers, saying, "You go first into the city. There, you will meet a man, who is shoulder.carrying water in a small clay.pot. Follow him.</bt><v n="14" />Ladhe na maso asa èmu mia èèna ka, na, miu madhutu ne asa d'ara. Hèia miu peka mi lamatua èmu èèna, sèmi ne'e, &lt;Ama Mese ji'i manèngi kama èci, ho Na neo tao kalela Paska dènge ana madhutu Nèngu.&gt;<bt>When he enters into a house somewhere, you(PL) follow him into that house. To say to the master of that aforementioned house like this, "Our(exc) teacher requests a room, for Him to do Paska with His followers."</bt><v n="15" />Pe dhèu èèna paj'uj'u kama aae èci ètu èmu dedha na, dhu na sadia nare le. De miu dua mi dhoka lami lalau nganga'a di.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that person will designate a large room, in the house above (=upper floor), which is already prepared. So the two of you just need to go serve/prepare/arrange the food [and nothing else]."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Hèia dua ra lasi ka asa d'ara kota. D'ai nèi, rèngu rèdhi tare'a, sama sèmi ngaa dhu Yesus moa deo na. Ka ra sadia aa'i-aa'i, ho Yesus si ra'a kalela Paska ètu era èèna. Èle èèna ka, dua ra lasi paroa Yesus si.<bt>So the two of them went into the city. Arriving there, they saw that it was true, just like what Yesus had promised recently. And they prepared/arranged the food, so Yesus (coll) could eat Paska at that place. After that, the two of them went and summoned Yesus (coll).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ropa lod'o oe cèna, hèia Yesus dènge ana madhutu dhèu canguru dua sèra d'ai era èèna.<bt>When the sun was about to set, Yesus and the 12 followers arrived there.</bt><v n="18" />Ka ra madhèdi ra'a sama-sama. Ètu talora ra'a era, Yesus padhai lii dènge si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Miu nanene ku! Èèna na dhèu èci nèti miu se pahie eele Ja'a mi dhèu leo.&gt;&gt;<bt>So they sat and ate together. While they were eating, Yesus spoke to them saying, "You listen here! Tomorrow-next day one person from you here will sell Me off to other people."</bt><note reference="14:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 41:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ropa tadèngi lii èèna, ana madhutu Yesus sèra cag'ag'a dènge manyasa. Ka rèngu èci-èci mulai karèi Yesus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu Ama peka èèna, ja'a aad'o, sina ma?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they heard that, Yesus followers were surprised and regretful/grieved. And each one of them began to ask Yesus, "The person who Father was speaking about, it's not me, right?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu cèb'u roti palere-lere dènge Ja'a asa d'ara mago ne, nèngu ka dhu pahia Ja'a.<bt>So Yesus answered, "Who it was that dipped bread together with Me into this bowl, he is the one who will sell Me."</bt><v n="21" />Mi sanèd'e! Ja'a ne, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a. Ja'a hud'i madhe ku, sama sèmi dhu suri tèke le, ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua. Te ngaa kasia, dhèu dhu neo pahia Ja'a èèna, bèli-camèd'a nèngu dui nare pala na! Hua iia risi, ina na baku nara iisi ne!&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember, ee! I, the Childe of Humans, must die, just like what has already been written in the Writings of God. But it's a pity, for the person who wants to sell Me, in the future he will shoulder.carry his division (=just deserts). It is best that his mother didn't give birth to him!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="palere = sama-sama; cèbu = celup"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">palere = sama-sama; cèbu = celup</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus peka na, roti dènge èi anggor j'aj'i mi tadha ho èdhi sanèd'e Ne [\s2]<bt>Lord Yesus says, saying2, that bread and grape juice/wine, is a sign remembering Him [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:26-30; Lukas 22:14-20; 1 Korintus 11:23-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ropa rèngu ètu talora ra'a era, Yesus nare roti cue, hèia Na manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua. Ka Na pamae roti ne, hèia Na j'ole asa ana madhutu Na sèra. Ka Na peka na, &lt;&lt;Roti ne'e ne, ngi'u Ja'a kèna. Mere ho mi'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>While they were still in the middle of eating, Yesus took a unit of bread, and He requested thanks to God. And He broke it up, and He gave it stretching out his hand to His followers. And He said, "This bread here, is My body. You(PL)-take to eat."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mi'a/mi'e ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">mi'a/mi'e =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01803b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Èle èèna ka, Na nare galaa dhu isi dènge èi hua anggor. Na manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua kahèi. Ka Na j'ole galaa èèna asa ana madhutu Na, sèna ka rinu.<bt>After that, He-took a glass filled with juice of the anggor fruit. And He requested thanks to God. And He extended the aforementioned glass to His followers for them to drink.</bt><v n="24" />Hèia Na peka, &lt;&lt;Èi anggor ne'e ne, raa Ja'a kèna, dhu suti sèna ka hia mamuri mi dhèu ae. Raa ne, j'aj'i mi tadha ho pasanèd'e, peka na, ngaa dhu Ama Lamatua moa le èèna, limuri ne j'aj'i le tare'a. Mere ho minu ka!<bt>And He spoke like this, "This anggor juice here, is My blood, which is poured out/spilled out giving life for [BENEFACTIVE] many people. This blood here is a sign for remembering, saying that what God has promised, has now truly happened. Take to drink it!</bt><note reference="14:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 24:8, Yermia 31:31-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Mi sanèd'e paie! Nèti mèda ne'e ne, Ja'a kinu heka èi anggor. Toke d'ai Ja'a dènge Ama Ku ngèd'u paredha sama-sama ètu sorga, heka kinu hari kèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember well [=toward understanding]! From this night, I will no longer drink the juice of the anggor fruit. Until my Father in heaven2 sits in government, only.then will I-drink it again."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hia mamuri = kasi hidup; ma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hia mamuri = kasi hidup; ma dedha dhèu ae = bagi banyak orang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Èle èèna ka, ra sod'a lii sod'a èci, ho ra koa-kio kolongara Ama Lamatua. Ka mèda èèna kahèi, lasi dènge asa ledhe Saitun.<bt>After tha, they sang a song, and they praised the name2/reputation of God. And that night also, they went to the Saitun mountain.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus peka uuru, na, bèli-camèd'a Petrus pasili Nèngu<bt>The Lord Yesus says first (temporal), that in the future Petrus will deny.truth [saying] that he doesn't know2 Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:31-35; Lukas 22:31-34; Yohanis 13:36-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ètu d'ara kakako rèngu èèna, Yesus padhai lii, peka na, &lt;&lt;D'ara mèda ne'e ne, miu aa'i-aa'i mi rai tèke eele Ja'a mesa Ku. Sama sèmi dhu ra suri le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua, peka na,<bt>While they were journeying (=on the way) Yesus spoke saying, "Tonight, all of you will flee leaving Me alone. That's just as they have written, in the Writings of God saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Èèna na Ama Lamatua pamadhe ana madhenga badha,<bt>'Later on, God will kill the shepherd of the animals,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ka kahib'i-kalèbho na rai paj'ala asa haa, asa dhimu.&gt;<bt>and the flocks will disperse.in.all.directions to the west and to the east.'</bt><note reference="14:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 13:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Èèna na Ja'a madhe tare'a. Te ngaa lod'o Ja'a mamuri hari, Ja'a laku uru nèti miu asa propensi Galilea!&gt;&gt;<bt>So I will truly die, but then when I live again, I will go first from you(PL) to the province of Galilea!"</bt><note reference="14:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 28:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ka Petrus b'ala, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Masi ka dhèu leo rai eele Ama, te ngaa ja'a rai boe!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Petrus responded to Him, saying, "Father! Even if other people flee leaving Father behind, but I won't flee!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Hèia Yesus dhaa, &lt;&lt;Petrus! Mu patadhe! Mèda ne'e kahèi, manu kokotoo d'ai mèka dua hari, te ngaa èu pasili le Ja'a tèlu hari, peka na, èu tadhe boe Ja'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus answered/responded, "Petrus! Make note of this! Tonight also, the chicken will not.yet crow two times, but3 you(sg) will already have deny.truth Me three times, saying you do not know2 Me!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ka Petrus pajèka dènge Ne, peka na, &lt;&lt;Aad'o sèmi èèna, Ama! Ladhe Ama madhe, ja'a madhe dènge Ama kahèi. Te ngaa Ja'a pasili boe Ama, aa rai eele boe!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Petrus spoke.angrily with Him, saying, "It's not like that, Father! If Father dies, I will also even die with Father. I will not deny, and will not flee leaving behind Father either!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasili ; patiba ; patiba-pakara ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pasili ; patiba ; patiba-pakara = mutual formal agreement to not do s.t.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Angalai Petrus sèra lii èci èèna kahèi.<bt>Even Petrus' friends/companions (coll), spoke the same way.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus manèngi-mangaj'i ètu d'ara oka Getsemani<bt>The Lord Yesus prays in the field of Getsemani</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:36-46; Lukas 22:39-46)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Hèia Yesus si lasi d'ai d'ara oka cue ètu ledhe Saitun, ngara na &lt;Getsemani&gt;. D'ai èèna, hèia Yesus peka dènge ra, &lt;&lt;Miu madhèdi mate Ja'a mi ne'e. Ja'a neo laku manèngi-mangaj'i asa nèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>So then Yesus and His followers went until they arrived at a field, on the Saitun mountain, named 'Getsemani'. Arriving there, Yesus spoke to them, "You(PL) sit [and] wait for Me here. I'm going to pray over there."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ka Yesus gale nèti Petrus, Yakobis, dènge Yohanis lasi dènge Ne. Mulai nèti èèna ka, Na rasa d'ara Nèngu ma'ète laho mae-mae.<bt>And Yesus invited Petrus, Yakobis, and Yohanis to go with Him. Beginning from that time [CHECK if karèi or kèri here], He felt His insides to be really messed up (idiom).</bt><v n="34" />Hèia Na peka dènge ana madhutu Na sèra, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;D'ara Ja'a pèd'a titu kèna! Ja'a rasa sèmi oe madhe sa. Miu madhèdi mate mi ne'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He spoke to those followers of His, saying, "My insides are really sad! My insides are like they are almost dead. You sit [and] guard here."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dara ma'ète laho mae-mae sène ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dara ma'ète laho mae-mae sène = Ndao idiom; <span class="Bold">34:</span> dara pèdha = 1) sedih 2) angry (if Object); madhènga = implies watc hing or guarding something right there; mate = implies watching for s.t. that might come from outside; madhèdi madhènga = sit watching</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check dara pèdha"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">check dara pèdha</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01810b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35-36" />Hèia la'e ako kaj'èu ciki nèti era èèna, ka Na patitu kètu urutuu Na ètu rai, ka Na sabaj'a, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama pasue! Ladhe sèmi Ama d'èi, na, Ja'a baku pasae j'aj'èra ne'e d'ai madhe. Ja'a ke'a le, ètu madha Ama, abhu boe ngaa èci sa dhu Ama bisa boe tao. De ladhe bisa, na, Ama pakaj'èu eele babia ne'e nèti kabela-kao Ja'a. Masi ka sèmi èèna, baku madhutu dad'èi Ja'a; te ngaa hud'i madhutu dad'èi Ama Ku ka laa.&gt;&gt;<bt>So he went a short distance from that place, and He bowed His head down to the ground, and He prayed saying, "Father! If Father wants, I shouldn't shoulder.carry this difficulty/suffering to the point of dying. I know that before Father, there is nothing that Father is not able to do (idiom). Because of that, Father make.far.away this burden from My shoulder-blades. Even though it is like that, don't follow My will/desires, but3 it must be that just follow the will/desire my Father."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Hèia la'e ka, ako kaj'èu ciki"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Hèia la'e ka, ako kaj'èu ciki nèti era deo na, ka Na patitu kètu urutuu Na ètu rai, ka Na manèngi-mangaj'i peka na, "Oo, Ama! Ladhe sèmi Ama dèi, baku hia Ja'a pasae j'aj'èra ne'e. Ja'a ke'a, ètu madha Ama, nga èci sa dhu aad'o, dhu Ama abhu boe adu ue. Nèti èèna ka, Ama tao eele pakaj'èu j'aj'èra ne'e nèti kabela kao Ja'a. Te ngaa sèmi èèna o, baku ho dadèi dara Ja'a, te hud'i la, madhutu dadèi dara AmaKu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Èle èèna ka, Na lèpa asa ana madhutu Na, dhèu tèlu sèra, te ngaa ra bhèj'i luu. Hèia Na parèi si, ka Na padhai lii dènge Petrus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Petrus!<note reference="14:37" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;Simon&gt; ètu ne'e. Simon ne, ngara Petrus dhu leo.<bt>The Greek language Bible, writes, saying 'Simon' here. Simon is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>Èu bhèj'i, do? Ja'a nèbhu boe ètu nèi, te ngaa miu bisa boe beke mate Ja'a ciki sa!<bt>After that, He returned to His followers, those three people, but they were sleeping soundly. He woke them up, and He spoke to Petrus, saying, "He! Petrus! Are you asleep, oo? I'm over there for not long, but you(PL) can't stay.awake, waiting for me a little bit, ee!</bt><v n="38" />Kèd'i ho pamako musi madha èu. Kèd'i ka, ho beke dènge Ja'a! D'ara miu neo tao be'a kahèi, te ngaa ngi'u miu roe. De be'a risi miu sabaj'a, sèna ka ladhe miu lèke dadugu-rariu, miu baku manahu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Get up and clear up your eyeballs. Get up and stay.awake with Me! Your insides also want to do good, but your bodies are weak. Because of that, it is better for you to pray, so that if you encounter/get *temptation, you will win/overcome."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beke = mete, but doesn't have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">beke = mete, but doesn't have to be dead person; <span class="Bold">38:</span> pamèu ; mako = lunak (Ant = sakaa); lii dadugu rariu nidhu = godaan setan; segi = menang; dadugu rariu = temptation, usually implies some sort of external pressure, persuasion, etc. but can come from the situation itself (broader than lalai = heart drawn to do s.t.)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kèdi ho pamako musi madha èu."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Kèdi ho pamako musi madha èu. Kèdi ka, ho beke dènge Ja'a! Dara miu, neo kahèi ho tao be'a, te ngaa ngi'u miu roe. Nèti èèna ka, be'a risi miu manèngi-mangaj'i, sèna ka baku abhu lii dadugu rariu nidhu, sèna ka baku miu manahu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 10:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus la'e manèngi-mangaj'i ca tèka hari. Nèngu manèngi hari mi Ama Lamatua, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ladhe bisa, na, Ama pakaj'èu eele babia ne nèti Ja'a. Te ngaa hud'i madhutu dad'èi Ama Ku ka laa.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus went again to pray some. He requested again to God, saying, "Father! I ask/pray that if possible, take away this suffering from Me. But, it must that I just follow the desires/will of my Father.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ja'a manèngi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ja'a manèngi ho sèna ka, tao eele j'aj'èra ne'e nèti Ja'a. Te ngaa, hud'i la Ja'a madhutu dadèi Ama ku di.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ka Na lèpa hari asa era ana madhutu Na dhèu tèlu sèra. Te ngaa rèngu bhèj'i hari le, lula musi madha ra sakaa titu kèna. Hèia Na parèi hari si, te ngaa rèngu re'a boe dhaa sèmi ngaa mi Nèngu.<bt>And He returned again to the place of His three followers. But they were already sleeping again, because their eyeballs were really sleepy. So He woke them up again, but they didn't know what they should say to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="musi madha ra sakaa = mengantuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">musi madha ra sakaa = mengantuk sekali</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Hèia Yesus tèke eele si, ka la'e manèngi-mangaj'i d'ai tèlu hari kèna. Èle èèna ka, Na lèpa la'e parèi ana madhutu Na sèra. Na peka, &lt;&lt;Miu bhèj'i taruu era? Sange èèna ka laa! Kèd'i ka! Te dhèu dhu neo pahie Ja'a, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a ne, nuka mai dènge angalai nèngu sèra. Rèngu mai kèpe Ja'a, ho saraka mi dhèu bhelu-katub'a si.<bt>So Yesus left them behind, and went [and] prayed for the third time. After that, He returned and woke up His followers. He said, "You're still sleeping? Enough of that! Get up! Cause the person who sold Me, the Child of Humans has shown up with his companions (coll). They have come to arrest Me, to hand over [Me] to those evil people.</bt><v n="42" />Kèd'i ka! Pamako musi madha miu, ho ladhe ku asa nèi! Dhèu dhu neo pahie Ja'a ne, nuka mai nèi. Mai ho lati paraga dènge si!&gt;&gt;<bt>Get up! Clear up your eyeballs, so you can take a look over there! The person who wants to sell Me, is appearing here. Let's go meet him!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nuni-pa'oro = drag off,; |b42:|r pamarei"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">nuni-pa'oro = drag off,; <span class="Bold">42:</span> pamarei = buka mata; na/ni; soru = sambut (positive) ; nuka = sementara ; ni &lt; nèi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ra kèpe Yesus<bt>They arrest Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:47-56; Lukas 22:47-53; Yohanis 18:3-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ropa Yesus padhai lii era, hèia Yudas d'ai madha Yesus dènge dhèu ae titu kèna. Rèngu mai rèti dènge hela dènge cèki, ho kèpe Yesus. Dhèu se tao sèmi èèna, lula ra madhutu lii paredha nèti kètu agama Yahudi, mese agama, dènge dhèu heka-dhèu heka ad'a sèra.<bt>While Yesus was still speaking, suddenly Yudas arrived in front of Yesus with many people. They came bringing swords/machetes (generic) and carved.clubs (=shaped as clubs, not just sticks), to arrest Yesus. These people did this because they followed the commands of the fathers of religion, the teachers of religion and traditional elders.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cèki = kayu kudung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">cèki = kayu kudung</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Yudas hia mema tadha mi dhèu ae se, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe d'ai nèi, ja'a uu cee, na, Nèngu kèna. De mi kèpe Ne.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yudas had already given a sign to these many people, saying, "When we get there, whoever I kiss/sniff, He is is the one. So you(PL) arrest Him."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhèu heka-dhèu heka ad'a = tua-tua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhèu heka-dhèu heka ad'a = tua-tua adat; samala = fighting sword, long (one meter plus), thin, curved; cèki = club (already carved); samala iiki = short sword, but thin; hela = parang, swords, covers many types</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01812b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;verticalPosition:bottom">Yudas hia tadha, dènge na uu Yesus<bt>Yudas gives a sign, by kissing Yesus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ropa Yudas si d'ai era èèna, na la'e asa madha Yesus. Ka na lii, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama mese!&gt;&gt; Hèia na liku nare Yesus, ka na uu Ne.<bt>When Yudas (coll) arrived at that place, he went in front of Yesus, and he said, saying2, "Father teacher!" And he embraced Yesus, and he kissed Him.</bt><v n="46" />Hèia dhèu ae sèra ara asa madha Yesus, ka ra kèpe Ne.<bt>So those many people went in front of Yesus and they arrested Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Te ngaa ana madhutu Yesus èci bete hela na, ka na pare pama'ète rèu dhilu dhèu èci. Dhèu dhu nu'a ne, ènu nèti kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi.<bt>Suddenly one of Yesus followers withdrew his sword/machete, and he cut off the ear of a person. This wounded person, was the servant2 of the top important person of the Jahudi religion.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bete = cabut (parang) ; beke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">bete = cabut (parang) ; beke = mete</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Hèia Yesus peka dènge dhèu ae dhu mai kèpe Nèngu sèra, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Tasamia? Miu ngee, na, Ja'a ne dhèu bhelu, do? Ka miu mai kèpe Ja'a mèti hela dènge cèki?<bt>So then Yesus spoke to the many people who came to arrest Him (coll), saying, "How is it? Do you(PL) think that I here am an evil/bad person, or [what]? And you come arrest Me bringing swords and clubs?</bt><v n="49" />Bèli-bèli Ja'a aj'a miu ètu Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i, te ngaa miu èci sa kèpe boe Ja'a. Mai ka, kèpe Ja'a! Te j'ara ne j'aj'i sèmi dhu suri tèke le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>Every day, I taught you in the *Temple, but not even one of you arrested Me. So come on now, arrest Me. Cause this is the way, like what has been written in the Writings of God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="samala = long sword; pedang, kalewang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">samala = long sword; pedang, kalewang (anachronism); seru = sideways slash; pare = cut (off)</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:49" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 19:47, 21:37</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ana madhutu Yesus sèra madha'u titu kèna. Hèia ra rai tèke eele Yesus mesa Na ètu èèna.<bt>Yesus followers (coll) were terrified, and so they ran away leaving Him alone there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51-52" />Ètu era èèna, abhu ana mone ngèru èci kahèi dhu madhutu Yesus re limuri. Ana ne pahutu isi na dènge sig'i ca bèla. Dhèu sèra neo kèpe ne kahèi, ka na rai tèke eele sig'i na ètu kacui-aai dhèu sèra, lula na madha'u. Hèia na rai dènge boe mèdha-papake ètu ua na.<bt>At that place there was a young man following Yesus from behind. This child/underling had covered his body with a cloth/sarong. Suddenly those people grabbed him, and he ran away leaving behind his cloth in the hands of those people, because he was afraid. And he ran away without any clothes on his body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ka'ola = naked (vulgar, not uttered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ka'ola = naked (vulgar, not uttered in mixed company); na rai dènge boe mèdha papake ètu ngi'u na. ; ua = used in association with clothing and nakedness</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ra rèti Lamatua Yesus asa ama-ama j'ue lii langu agama Yahudi<bt>They take Yesus to the fathers who decide2 Jahudi religious court.cases</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:57-68; Lukas 22:54-55, 63-71; Yohanis 18:13-14, 19-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Èle èèna ka, ra rèti Yesus asa èmu kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi. Ètu èèna, dhèu kapai sèra pakaboko le. Rèngu sèra, nuka: kètu agama Yahudi, mese agama, dènge dhèu heka-dhèu heka ad'a sèra.<bt>After that, they took Yesus to the house of the most important person of the Jahudi religion. There those important people had already gathered. They were the fathers of religion, the teachers of religion, and the traditional elders of customary law.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Ropa ra kèpe rèti Yesus, Petrus madhutu mau-mau nèti limuri. Hèia na maso kahèi d'ai madha èmu kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi, ka na madhèdi manyiru ai sama-sama dènge dhèu j'aga ètu sèra.<bt>When they brought Yesus there, Petrus followed quietly from behind, and he also entered the yard of the house of that important person of the Jahudi religion, and he sat [and] warmed himself over the fire together with the people there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tua-tua ad'a (make consistent); kaba ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tua-tua ad'a (make consistent); kaba = tempurung, kulit; rai = tanah; dhèu kapai risi nèti agama Yahudi = high priest</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupjretwn: underling, servant, helper &quot;in all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z" status="Information">hupjretwn: underling, servant, helper "in all probability here the temple guard"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Ètu d'ara èmu èèna, kètu agama Yahudi sèra padhue dènge dhèu-dhèu dhu madhèdi j'ue lii langu agama. Ra patangi-tenge bukti ho pamanahu Yesus, lula ra neo pamadhe Ne. Te ngaa rèngu abhu boe bukti èci sa.<bt>Inside that house the fathers of the Jahudi religion (coll) discussed with the people who were sitting to decide the religious court.case. They were looking for proof (loan) to bring.down Yesus, because they wanted to kill Him. But they couldn't find even one proof.</bt><v n="56" />Ka ra paroa dhèu ae asa madha ho j'aj'i sakasii, sèna ka neo pabèbhe Yesus. Te ngaa lii sakasii rèngu sèra, èci dènge èci pamèci boe.<bt>And they summoned many people to the front to be court.witnesses (loan), to make Yesus fall. But2 the voice of those witnesses, not one matched what another one said.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pamèci = baku cocok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pamèci = baku cocok</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Abhu pèri-pèri dhèu sakasii leo dhu kèd'i titu, ka ra pakapod'e lii, peka na,<bt>There were other witness people, who stood up, and they twisted their words about Yesus, saying,</bt><v n="58" />&lt;&lt;Ji'i tadèngi dhèu ne'e peka na, &lt;Èèna na Ja'a paguri eele Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i dhu dhèu rai-haha tao dènge kacui-aai ra. Te ngaa èle tèlu lod'o ka, Ja'a patitu kore hari le Èmu èèna, dènge boe pake kacui-aai dhèu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>"We(exc) heard this person say, 'I will make.collapse the *Temple which human made with their hands. But in just three days, I will stand it up again, without using the hands of humans."</bt><note reference="14:58" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 2:19</note><v n="59" />Te ngaa lii lolo rèngu sèra èci dènge èci baka-leo hua.<bt>But, what each of them said was different from the others. (=no match).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èci dènge èci bakaleo hua ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">èci dènge èci bakaleo hua = Idiom 'satu dengan satu tidak saling cocok'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="60" />Hèia kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi èèna, kèd'i titu ètu talora dhèu ae dhu madhèdi ètu sèra. Ka na karèi Yesus, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu ae mai le galaa Èu. Nga tao ka Èu mau-mau, mo'o boe dhaa lii galaa sèra?&gt;&gt;<bt>So the top important person of the Jahudi religion, stood in the middle of those many people sitting there, and he asked Yesus, saying, "Many people have complained/accused You, why are You quiet, not wanting to respond to their accusations?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />Te ngaa Yesus mau-mau, lii boe ca hèb'a sa. Èle èèna ka, kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi ne, karèi hari Ne ca tèka, &lt;&lt;Èu peka ku laa! Tare'a-re'a Èu ne Kristus, Ana Ama Lamatua dhu Na moa nèti uuru èèna, do?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus remained silent, not saying one word. After that, the top important person of the Jahudi religion asked Him once again, "Tell us now! Are You truly the Kristus, the Child of God who He promised from long ago, or [what]?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="62" />Ka Yesus dhaa, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Mema tare'a sèmi èèna! Nèngu èèna ka, Ja'a ne! Bèli-camèd'a miu ladhe mèdhi Ja'a, Dhèu Rai-haha Tare'a-re'a ne, madhèdi re bab'oa g'ana Ama Lamatua ètu sorga. Koasa Nèngu kapai risi eele! Ladhe èèna na, Ja'a dènge Nèngu, ngèd'u paredha sama-sama. Èle èèna na, Ja'a puru mai nèti sorga dènge ra'i-liru.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus responded, saying, "It's really true like that! That one is Me here! In the future you(PL) will see Me, the Child of Humans, sitting there on the right side of God in heaven2. His power is incredibly great! When it's like that, I and He we(exc)-hold government together. After that, I will descend [and] come from heaven2, with a cloud/clouds."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ra'i liru = awan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ra'i liru = awan</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:62" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="63" />Ropa tadèngi nare lii padhai Yesus, kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi ne nasa titu kèna, hèia na ciu pamae kodho madhera ètu ua na. Ka na pajèka peka dènge dhèu-dhèu dhu madhèdi ètu sèra, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èdhi parluu heka sakasii!<bt>When he heard what Yesus had just said, this top important person of the Jahudi religion was furious, so.then he tore up his long clothes on his body, and he screamed speaking to the people sitting there (coll), saying, "We(inc) no longer need witnesses!</bt><v n="64" />Miu tadèngi le dènge ro'a dhilu miu, si? Nèngu unu Na ka dhu peka sèmi èèna! Nèngu padedha iisi Na, j'aj'i Ana Ama Lamatua. Lii ne'e ne, lii dhu pa'ele iie kolongara Ama Lamatua! Madhutu atora agama èdhi, dhèu dhu tao iisi na sama sèmi Ama Lamatua, dhèu èèna hud'i lèke huku madhe ku! De mi pama'ète tasamia?&gt;&gt;<bt>You here have already heard with your own ears, right? He himself3 has spoken like that! He elevates himself, to be the Child of God. These words, are words that slander the name2/reputation of God! According to the regulations of our(inc) religion, a person who makes himself2 the same as God, that person must get punished by death! So how do you decide2 about Him?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ua = badan (in connection with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ua = badan (in connection with clothes); ngi'u = badan, diri ; isi = badan, diri; Nèngu unu na ka = dia sendiri; mesa = sendiri @@; <span class="Bold">64:</span> lii dhu pa'ele iie kolongara (Ama Lamatua) = blaspheme, slander, hujat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèia rèngu aa'i-aa'i pama'ète, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu ne'e ne, tare'a-re'a sala! De Nèngu ne hud'i lèke huku pamadhe!&gt;&gt;<bt>So they decided, saying, "This person, is truly wrong! He here, must get punished by killing!"</bt><note reference="14:64" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 24:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="65" />Hèia pèri-pèri dhèu kèd'i lasi sabhuu ilu mi rèhu Yesus. Ra hutu musi madha Na, ka ra game Ne. Hèia ra karèi Ne, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe Èu j'aj'i dhèu mèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua, na, Èu peka sèku! Cee ka dhu j'ubhu Èu?&gt;&gt; Èle èèna ka, ra pua dhèu dhu madhenge Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i, ho mai pakako rèti Yesus. Ropa ra kako, ra tèb'e pa'oke Ne nèti haa, nèti dhimu.<bt>Suddenly several people got up and spit saliva on the face of Yesus. They covered His eyeballs, and they beat Him. And then they asked Him, saying, "You try and tell [us]! Who was it that punched you then? After that, they ordered people who guard the *Temple, to come and take Yesus off. When they went, they slapped him from the west and from the east.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèb'e = tampeleng ; tèbhe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">tèb'e = tampeleng ; tèbhe = tarompet (dari sejenis siput besar, atau dari tanduk kerbau) ; pa'oke = from all sides</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus pasili tèlu hari, peka na, nèngu tadhe boe Lamatua Yesus<bt>Petrus says three times, he doesn't know2 the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:69-75; Lukas 22:56-62; Yohanis 18:15-18, 25-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="66-67" />Mèda èèna, Petrus madhèdi era ètu madha èmu èèna. Hèia ènu dhèu bhèni èci nèti kètu kapai risi agama Yahudi, mai ka nèdhi Petrus madhèdi manyiru ai. Na ladhe kaloo ka rèhu Petrus, ka karèi, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Deo na èu sama-sama dènge Yesus, dhèu Nasaret èèna, si?&gt;&gt;<bt>That night, Petrus was still sitting there in the yard of that house. Suddenly a female servant2 of the important person of the Jahudi religion, came and saw Petrus sitting warming himself over the fire. She looked carefully at Petrus' face and asked, saying, "You here, were also together with Yesus, that Nasaret person (coll)?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manyiru ai = panggang badan; è'nu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">manyiru ai = panggang badan; è'nu = hamba ; kaloo = memperhatikan dengan cermat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="68" />Te ngaa Petrus dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Aad'o! Nga tao ka èu karèi sèmi èèna! Ja'a tadhe boe Dhèu èèna.&gt;&gt; Hèia Petrus kalua, ka la'e titu ètu hèb'a tedhe. [Kabèdhi laa, manu kokotoo.]<bt>And Petrus responded saying, "No! Why do you ask like that! I don't know2 that man." so then Petrus went out and sat at the gate of the fence. [Suddenly the chicken crowed.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kokotoo = berkokok (ayam)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kokotoo = berkokok (ayam)</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:68" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani cahag'e, suri boe kalimat ètu d'ara kurung ne.<bt>Some Yunani language writings do not have this sentence in brackets.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="69" />Hèia dhèu bhèni èèna ladhe nèdhi hari Petrus. Ka na peka dènge dhèu ètu sèra, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Nèngu ne ca dhèu nèti rèngu kahèi!&gt;&gt;<bt>The aformentioned woman, again saw Petrus, and she said to the people in that place, saying, "He here also, is one of those people!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="70" />Te ngaa Petrus pasili hari, ka na peka, &lt;&lt;Tao-tao èu huj'u! Ja'a tadhe boe Dhèu ne'e!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus denied again, and said, "You must be crazy! I don't know2 this man!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Nèbhu boe ka, dhèu èci ètu èèna kahèi, peka hari mi Petrus, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èu ne baku pasili, peka na, èu dènge boe dhèu se'e se! We! Miu se aa'i-aa'i mi, dhèu Galilea, si?&gt;&gt;<bt>Not long after that, one of the people who were also there, and spokke again to Petrus, saying, "You here, shouldn't deny saying that you were not with these people! We! You(PL) lot are all people from Galilea, right?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="71" />Ka Petrus pab'ala hari, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a bani subha! Ja'a tadhe boe Dhèu nèi!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Petrus responded again, saying, "I'm bold enough to swear.oath! I do not know2 that person!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="72" />Petrus dhu padhai lii nare mèka, kabèdhi laa, manu kokotoo ka dua hari kèna. Hèia Petrus sanèd'e lii dhu Yesus peka dènge nèngu, &lt;&lt;Ladhe manu kokotoo d'ai mèka dua hari, te èu pasili le Ja'a tèlu hari peka na èu tadhe boe Ja'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>Petrus had not.yet finished speaking, and suddenly, a chicken crowed the second time. So then Petrus remembered the words that Yesus had spoken to him, "When the shicken has not yet crowed two times, but3 you will already have denied Me three times saying you don't know2 Me!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ropa ngee nèdhi, hèia Petrus tangi d'ara pèd'a.<bt>When thinking that, Petrus cried with sad insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manu = ayam; tangi ngob'i-ngob'i ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">manu = ayam; tangi ngob'i-ngob'i = mengangis tersedu-sedu, whimpering</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ra rèti Lamatua Yesus asa madha gubernur Pilatus<bt>Lord Yesus in front of Gubernur (loan) Pilatus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:1-2, 11-14; Lukas 23:1-5; Yohanis 18:28-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Mad'ae aae era, dhèu-dhèu j'ue lii langu agama Yahudi sèra pare'a lii ho pamadhe Yesus. Ka ra èki rèti Ne, lasi asa madha gubernur Pilatus.<bt>Early in the morning, those people who decide the Jahudi religious court.cases reached an agreement to kill Yesus. And they tied Him up, and took him before Gubernur Pilatus.</bt><v n="2" />Ropa d'ai madha gubernur, ka na karèi Yesus, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Tasamia? Èu ne tare'a Dhèu Aae Yahudi, do?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they arrived in front of the gubernur, he asked Yesus, saying, "How is it? Are You truly the King of the Jahudi's, right?"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pare'a lii = sepakat, sakongkol; meda"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pare'a lii = sepakat, sakongkol; meda = kemarin; mèda = malam; mèdha = barang ; madha = mata; madhe = mati;@@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus dhaa, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Tare'a. Ama gubernur peka lèke kèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered, saying, "Right. Father Gubernur speaks correctly."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Hèia kètu agama Yahudi sèra peka dènge gubernur, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu ne'e tao sala ae titu kèna!&gt;&gt; Hèia ra lolo ka sasala Na èci-èci.<bt>So then the fathers of religion (coll) spoke to the gubernur, saying, "This person, has done lots of wrongs!" And they reported to him each of His wrongs (or: one-by-one).</bt><v n="4" />Ka gubernur karèi hari Yesus, &lt;&lt;Èu tadèngi boe lii padhai dhèu se'e, do? Dhèu se'e, pasala le Èu ae-ae. Èu b'ala ku laa!&gt;&gt;<bt>And the gubernur again asked Yesus, "Don't you hear what these people are saying, or [what]? These people have accused You of many things. Go ahead and respond now!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhaa = menjawab (pertanyaan yang ditujukan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhaa = menjawab (pertanyaan yang ditujukan kepada Yesus)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Te ngaa Yesus b'ala boe ca hèb'a sa, ka gubernur malaa.<bt>But Yesus didn't respond with even one word, and because of that the gubernur was amazed/confused.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gubernur Pilatus pama'ète, na, Yesus abhu huku madhe [\s2]<bt>Gubernur Pilatus decides, Yesus gets punished by death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:15-26; Lukas 23:13-25; Yohanis 18:39-19:16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tèu mai-tèu mai, dhu tema le, ladhe d'ai lod'o kalela Paska dhèu Yahudi, dhèu ae sèra paj'uj'u ana bèdho èci, ho gubernur patalale ne.<bt>Each year, it was already common, when the day arrived for the Jahudi people to do Paska (Passover), many people designated one prisoner for the gubernur to release him.</bt><v n="7" />Lod'o èèna, ana bèdho èci, ngara na Barabas. Uru èèna, ra kèpe ne, taga na palab'a dènge dhèu paredha Roma, aa na pamadhe dhèu kahèi.<bt>At that time, there was a prisoner named Barabas. Formerly they arrested him, because3 he opposed the people of the government of Roma, and he had also killed people.</bt><v n="8" />Lula lod'o tatao Paska èèna oe dètu le, dhèu ae lasi manèngi gubernur Pilatus, ka ra pa'oo-parodha, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ama gubernur! Lod'o tatao Paska dètu le! Lod'o sèmi ne'e, Ama gubernur patabuli ku ana bèdho èci, sama sèmi tèu-tèu uru sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because the day of doing Paska was already near, many-many people came [and] requested gubernur Pilatus, shouting.to.pressure saying, "Father Gubernur! They day of doing Paska is already near! On a day like this, Father Gubernur releases a prisoner, just like each year before now."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nèru = tiap; |b8:|r patabuli ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">nèru = tiap; <span class="Bold">8:</span> patabuli = lepaskan (possible candidate for salvation)@@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Hèia gubernur b'ala lii rèngu, &lt;&lt;Ladhe sèmi èèna, ja'a patabuli cee? Tasamia, ladhe ja'a patabuli Dhèu Aae Yahudi miu, do? Miu mo'o, do aad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>So then the gubernur responded to what they said, "If that's the way it is, who should I release? How about I release your-pl King of the Jahudi, or [what]? Do you(PL) want that, or not?"</bt><v n="10" />Gubernur peka sèmi èèna, lula nèngu ne'a le, kètu agama Yahudi ka rèti Yesus mai asa nèngu, taga ra kacèki dènge Yesus.<bt>The gubernur spoke like that, but he already knew that the important religious people had brought Yesus to him, because they hated/were jealous of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ro'o; no'o (vulgar in KM); mo'o;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ro'o; no'o (vulgar in KM); mo'o; ko'o; Kèri sèmi èna, = Kalau begitu,; <span class="Bold">10:</span> dèi boe = range from not like to hate; kacèki dènge = hate s.o.; nasa = angry</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Hèia kètu agama Yahudi se dadugu dhèu ae sèra, ho manèngi gubernur, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ji'i ngo'o boe Nèngu! Ji'i d'èi dhoka patabuli Barabas di!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then the chief priests incited those many people to request the gubernur, saying, "We(exc) don't want Him! We only want to free Barabas!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ka gubernur karèi hari dhèu ae sèra, &lt;&lt;Ladhe sèmi èèna, Yesus, dhu ra pangare na &lt;Dhèu Aae Yahudi&gt; èèna, ja'a tao Ne, tasamia?&gt;&gt;<bt>And the gubernur asked again those many people, "If it's like that, Yesus, who they call the King of the Jahudi, what should I do with Him?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ka aa'i-aa'i ra pa'oo, peka na, &lt;&lt;Pamadhe Ne! Paku Ne mi aj'u palolo-palèbha!&gt;&gt;<bt>And they all shouted, saying, "Kill Him! Nail Him to the *cross (=crossed wood; doublet)!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pa'oo = teriak ; kadhoe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pa'oo = teriak ; kadhoe = gantung; aj'u palolo-palèbha = kayu palang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Hèia gubernur karèi si, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Sasala Na ngaa? Ja'a parisa kore le. Te ngaa abhu boe sasala Na èci sa, dhu Nèngu tao!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernur asked them, saying, "What is His wrong? I have already examined/interrogated (loan) Him carefully. But there is not one wrong that He has done!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa dhèu se asa ka hino pa'oo-parodha, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Pamadhe Ne! Paku Ne mi aj'u palolo-palèbha!&gt;&gt;<bt>But these people, shouted [doublet] with even louder voices, saying, "Kill Him! Nail Him to the crossed wood!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Lula gubernur neo pakarej'e d'ara dhèu ae sèra, ka na patabuli Barabas madhutu dad'èi rèngu. Ka na paredha dhèu j'aga sèra lasi kalabhe Yesus pake gui.<bt>Because gubernur wanted to please the insides of those many people, he freed Barabas, according to their wishes. And he commanded the guard people (coll), to go beat Yesus with rope/cord.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ciu = tarabek ; madèka ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">ciu = tarabek ; madèka = tajam (blade) ; mariu = runcing (tip)</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sordad'u Roma kalabhe Lamatua Yesus pake cambuk. Cambuk ne, uru èèna, ra tao nèti dhari ceo dhu èki ètu suu gui èci. Catèka-catèka ra tao mèdha madèka aa mariu ètu suu dhari sèra. Mèdha madèka aa mariu sèra, sèmi rui badha, tamèru, do aad'o, na, bèsi. Ladhe kalabhe pahari-pahari pake cambuk sèmi ne'e, ka'uri dhèu bisa ciu eele.<bt>They beat the Lord Yesus using a whip (loan). This whip, formerly, they made from nine cord which were tied at the end with a handle. Sometimes they made sharp things on the ends of those cords. Those sharp things, were like animal bones, lead, or even iron. If whipped over and over using that whip, skins can peal.off throw.away.</bt></note>Game rare Ne, hèia sordad'u sèra rèti ka Yesus lasi neo paku pamadhe Ne ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha.<bt>After beating Him, the soldiers (assimilated loan) (coll) took Yesus to nail wanting kill Him on the *cross.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gui = rotan (for punishment); kalabhe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">gui = rotan (for punishment); kalabhe dènge gui = beat/punish w/rattan (short club); <span class="Bold">15:</span> madhèka = tajam; mariu = runcing</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sordad'u sèra game pa'asu Lamatua Yesus<bt>The soldiers (coll) take turns beating Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:27-31; Yohanis 19:2-3)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Èle èèna ka, sordad'u sèra ère rèti Yesus asa era dhu taleo èci ètu madha èmu gubernur.<bt>After that, those soldiers took Yesus away to the wide place at the house of the gubernur.</bt><note reference="15:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Era sordad'u sèra, ra pangare dènge lii Latin, peka na, <span class="Italic">praetorium.</span> Benteng èèna ètu d'ara kompleks èmu jabatan gubernur.<bt>The place of those soldiers, they called in the Latin language saying <span class="Italic">praetorium</span>. That place of the soldiers was in the complex (loan) of the official (loan) residence of the gubernur.</bt></note>Ka ra paroa anga sordad'u dhu leo sèra ca batalion, ho pakaboko.<bt>And they summoned all their companion soldiers (=their mates) one batalion, to gather together.</bt><v n="17" />Ra papake Yesus kodho madhera aae èci, dhu mea oe sèmi mangèru sa, sama sèmi mèdha-papake dhèu aae-dhèu aae. Ka rare loro aj'u dhu padhudhu, ho ènyu solo. Hèia ra ènyi solo padhudhu èèna mi kètu Yesus. Ka ra tao Ne, sèmi dhèu aae dhu ded'e hiu, dhu pake solo dhèu aae.<bt>And they clothed Yesus with a very long clothes, which was red tending toward blue, just like the clothes of kings/nobility. And they took creeping.branches that had thorns, and wove a hat. And they mashed.down that aforementioned thorny hat on the head of Yesus. And they did Him, like a new king, who wore the hat of a king.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="; |b17:|r dadana aj'u = ranting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">; <span class="Bold">17:</span> dadana aj'u = ranting pohon; Ènyu solo = anyam topi; mea-mangèru = purple, (but may be a fabricated term, UNS's stumbled on it, one response = jingga); ènyu = weave; ènyi = mash down on head; d'ed'e hiu = lantik, install, coronation; sanabhu = mirip (becoming archaic); loro aj'u = yang menjalar, vine, creeping branches (like bunga kertas); dadana = small branches</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00321C.tif" rtfFormat="width:6cm;textWrapping:around:horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra sangaja pakab'ua Yesus. Ra peka, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ama Dhèu Aae Yahudi dhu hua iia!&gt;&gt;<bt>All of them deliberately (=mockingly) showed honour/appreciation to Yesus, speaking, saying, "Father King of the Jahudi who is most respected!"</bt><v n="19" />Aa ra sangaja pacud'u kètu ho pakab'ua Yesus. Ka ra sabhuu ilu pèri-pèri hari mi rèhu Yesus. Sèmi èèna kahèi, ra d'eu kètu Yesus dènge gui pahari-pahari.<bt>And they mockingly bowed their heads to show.respect to Yesus. And they spit saliva several times at the face of Yesus. In the same way, they beat Yesus on the head with a short.punishing.stick repeatedly.</bt><v n="20" />Ropa ra tao rare sèmi èèna, ka ra bhoke eele kodho madhera nèti ua Na. Ka ra papake hari mèdha-papake Na. Èle ka, rèti Yesus asa li'u Yerusalem, ho neo paku Ne ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha d'ai madhe.<bt>When they had finished doing Yesus like that, they removed aforementioned long clothes that He had on His body, and they clothed [Him] again with His own clothes. After that, they took Yesus outside Yerusalem, to nail Him to the crossed wood until dead.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gui = rotan, cambuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">gui = rotan, cambuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ra paku Lamatua Yesus ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha<bt>They nail the Lord Yesus on the crossed wood</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:32-44; Lukas 23:26-43; Yohanis 19:17-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ropa rèngu kalua nèti Yerusalem, d'ai talora j'ara paraga dènge dhèu kota Kirene èci. Ngara na Simon, ama nèti Aleksander dènge Rufus. Ropa na neo maso asa Yerusalem, sordad'u sèra pakaseti ne pasae aj'u palolo-palèbha Yesus.<bt>When they went out from Yerusalem, arriving at the middle of the journey they met a person from the city of Kirene. His name was Simon, the father of Aleksander and Rufus. When he was about to enter Yerusalem, those soldiers forced him, to shoulder.carry the crossed wood of Yesus.</bt><note reference="15:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 16:13</note><v n="22" />Ère rèti Yesus asa era èci, ngara na Golgota. (Sasoa na, &lt;era rui kètu&gt;.)<bt>They took Yesus to a place, named Golgota. (Which means, 'place of head bone (=skull)'.)</bt><v n="23" />D'ai era èèna, ra neo hia Yesus ninu èi hua anggor manyilu dhu pab'ali dènge èi na'i, sèna ka Na taha rarii nèti nu'a-nu'a ètu ngi'u Na sèra. Te ngaa Yesus no'o boe ninu.<bt>Arriving at that place they wanted to give Yesus to drink bitter/sour juice of the anggor fruit which was mixed with medicine (idiom=tobacco juice) so He could endure pain2 from the fresh.wounds on His body (coll). But Yesus didn't want to drink.</bt><v n="24-25" />Hèia ra paku kacui-aai dènge haga Yesus ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha. Paku rare ka, ra patitu aj'u palolo-palèbha èèna, ele boe d'ara hake ceo mad'ae sa. Èle èèna ka, sordad'u sèra ère lot, ho re'a cee ka dhu abhu mèdha-papake Yesus.<bt>So they nailed the hands and feet of Yesus on the crossed wood. After nailing, they stood.up the crossed wood, around 9 hits (=o'clock) in the morning. After that, those soldiers drew lots (assimilated loan, cast lots has collocational clash, where they use draw lots), so they would know who got Yesus' clothes.</bt><note reference="15:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 22:19</note><v n="26" />Ka ra suri ètu papa èci dhu ra paku re dedha kètu Yesus, peka na,<bt>And they wrote on a small board, which they nailed above the head of Yesus, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakaseti = 1) baseti, 2) memaksa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pakaseti = 1) baseti, 2) memaksa (check lakaseti --rejected by UNS's); pasae = mengangkat sesuatu dengan bahu; <span class="Bold">22:</span> udu rui = tengkorok ; udu = kumpul; <span class="Bold">23:</span> taha rarii = tahan rasa sakit, menahan rasa sakit karena siksaan; na'i = tembako, tobacco; èi na'i = obat, medicine (lit. tobacco juice)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line Centered" usfm="qc">
      <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Ne'e ne, Dhèu Aae Yahudi&gt;&gt;</span>
      <bt>"This one here, is the King of the Jahudi"</bt>
    </p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Rèngu pake alasan èèna ka, ho huku pamadhe Yesus.<bt>They used that as the reason (loan), to punish Yesus with death.</bt><v n="27" />Ètu èèna, ra paku parapo dhèu dua kahèi pa'èci dènge Yesus. Èci re cabèka g'ana, aa èci hari re cabèka kariu Yesus.<bt>In that place they also nailed two robbers together with Yesus. One there on the right side; one again there on the left side of Yesus.</bt><v n="28" />[Dènge j'ara ne, rèngu madhutu sama sèmi dhu ra suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Ama Lamatua, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ra tao Ne sama sèmi dhèu bhelu.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[In this way, they followed just like had been written in the Writings of God, which said, "They did/made Him, just like a bad/evil person."]</bt><note reference="15:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani dhu uru tèka pamaso boe ayat 28.<bt>The oldest Yunani language writings do not enter verse 28.</bt></note><note reference="15:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:12</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01836b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu kako re èèna, ladhe rèdhi Yesus dhu ra paku ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha. Ka ra pakareko kètu, aa ra padhai lii pamakae Yesus, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Heh! Èu ne peka na, Èu bisa paguri eele Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i, ho d'ara tèlu lod'o, Èu pakèd'i hari, si?<bt>The people who walked by there, saw Yesus hung on the crossed wood and they shook their heads, and they spoke to cause.shame to Yesus, saying, "He! You here were saying You could cause the Temple to collapse, so that in three days [you] could build it up again, right?</bt><note reference="15:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 22:8, 109:25, Markus 14:58, Yohanis 2:19</note><v n="30" />Èu puru sèku nèti aj'u palolo-palèbha èèna, ho patabuli ngi'u Èu! Ladhe sèmi èèna, heka ji'i parcaya, na, Èu ne, Ana Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>You try to descend now from that crossed wood, to free Yourself! If its like.that, only.then we-e will really believe You-sg here are God's Child.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakareko kètu = goyang kepala.; |b30:|r"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pakareko kètu = goyang kepala.; <span class="Bold">30:</span> patalale ; pataleo ; patabuli ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, kètu agama Yahudi sèra, padhai lii pamakae Yesus, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Nèngu ne, patabuli le dhèu leo nèti rupa-rupa j'aj'èra, te ngaa Nèngu bisa boe patabuli ngi'u Nèngu unu Na nèti j'aj'èra ne'e.<bt>In the same way, the fathers of the Jahudi religion (coll) spoke to cause.shame to Yesus, saying, "He has released/saved other people from various sorts of suffering, but He cannot free Himself from this suffering/difficulty.</bt><v n="32" />Nèngu peka unu Na, Nèngu ne &lt;Kristus&gt;, dhu uru èèna Ama Lamatua moa tèke le. Dhèu leo peka na, Nèngu ne Dhèu Aae Isra'el. Ladhe tare'a sèmi èèna, hud'i laa Na puru nèti aj'u palolo-palèbha ne, sèna ka ji'i ngèdhi Ne. Heka ji'i parcaya Ne kèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>He Himself said that He is Kristus, who God promised from before. Other people say that He is the King of Israel. If that is true, He must descend from this crossed wood, so that we(exc) can see Him [do that]. Only.then will we believe in Him."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pamamuri = cause to live, bring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pamamuri = cause to live, bring to life, save; sui = tebus, redeem; soru iisi = lindungi diri; soro = 1) sorong, extend (hand), 2) jemput; soro tèke = abandon, leave behind; sori = pisahkan, separate from difficulty, save (from Benyamin, but not known by others)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sèmi èèna kahèi, ama-ama agama Yahudi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Sèmi èèna kahèi, ama-ama agama Yahudi sèra, padhai lii pamakae Yesus, aku rèngu na, "Nèngu ne, pamamuri le dhèu leo, te ngaa ngi'u Nèngu mesa Na, abhu boe Na pamamuri.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dhèu dua dhu ra paku sama-sama dènge Yesus sèra, padhai lii pamakae Yesus kahèi.<bt>The two people who were nailed together with Yesus (coll), they also spoke to cause.shame to Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus madhe<bt>Yesus dies</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:45-56; Lukas 23:44-49; Yohanis 19:28-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />D'ara lod'o titu mera sa, era èèna maroga, toke d'ai hake tèlu loo nihia.<bt>In the middle of the day (lit., suddenly, that place was very dark, untuk around three in the afternoon.</bt><v n="34" />D'ai hake tèlu nihia, hèia Yesus pa'oo pake lii Aram, peka na, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Eloi! Eloi! Lema sabaktani?&gt;&gt;</span> (Dhu sasoa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua Ja'a! Lamatua Ja'a! Nga tao ka, Ama Ku tèke eele Ja'a sèmi ne'e?&gt;&gt;)<bt>At three in the afternoon, Yesus shouted using Aramaic saying, "<span class="Italic">Eloi! Eloi! Lema sabaktani?</span>" (Which means, saying, "My God2! My God2! Why has Father abandoned/turned back on Me like this?")</bt><note reference="15:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 22:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Abhu pèri-pèri dhèu ètu èèna, tadèngi lii pa'oo Yesus. Ka ra peka, &lt;&lt;Miu nanene ku laa! Te Na paroa Elia, dhèu nèti lii padhai Ama Lamatua uru èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>Several people who were there, heard what Yesus shouted, and they said, "You(PL) listen here! Cause He's calling Elia, God's spokesperson from before."</bt><v n="36" />Ka dhèu èci rai la'e nare ula dhasi, ka na cèb'u asa d'ara èi hua anggor manyilu. Hèia nare ula èèna, èki ètu suu tatea èci, ka na soro asa panyoro Yesus ho Na camuci. Dhèu èèna peka, &lt;&lt;Èdhi tatae sèku. Cee ne'a, tao-tao Elia mai, ho papuru Ne nèti aj'u palolo-palèbha èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>And one person ran [and] got moss/sponge, and he put it into sour/bitter juice of the anggor fruit, and he took that sponge [and] tied it to the end of a staff, and he extended it to Yesus' lips, and He sucked it. [Greek unclear: irrealis purpose, not clear if fulfilled.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kadosa = cuka; tao-tao = jangan-jangan;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">kadosa = cuka; tao-tao = jangan-jangan; tatae sèku = wait momentarily ; hia Na camuci here irrealis ; ula dhasi = sponge</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 69:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Hèia Yesus pa'oo hari ca tèka, heka Na madhe kèna.<bt>So Yesus shouted once again, only.then did He die.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ètu d'ara Èmu Kapua Manèngi-Mangaj'i abhu bèla dhu bhèla aae, ra kadhoe pa'abhe Kama Luri Mola-Mèci. Ropa Yesus ma'ète a'ae, bèla ne mae cèri bagi mi dua, nèti dedha toke d'ai haha.<bt>In the *Temple, there was a cloth which was big [and] wide which they hung closing.off the Room of God2 which is holy2. When Yesus took His last breath (lit. separated His breath; = died), this cloth tore apart in two, from top to bottom.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bèla = yang dimaksud kain gorden;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">bèla = yang dimaksud kain gorden; bèla dhu bhèla aae = kain yg lebar besar</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 26:31-33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ètu Golgota abhu komedhaa sordad'u j'aga dhu titu dètu aj'u palolo-palèbha Yesus. Ropa ladhe nèdhi mamadhe Yesus, na cag'ag'a. Hèia na peka, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ira ii! Mema tare'a! Dhèu ne'e ne, Ana Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>At Golgota, there was the head of the guarding soldiers who was standing near the crossed wood of Yesus. When he saw Yesus' death, he was surprised. And he said, saying, "It's really true! this person here was the Child of God."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40-41" />Abhu pèri-pèri dhèu bhèni dhu madhutu lasi asa era èèna kahèi. Ra titu nèti kaj'èu, ladhe rèdhi mamadhe Yesus ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha èèna. Rèngu se ka dhu uru èèna lalau-lalo'o Yesus ètu Galilea. Rèngu sèra, nuka: Salome, Maria nèti rae Magdala, dènge Maria èci hari (nuka ina Yakobis dènge Yoses),<bt>And then several women also, who followed to that place, standing at a distance, saw Yesus' death at that crossed wood. These were those who had been serving2 Yesus in Galilea. Their names were Salome, Maria from the village of Magdala, and another Maria (being Maria the mother of Yakobis and Yoses),</bt><note reference="15:40-41" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani cahag'e suri, peka na, &lt;ina Yoses&gt;. Cahag'e hari, peka na, &lt;ina Yosef&gt;.<bt>Some of the writings in the Yunani language say, "the mother of Yoses'. Some others again 'the mother of Yosef'.</bt></note>dènge dhèu bhèni leo hari dhu mai asa Yerusalem, sama-sama dènge Yesus.<bt>with other women again who came to Yerusalem, together with Yesus.</bt><note reference="15:40-41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 8:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ra padhane Lamatua Yesus<bt>They bury the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:57-61; Lukas 23:50-56; Yohanis 19:38-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42-43" />Ropa lod'o oe cèna, hèia dhèu èci tenge j'ara ho papuru ngi'u aae Yesus nèti aj'u palolo-palèbha. Dhèu èèna, ngara na Yusuf, nèti kota Arimatea. Nèngu ne'e kahèi, ca dhèu dhu j'ue lii langu agama Yahudi. Nèngu dhèu d'ara be'a kahèi. Aa nèngu mate nèbhu le paredha Ama Lamatua mai.<bt>When the sun was sinking, a person looked for a way to bring down the body of Yesus from that crossed wood. That person was named Yusuf, from the city of Arimatea. He also was a person who decided court.cases of the Jahudi religion. This person had good insides. He had been waiting for the government of God to descend coming.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sordadu ~ sordad'u ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">sordadu ~ sordad'u ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Lod'o Yesus madhe èèna, lèke hari Jumat. Bèli na, lèke lod'o manèngi-mangaj'i dhèu Yahudi. Nèti èèna ka, Yusuf neo papuru eele ngi'u aae Yesus ètu d'ara lod'o hari Jumat èèna. Ka na pabani iisi na, la'e paraga dènge gubernur Pilatus, manèngi ho papuru ngi'u aae Yesus.<bt>When Yesus died, it was Friday (loan). The next day was the day of worship for the Jahudi people. Because of that, Yusuf wanted to take down the body of Yesus on that Friday. And so he got up the courage (lit. emboldened himself2) and went to meet with Gubernur Pilatus to request to take down the body of Yesus.</bt><v n="44" />Ropa gubernur tadèngi lii manèngi Yusuf ne, na malaa. Hèia na peka, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Eea! Nga tao ka, dhèu Ne madhe malai sa mia ne! Ja'a ngee, na, dhae madhe mèka!&gt;&gt;<bt>When gubernur heard this request of Yusuf, he was amazed/surprised. So he spoke, saying, "Eea! Why, did this person die so quickly in that way? I thought he wouldn't be dead yet!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèia na pua dhèu lasi paroa komedhaa, ka na karèi ne, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Sa mia? Yesus madhe le, do dhae?&gt;&gt;<bt>So he ordered a person to go summon the head of those guarding soldiers, and he asked, saying, "How about it? Is Yesus already dead, or not yet?"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Komedhaa èèna b'ala, peka na, &lt;&lt;Tare'a, ama! Na madhe le karèi deo na.&gt;&gt; Ropa gubernur tadèngi nare lii dhaa èèna, hèia na hia Yusuf la'e nare ngi'u aae Yesus.<bt>The head of the soldiers responded, saying, "Correct, sir! He's already been dead since earlier." When the gubernur heard what the head of the soldiers said, he sent Yusuf to get/take the body of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karèi deo na = dari tadi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">karèi deo na = dari tadi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01847b.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;verticalPosition:bottom">Rèngu rèti ngi'u aae Lamatua Yesus asa d'ara ro'a<bt>They take the Lord Yesus' corpse into the hole</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Hèia Yusuf la'e hèli bèla madhera dhu kab'ua èci, ka na la'e asa Golgota. D'ai nèi, ka na papuru ngi'u aae Yesus nèti aj'u palolo-palèbha. Na pahutu ngi'u aae Yesus dènge bèla hiu. Tèu èèna, ra heka pae rare ro'a èci ètu d'ara hadhu aae. Hèia ra nedhe rèti ngi'u aae Yesus asa d'ara ro'a èèna. Ka ra loli rare hadhu kabela dhu kapai èci, ho ra bèdho paie hèb'a ro'a èèna. Èle èèna ka, Yusuf si lèpa.<bt>So Yusuf went to Golgota, and he took down the body of Yesus from up on the crossed wood. He covered Yesus body with a new cloth. They had recently finished carving/chiseling a hole in a big rock. So they lifted/carried the body of Yesus into that hole. They rolled up a flat stone which was big, to close up the mouth of that hole. After that, Yusuf mob returned home.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padhane = implies covering with soil,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">padhane = implies covering with soil, UNS's say any kind of burial, but not cremation ; kae paja =women's wrap ; bèla madhera = long cloth</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Lod'o èèna, Maria nèti rae Magdala, dènge Maria èci hari, (ina Yoses), madhutu d'ai era èèna kahèi. Dua ra rèdhi era dhu ra padhane Yesus, ka ra patadhe paie era èèna.<bt>At that time, Maria from the village of Magdala, and another Maria (the mother of Yoses), followed until they arrived also at that place. The two of them saw the place where they buried Yesus, and they took good note of that place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus mamuri hari!<bt>The Lord Yesus lives again</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:1-8; Lukas 24:1-12; Yohanis 20:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Bèli èèna, lèke hari Sabtu, nuka lod'o sabaj'a dhèu Yahudi. Ropa lod'o cèna la'e, Maria nèti rae Magdala, Maria dhu leo hari (ina Yakobis), dènge Salome, lasi hèli èi hèu mèngi, sèna ka bèli rèngu bisa lasi pasuti mi ngi'u aae Yesus madhutu ad'a dhèu Yahudi.<bt>The next day was Saturday, that is the Yahudi people's day of prayer. After the sun had already set, Maria from Magdala, that other Maria (that.is Yakobis' mother), and Salome, went to buy fragrant oil, in.order.that tomorrow they wanted to go sprinkle it on Yesus' corpse, following the Yahudi people's tradition.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Èle èèna, Maria nèti Magdala, Maria"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Èle èèna, Maria nèti Magdala, Maria dhu leo hari (ina Yakobis), dènge Salome, ra mate dai lod'o cèna, ho èle lod'o sabaj'a. Heka ra lasi hèli èi hèu mèngi, sèna ka bèli rèngu lasi pakose mi ngi'u Yesus, madhutu ad'a dhèu Yahudi.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ropa hari Migu mad'ae aae èèna, tèlu ra lasi asa ro'a Yesus.<bt>When it was early in the morning on Sunday (loan), the three of them went to the hole/grave of Yesus.</bt><v n="3-4" />Ètu talora j'ara, tèlu ra padhue, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Waa! D'ai nèi, na, cee ka dhu bisa loli eele hadhu aae èèna nèti hèb'a ro'a? Èdhi tèlu ti bisa boe, lula hadhu èèna kapai bia!&gt;&gt;<bt>In the middle of the journey, the three of them were discussing, saying, "Waa! When arriving there, who is it that will roll away that huge stone, from the mouth of the hole? Just the three of us(inc) alone, can't do it, because that stone is too heavy!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari Migu = hari Minggu; |b4:|r"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hari Migu = hari Minggu; <span class="Bold">4:</span> ti = sendiri (jamak -1p) ; sendiri berubah bergantung subyek</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa ropa rèngu d'ai ro'a èèna, rèdhi hadhu èèna dhu hari eele le nèti hèb'a ro'a.<bt>But when they arrived there, they saw that stone which was already moved away, from that mouth hole.</bt><v n="5" />Hèia bhèni se maso asa d'ara. Rèngu cag'ag'a titu kèna, lula ètu d'ara ro'a èèna, rèdhi ana mone ngèru èci madhèdi ètu sebhe g'ana rèngu, dhu pake mèdha pudhi lao-lao.<bt>So those women entered into that hole. They were very surprised, because inside that hole they saw a young man, sitting on their right side, who was wearing pure white clothes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pudhi heo lo'a-lo'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">pudhi heo lo'a-lo'a</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Hèia mone ngèru èèna, peka dènge rèngu, &lt;&lt;Baku madha'u! Ja'a ke'a, na, miu mai tenge Yesus dhèu Nasaret, dhu ra paku pamadhe ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha. Na aad'o heka ètu ne'e, lula Na mamuri hari le! Mai ho ladhe unu mi, te ngi'u Yesus aad'o heka ètu era dhu ra paj'unu Na.<bt>So then that aforementioned young man said to them, "Eee! Don't be afraid! I know that you(PL) are looking for Yesus, the person from nasaret who they nail to death on that crossed wood. He is not here any more. Because He is already living again! Come to see for yourselves, but3 Yesus body is no longer here in the place where they laid Him.</bt><v n="7" />De lami ka lai-lai, ho lole dènge Petrus si, peka na, Yesus mamuri hari le! Na la'e uuru le asa Galilea. Èèna na rèngu paraga dènge Yesus ètu nèi, sèmi dhu uru èèna Na peka mema le dènge rèngu. De lami ka!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, go quickly, to tell Petrus (coll). Tell him that Yesus is already living again! He has gone first before them to Galilea. Later, they will meet with Yesus there, just like before, He already said to them beforehand. So go on!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari = geser; |b5:|r ro'a ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">hari = geser; <span class="Bold">5:</span> ro'a = 1) hole, 2) grave</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:32, Markus 14:28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ropa bhèni se rèdhi heka ngi'u Yesus ètu era dhu ra paj'unu Na, rèngu cag'ag'a. Ka rai asa li'u lasi. Hèia rèngu lèpa dènge ka, ra peka boe dènge dhèu èci sa ètu j'ara, lula rèngu madha'u titu kèna.<bt>When these women so longer saw the body of Yesus, in the place where they laid Him, they were surprised. And they ran outside. Then they went-home then, and they didn't tell even a single person on the way, because they were terrified.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">[Yesus paraga dènge Maria nèti rae Magdala<bt>[Yesus meets with Maria from the village of Magdala</bt><note reference="16:9-20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani dhu uru risi sèra, dènge dhu be'a risi, tèja ètu ayat 8. Lii lolo Markus pa'èle dènge dua j'ara: èci dhu ako madhera (Markus 16:9-20), aa èci hari dhu bab'a (Markus 16:9-10). Madhutu a'abhu dhèu d'èlu-mèu Lii Lolo Markus, dua nats se'e, ra suri limuri. Dua-dua sèra lole lula-nèti Yesus mamuri hari nèti mamadhe Na, dènge sasab'a nèti dhèu dhu parcaya Yesus sèra.<bt>The oldest writings in the Yunani language, and those that are best, end at verse (loan) 8. Markus' story ends in two ways: one which is long (Markus 16:9-20), and another which is short (Markus 16:9-10). According to the opinion of people who know Markus' story very well (=expert), these two ways were written afterward. Both of them tell of the resurrection of Yesus from His death, and the work/task of people who believe in Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:9-10; Yohanis 20:11-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Hari Migu mad'ae aae era, Yesus pad'elo uuru ngi'u Na mi Maria nèti Magdala, dhu uru èèna, Yesus babège eele nidhu pidhu nèti nèngu.<bt>Early on Sunday morning, Yesus revealed Himself to Maria from Magdala, who formerly Yesus had evicted seven evil.spirits from her.</bt><v n="10" />Ropa na nèdhi nare Yesus, hèia la'e dènge ka, peka dènge dhèu-dhèu dhu uru èèna madhutu Yesus. Dhèu sèra pakaboko taruu ètu era èci. Rèngu ètu d'ara susa era, taga ra ngee mamadhe Yesus.<bt>When she saw Yesus then, she went and told the people who formerly had been following Yesus. those people were gathered together continually in one place. They still were having difficult2 insides, because4 they were thinking about that death of Yesus.</bt><v n="11" />Ka Maria peka dènge rèngu, aku nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Nga tao ka miu susa era? Susa ia ka, te Yesus mamuri hari le! Deo na, ja'a heka paraga dènge Ne kèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>And Maria told them, saying, "Why are you still in difficulty2? Don't be sad! Cause Yesus is already alive again! I've just met with Him, just now!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beke = kumpul malam (mete) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">beke = kumpul malam (mete) ; Ja'a heka paraga dènge Ne, lai-lai ne'e! = (vague, can be last week)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ja'a heka paraga dènge Ne, lai-lai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Ja'a heka paraga dènge Ne, lai-lai ne'e!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa rèngu aa'i-aa'i dhaa, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Èu ne, monya! Ji'i lèka boe.&gt;&gt;<bt>But they responded, saying, "You are tricking/deceiving us! We(exc) are not taken in by it."</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus pad'elo ngi'u Na mi dhèu dua<bt>Yesus reveals himself to two people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 24:13-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Èle èèna ka, dhèu madhutu Yesus dhèu dua lasi asa rae èci. Ropa d'ai talora j'ara, Yesus pad'elo ngi'u dènge si. Te ngaa Nèngu ub'a le. Nèbhu boe, heka ra tadhe Ne.<bt>After that, two of Yesus' followers (broad sense) went to a village. While they were on they way, Yesus revealed himself to them. But He had changed. Soon/after awhile, they recognised Him.</bt><v n="13" />Hèia dua ra lèpa hari, lasi peka dènge angalai ra sèra, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Wee! Miu nanene ku laa! Lai-lai deo na, ji'i paraga le dènge Yesus ètu j'ara!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then the two of them returned.home again [and] spoke to their companions (coll), saying, "Wee! You(PL) listen up! Just recently we(exc) have met with Yesus on the road!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa angalai ra aa'i-aa'i dhaa, aku rèngu na, &lt;&lt;Eeh! Miu baku monya sèmi èèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>But all those friends said, saying, "Ee! You should not trick/deceive us like that!"</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus pad'elo ngi'u mi ana madhutu Na aa'i-aa'i<bt>Yesus reveals himself to all of His followers (coll)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:16-20; Lukas 24:36-49; Yohanis 20:19-23; Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 1:6-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Èle èèna ka, Yesus paraga dènge ana madhutu Na sèra, dhèu canguru èci, ropa ra madhèdi ra'a-rinu. Ka Na jèke si, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Wee! Miu kètu hadhu pa'ae sa mia ne! Dhèu peka le dènge miu, rèngu rèdhi le Ja'a dènge musi madha rèngu, te ngaa miu parcaya boe! Aku miu na, dhèu sèra monya! De ne'e ne, Ja'a unu ku mai. Mema tare'a Ja'a madhe, te ngaa Ja'a mamuri hari le! De mèdhi le, sina ma!<bt>After that, Yesus met with His followers (coll), eleven people, who were sitting eating-drinking. And He scolded them, saying, "Wee! You(PL) are so very stubborn (lit. rock heads)! People have already spoken with you that they have already seen Me with their own eyeballs, but you didn't believe! According to you, those people were talking nonsense! Na! Now, I myself have come. It's really true, I died, but I am alive again! So now you have seen, ya!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />De lami ka asa mia-mia palème rai-haha ne. Peka dènge dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra Lii Lolo Be'a Ja'a ne.<bt>After that, Yesus sent them, saying, "Go on to everywhere on this earth, [and] tell everyone My Good News2.</bt><note reference="16:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 1:8</note><v n="16" />Dhèu cee dhu parcaya Ja'a aa abhu sarani, èèna na Ama Lamatua hia ne mamuri sèna ka na bisa pea taruu dènge Ne ètu sorga. Te ngaa cee dhu parcaya boe Ja'a, èèna na nèngu abhu huku nèti Lamatua, ka Lamatua core eele ne asa li'u la'e, ho na pea taruu ètu nèi.<bt>Whoever believes in Me, and gets *baptised, God will give him/her life to stay continually with Him in heaven2. But whoever does not believe, s/he will get heavy punishment from God2 so that He will throw him away to the outside, to stay/live continually there.</bt><v n="17" />Aa dhèu dhu parcaya Ja'a sèra, rèngu tao rupa-rupa tadha malaa, sèna ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i sèra re'a, peka na, &lt;&lt;Koasa ra mema mai nèti Ama Lamatua!&gt;&gt; Conto sèmi, èèna na rèngu bisa babège eele nidhu pake kolongara Ja'a. Ladhe èèna na, Ama Lamatua hia si padhai lii pake lii leo dhu rèngu mesa ra dhane rare boe.<bt>And those people who believe in Me, they will do all sorts of amazing signs, so that everyone will say, "That power has truly come from God!" So they will be able to evict evil.spirits, using My name2/reputation. Later on God will give them/allow them to speak using other languages which they do not know.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhane = paham"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">dhane = paham</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ladhe rèngu kèpe mege dhu dènge raco, do, rinu lèke raco, ngaa-ngaa tao boe. Ladhe ra tao kacui-aai asa dhèu pèd'a, dhèu èèna èle nèti papèd'a-tarègu na.&gt;&gt;<bt>If they hold snakes that are poisonous, or they drink poison, nothing will happen. If they put their hand on a sick person, that person will be healed from the sickness."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="uku kedi = heavy punishment ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">uku kedi = heavy punishment ; uku = suanggi ;; <span class="Bold">18:</span> mege kaisao = sejenis ular yg berbisa (pendek, berbisa, hijau); calaka; èna ka oo = sekalipun; èna na = abis itu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua Yesus ca'e asa sorga<bt>Yesus ascends to heaven2</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 24:50-53; Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 1:9-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ropa padhai lii èle dènge ana madhutu Na sèra, hèia Ama Lamatua paca'e Yesus asa sorga. Ètu nèi, Nèngu j'aj'i ai g'ana Ama Na, ka rèd'u paredha sama-sama.<bt>When finished speaking with His followers (coll), then God took up Yesus to heaven2. Yonder, He is the right hand of His Father, and they hold government together.</bt><note reference="16:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 1:9-11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Èle èèna, hèia ana madhutu Na sèra madhutu paredha Na. Rèngu lasi asa mia-mia, ho lole mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i Lii Lolo Be'a Yesus. Hèia Ama Lamatua hia si koasa ho ra tao tadha-tadha malaa dhu Yesus peka le dènge rèngu. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu ae parcaya Yesus, taga rèngu re'a le Lii Lolo Be'a èèna, lèke tare'a-re'a.]<bt>So then after that, His followers followed His commands. They went all over the place to tell all people the Good Story about Yesus. And God gave them power to do amazing signs of various sorts which Yesus had told them. Because of that, many people believed in Yesus, because3 they already knew that Good Story was true.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">[Ra pa'èle lii lolo Markus madhutu sasuri leo dhu uru-uru sèra<bt>[The end of Mark's story, according other old writings (coll)</bt><note reference="16:9-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani dhu uru risi sèra, dènge dhu be'a risi, tèja ètu ayat 8. Lii lolo Markus pa'èle dènge dua j'ara: èci dhu ako madhera (Markus 16:9-20), aa èci hari dhu bab'a (Markus 16:9-10). Madhutu a'abhu dhèu d'èlu-mèu Lii Lolo Markus, dua nats se'e, ra suri limuri. Dua-dua sèra lole lula-nèti Yesus mamuri hari nèti mamadhe Na, dènge sasab'a nèti dhèu dhu parcaya Yesus sèra.<bt>The oldest writings in the Yunani language, and those that are best, end at verse (loan) 8. Markus' story ends in two ways: one which is long (Markus 16:9-20), and another which is short (Markus 16:9-10). According to the opinion of people who know Markus' story very well (=expert), these two ways were written afterward. Both of them tell of the resurrection of Yesus from His death, and the work/task of people who believe in Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ropa bhèni dhèu tèlu se d'ai era Petrus si, ka ra peka mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i, lii lole dhu ana ngèru deo na peka dènge rèngu ètu ro'a.<bt>When the women, those three people, arrive at the place of Petrus (coll), they told everybody the story of that aforementioned young man speaking to them at the hole/grave.</bt><v n="10" />Èle ka, Yesus unu Na hia paredha mi ana madhutu Na, ho lasi peka-padhai Lii Lolo Be'a Na asa mia-mia palème rai-haha ne. Lii Lolo Be'a pad'elo j'ara, sèna ka Ama Lamatua saku eele sasala-sasigo dhèu, ho ra mamuri taruu dènge Ne.<bt>After that, Yesus himself, commanded His followers, to go [and] tell this Good Story everywhere all over this world. This Good Story shows the way so that God wipes away the sins2 of people, so they can live continually with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Èle ka, Yesus unu na, hia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:38:29Z">Èle ka, Yesus unu na, hia paredha ma ana madhutu Na, ho lasi peka padhae, Lii Lolo Be'a ne, asa mia-mia palème rai-haha ne. Lii Lolo Be'a ne, padelo j'ara sèna ka Ama Lamatua hia dhèu mamuri nèti sasala-sigo rèngu ho ra mamuri taruu dènge Ne.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Lii Lolo Be'a mema lèke mola-mola! Nèti èèna ka, na taha taruu toke d'ai mia-mia la'e.]<bt>This Good Story is really reliably true! Because of that, it endures continually, until the end of time (=to the point of whatever-whatever).]</bt></p>
    <fig path="maps\bible\palestin.bmp" rtfFormat="width:10.5cm" />
  </book>
</bible>